title: morgh-o polo
directions: Cook chicken with onions, turmeric, salt and pepper in vegetable oil.
Add remaining ingredients to chicken mixture and steam.
Rinse the rice several times in warm water; soak in warm water, then set aside.
Bring a large pot of salty (2 tablespoons) water to a rapid boil.
Drain the water from the soaked rice and pour the rice in boiling water.
Boil 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally to prevent the grains from sticking together.
Drain the rice in a colander; rinse cold tap water over rice.
Cook the meat with onion and spices (salt and turmeric).
Boil meat with water until well cooked.
Mix lentils together with rice and raisins.
Place melted butter in bottom of the pot.
Sprinkle half of the rice mixture in the pot with meat on top; cover with onions.
Pour over the top any juices remaining from cooked meat. Cover the pot at low temperature; steam for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello and add rest of ingredients.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan and chill until firm.
Spread with 1 cup sour cream (I use fat-free) and pour remaining mixture on top.
Chill.

title: cold taco dip
directions: Spread refried beans on round platter.
Mix sour cream and taco mix.
Spread on top of beans.
Add layers of tomatoes, black olives, pepper, cheese and scallions.
Spoon salsa over top and chill overnight.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: tangy german potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes; place in a saucepan and cover with water. Cook until tender but firm.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, and vanilla.
Add flour, salt, and nuts.
Mix well.
Chill dough.
Roll into 1 inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 - 12 minutes or until set.
Cool slightly.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Cool completely. Roll in powdered sugar again.

title: meringue bars
directions: Cream the 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and shortening.
Add the water and egg yolks.
Add the flour, baking powder and soda.
Beat well and press into flat greased pan.
Sprinkle with the chips and walnuts.
Beat the egg whites until stiff.
Add the brown sugar and spread lightly over the chips and nuts.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in the eggs, one at a time, then add the vanilla.
Sift the flour, baking powder and soda together.
Work the wet and dry mixtures together thoroughly with your hands. If the dough is not stiff enough, add a little more flour.
Form the dough into two rolls.
Chill them one hour, then slice into 1/2-inch slices and place on ungreased baking sheet or take the dough by spoonful and roll into balls and place on baking sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: smoked turkey salad
directions: Mix to taste with Miracle Whip, thinned with pineapple juice.

title: jello icebox pie
directions: Chill Pet milk.
Put 1 cup boiling water in box of jello. Stir and let cool.
Whip Pet milk until stiff.
Add sugar and then jello.
Pour over vanilla wafer pie crust.

title: easy spaghetti sauce(low-fat)
directions: In a food processor or blender, combine all ingredients (except beef).
Process until smooth. Brown ground beef; drain and add blended sauce.
Serve over spaghetti noodles.
Serves 4.

title: fried turkey
directions: You will also need this equipment:
1 cattle syringe (can be purchased at a feed store), 10 gallon pot with basket and Butane cooker.

title: burger pizza
directions: Roll out biscuit dough to fit 1 (14-inch) pizza pan or 2 pizza pans. Brown meat in skillet, then crumble over dough.
Sprinkle over meat the salt and spices. Pour sauce over this and top with cheeses. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes. Cut in wedges and serve hot.

title: make-ahead lettuce salad(makes 8 to 10 servings)
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch glass dish, layer lettuce, cauliflower, mayonnaise, onions, bacon and cheese.
Sprinkle with sugar. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Toss just before serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix ingredients by hand until creamy, roll into balls and dip in chocolate or put enough chocolate in the bottom of a paper cup or candy mold to cover bottom.
Add peanut butter ball, then cover the top with chocolate.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger in pan.
Stir in taco seasoning.
Mix well. Spread hamburger in baking dish.
Spread sour cream over meat. Spread taco sauce on the sour cream.
May not need the whole jar of taco sauce.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake until cheese is melted, about 30 minutes at 325°.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: church windows
directions: Melt chocolate and oleo.
Then add nuts and marshmallows. Roll on wax paper (I divide mine into two).
Roll in coconut. Chill 1 hour and slice.

title: quick spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate 2 days prior to serving. Serve with chips and crackers.

title: texas brownies
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine flour and sugar.
In a heavy saucepan combine margarine, coffee or water and cocoa.
Stir and heat to boiling.
Pour over the flour and sugar.
Add the buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into well-greased 11 x 17 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. While brownies cook, prepare frosting.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Place in unbaked pie shell. Put quiche in oven over foil in case of spills.
Bake about 40 minutes or until center of quiche becomes solid.

title: meat sauce for spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger and drain well.
Add all the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer on low heat for 45 minutes to one hour. Serve on top of your favorite spaghetti or linguine.

title: garbanzo-soy-oat patties
directions: Combine all ingredients except rolled oats in blender and chop fine, or beans may be ground in a food chopper and combined with other ingredients.
Place in bowl.
Add rolled oats and let stand 10 minutes to absorb moisture.
Drop from tablespoon on sprayed baking pan or electric skillet.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes until nicely browned.
Turn over.
Cover and bake 10 minutes more.
Reduce heat and cook 10 minutes more.
Serve with tomato sauce.
Yield:
4 (2 patty) servings.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Blend Crisco and margarine together; add sugar and blend well. Add eggs, one at a time and blend well.
Add buttermilk and flour, a little at a time, until all is used.
Put in lined cake pan or floured cake pan.
Bake at 325° about 1 1/2 hours.

title: spanakopita(spinach pie)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute scallions and parsley in about 2 tablespoons of the butter until soft.
Add spinach, salt, pepper and dill.
Cool mixture.
Lightly beat eggs; add cheeses and spinach mixture.
Mix well.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let stand overnight, then fold in the Whip until stiff.
Add pecans.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients. Form small balls with batter.
Put balls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen sausage balls.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix and bake at 400° until set and brown.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Have cookie sheets ready.
Stir peanut butter, sugar and eggs in bowl until well blended (it will be sticky).
With floured hands, roll level measuring tablespoons into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Place 1 1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown and drain the ground beef.
Add the refried beans and taco seasoning.
Mix well.
Put into a 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Top with the sour cream, taco sauce and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: mexican rabbit
directions: Melt butter.
Add green pepper and onion.
Cook until soft. Add cheese; stir until melted.
Mix corn and egg; add to cheese mixture.
Add all other ingredients and heat thoroughly.
Serve on toast with crisp slices of ham or bacon.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix
peaches, pineapple and pineapple juice and refrigerate
a couple
of hours.	Add grapes and kiwi.
Just before serving, add strawberries and bananas.

title: teacher's fresh apple cake
directions: *Apples
do
not
need to be peeled.
They can be cored and chopped or grated in a food processor.

title: easy sweet chocolate pie
directions: Melt candy in double boiler (not in microwave). Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into shell and refrigerate.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make into rolls.
Cover each with Saran Wrap.
Put into freezer.
When ready to use, slice and bake in a 375° oven.

title: corn casserole
directions: Place margarine in dish with onions and peppers.
Cook until onions are white.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Top with grated cheese or thin slices of cheese.
Bake at 350° until it is hot through and bubbles.

title: pepper steak
directions: Add beef to melted butter in a skillet; sprinkle with garlic powder and cook, stirring lightly until brown.
Remove meat; add onion and pepper.
Saute for 2 minutes; return meat to skillet along with tomatoes and bouillon cube.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add cornstarch, water, soy sauce, sugar and salt.
Stir into meat mixture; cook until thickened.
Serve at once over whipped potatoes or rice.

title: cajun shrimp
directions: Add olive oil or olive oil spray to large saucepan.
Over medium heat, saut onion, garlic, bell pepper and celery until onion is translucent.
Add parsley, bay leaf, cayenne pepper and stir.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Add water as needed.
Cook for at least 30 minutes.
Stir in shrimp and cook until pink (less than 5 minutes).
Add 1 teaspoon sugar or Splenda to bring out flavors.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve over 1 cup cooked rice.
Serves 2.

title: broccoli slaw
directions: Mix together all ingredients and chill.
I use breakfast bacon, fried until crisp.
Cook and crumble.

title: strudel
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and chill 4 hours or overnight. Divide dough into 4 equal pieces. Roll out each piece to 14 x 7-inches. Spread 1/2 cup preserves over each roll topped with 1/2 cup walnuts. Roll up dough as if for jellyroll. Place on cookie sheet. Brush top with beaten egg and score diagonally on top with knife. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate almond mousse
directions: Place chocolate and water in saucepan, stir over low heat until well blended.
Cool and combine cooled chocolate, milk, cream and vanilla in large bowl of electric mixer.
Chill; then whip until soft peaks form.
Put in dishes.
Freeze until firm. Top with almonds.

title: brownie trifle
directions: Prepare brownie mix and bake according to package directions in 13 x 9-inch pan.
While warm, prick top with a fork and brush with Kahlua, if desired.
Let cool completely and crumble.
Prepare mouse mix according to directions, omit chilling.

title: chicken parisienne
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts lightly with salt, pepper and paprika.
Place chicken breasts in crock-pot.
Mix white wine, soup and mushrooms until well combined, mixing in sour cream NOW if you will be cooking on low.
Pour over chicken breasts in crock-pot.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and cook on Low 6 to 8 hours.
(High: 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 hours with sour cream added during last 30 minutes).
Serve sauce over chicken with rice or noodles. This recipe may be doubled for 5-quart crock-pot.

title: mexican rice salad
directions: Combine eggs, rice, green onions, celery, cheese and chiles in large mixing bowl.
Blend sour cream, lemon juice, picante sauce and seasonings.
Pour over the egg mixture; mix well.
Chill.

title: mustard-herb marinade for chicken or fish
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given with wire whisk until very well blended.
Cover 2 to 3 pounds fish or chicken with marinade and marinate a minimum of two hours.
Better if marinated overnight, even up to 24 hours.
Cook over charcoal or on a gas grill and brush with remaining marinade while grilling until done. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: hamburger barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together in a skillet.
Drain excess grease and add the remaining ingredients.
Let simmer (covered) on low for 15 minutes.
Ready to serve.

title: easy supper casserole
directions: Cook onion until golden in skillet.
Crumble and brown ground beef.
Combine macaroni, celery, tomato sauce, cheese, salt, pepper, onion and hamburger in casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes or until heated through.

title: tuna mountain
directions: Cream together margarine and cream cheese with mixer.
Beat in tuna, onion, lemon juice, salt, pepper and tarragon until smooth. Chill.
Shape into a mountain on a plate.
Cover with parsley and sprinkle top with egg.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Bake pie shell for 10 minutes.
Toss cheese with flour.
Add onion and parsley; sprinkle on the base of pie shell.
Beat eggs with half and half; pour over cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Arrange sausage links and crumbled bacon on top.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pistachio cream puffs
directions: Add margarine
and
salt
to
cup boiling water in a saucepan.
Reduce
heat.
Stir
in flour and continue stirring until it
balls
around
the spoon.
Remove from heat. Add the eggs, one
at
a
time, beating each one in well.
Beat in the last egg
until
mixture
breaks
away from the spoon. Drop by teaspoonfuls
onto	greased
baking sheet. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Bake
for
minutes. Cool and fill with pistachio
pudding	prepared
according
to box directions and folded
into whipped topping.
(Plain whipped cream or topping or a vanilla pudding mixed with drained, crushed pineapple may be used as a filling instead.)

title: teriyaki pork steaks
directions: Combine all ingredients except meat in a nonmetallic container.
Stir well and add pork.
Marinate for 2 hours at room temperature or overnight in the refrigerator.
Remember, the longer the pork marinates the better the flavor.
Barbecue or broil for 8 to 10 minutes on each side or until pork is still slightly pink inside and the juices just run clear.
If in a hurry, while plain pork steaks are broiling, add 1 tablespoon of cornstarch to marinade and heat.
Pour over cooked pork.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt oleo; add flour and mix all other ingredients and put in baking dish and cook slowly until thick.

title: snowball salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate over night or at least 6 hours. (Can use mixed fruit jell-o and fruit cocktail. This makes a pink mixture.)

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash and dry tomatoes.
Cut in 1/4-inch slices and coat in mixture of flour, meal, salt and pepper.
Heat shortening in skillet to moderately hot temperature.
Fry, turning slices until golden brown.

title: hamburger and tuna casserole
directions: Brown onions in butter.
Add celery soup, milk, tuna (or hamburger), peas and macaroni.
Stir together and put in casserole dish.
Add pieces of Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 325° about 25 or 30 minutes.

title: orange glazed cornish game hens
directions: (For more hens, double ingredients.)

title: mississippi mud
directions: Melt sugar and butter together until creamy.
Beat in eggs and flour.
Blend in cocoa, vanilla and walnuts and combine thoroughly.
Spread batter into greased 9 x 13 baking pan and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brownies are done.
Remove from oven and while brownies are hot, cover with marshmallows. Cover pan with foil and let stand 5 to 10 minutes or until marshmallows are partially melted.
Spread marshmallows evenly over brownies and let cool.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix German chocolate cake mix as on box.
Divide batter in half.
To half batter add 1/2 cup of melted oleo and 1/2 cup of Eagle Brand milk. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
While baking melt 14 ounces of Kraft caramels, 1/2 cup oleo, other half of Eagle Brand milk and 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Pour mixture over baked cake, then on the caramel mixture pour remaining cake batter.
Bake additional 20 to 25 minutes.
Use your own icing.
Very rich.

title: baked brie hors d'oeuvres
directions: Note:
I find Edward's Supermarket is the only store that carries this size Brie.
You may use a smaller one.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples in a buttered dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, salt and water.
Mix flour, sugar and butter.
Pour over the apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve hot with cream.

title: carry along casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in butter in skillet with onions and green peppers.
Saute until meat is done.
Stir in flour.
Add tomato sauce, marjoram, salt, pepper and water.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, parsley, egg and onion salt.
Mix well.
Toss with noodles.
Alternate layers of meat and macaroni in a 3-quart casserole dish, ending with meat mixture.
Bake in oven at 375° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fast fruit dip
directions: Beat ingredients at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Serve with fruit.
Makes approximately 1 1/2 cups or 12 servings.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Pare eggplant.
Cut in 1-inch cubes and boil in pan with onion and salt until tender, but not mushy, about 5 minutes.
Drain.

title: fancy salad or dessert
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Serve on beds of lettuce on salad plates or in small dessert dishes.

title: homemade chocolate pudding
directions: Mix all dry ingredients well. Add milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add vanilla and butter. Serve warm with ice cream or serve cold.

title: hamburger and potatoes
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Add soup or tomatoes and mix well.
Pour into small baking dish.
Arrange potatoes around sides of hamburger.
Bake in 425° oven until potatoes are brown.

title: fish chowder
directions: Cut an elephant (medium size) into small bite-size pieces. This usually takes about 2 months.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over gas fire in open pot about 4 weeks, maintaining 465°.
This will serve about 3,800 people.
If more people are expected, 2 rabbits may be added, but do this only if necessary. Most people do not like to find hare in their stew.

title: linda's famous corn cob jelly
directions: Cover corn cobs with 4 cups water.
Bring to boil and cook for 10 minutes.
Strain.
Pour 3 cups juice in saucepan and add enough water to make 3 cups liquid, if necessary.
Add 2 or 3 drops red food coloring.
Add dry Kool-Aid.
Add Sure-Jell.
Bring to boil.
Add sugar; cook over high heat for 1 minute.
Pour into 5 medium jelly jars.
Cover with 1/8-inch melted paraffin.

title: glazed turkey legs
directions: Place turkey legs in 10-inch round microproof dish.
Cover with paper towel.
Use Cook cycle and cook 15 minutes, turning once. Turn legs over.
Use Cook cycle and cook 15 minutes.

title: texas ranch beans
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onion together; drain.
In a large ovenproof bowl, add beans, soup and sugar.
Add meat mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry squares
directions: In large bowl, cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and flour.
Add extracts.
Mix well.
Spread batter into a greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Cut surface of batter with knife to make 28 squares.
Spoon cherry or apple filling in center of each square.
Batter puffs up over filling during baking.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.
Cut in squares.

title: walnut-broccoli bake
directions: Grease 2-quart oblong baking dish. Cut broccoli in 1-inch pieces and spread in dish.
Melt butter in pan. Stir in flour and bouillon. Cook 1 to 2 minutes. Add milk. Bring to boil until thickened and pour over broccoli.

title: haupia (coconut pudding)
directions: In a saucepan, combine coconut milk and sugar.
Gradually mix in cornstarch.
Add vanilla and salt.
Stir and cook on medium heat until thickened.
Pour into dish and chill for at least 1 hour.
Cut into 36 squares.

title: rice 'n' salmon casserole
directions: Flake salmon (remove bones or crush finely).
Combine with rice.
Melt margarine; remove from heat; blend in flour.
Stir in milk and seasonings and cook over low heat until sauce is thickened.
Combine sauce with salmon-rice mixture and place in 1 1/2-quart slightly greased casserole.
Top with cheese.
Cover. Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: chantille's chicken spaghetti
directions: Combine vegetables in broth and boil until slightly tender (about 5 minutes).
Add milk and chicken.
Combine cornstarch with a small quantity of water, then add to ingredients, cooking until sauce thickens.
Add to drained pasta and combine well.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
If you like a little more or less sauce, adjust recipe to your liking. We like ours with plenty of white sauce.

title: crunchy chicken casserole
directions: Combine
all ingredients except onion rings and cheese. Pour into
a
greased
1 1/2 quart casserole.
Sprinkle onion rings and cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baby wipes
directions: Cut paper towels in half to make 2 rolls with electric knife. Put 1 roll in a 20 to 22 cup canister.
Mix water, shampoo and oil together.
Pour over paper towels; pull out cardboard from center of roll.
Use from center.
Save extra half roll for next batch of wipes.

title: mom's homemade barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Ready to use.

title: streusel topped creamy pumpkin pie
directions: Stir milk and pumpkin in a large bowl until smooth. Add pudding mixes and spice. Beat with wire whisk until well blended. Gently stir in 1/2 of the whipped topping. Spoon into crust. Refrigerate 4 hours until set. Sprinkle with Streusel Topping just before serving.

title: key west grilled chicken
directions: Place the chicken in a shallow dish; set aside. In a small bowl, combine the remaining ingredients; mix well and pour over the chicken. Cover and marinate in refrigerator for 1 hour, turning occasionally.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix mayonnaise, eggs, onion, soup, cheese, salt and pepper together; add to broccoli.
Pour into square dish; top with crackers.
Drizzle margarine over crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: texas beef skillet dinner
directions: In a skillet, cook ground beef or turkey and onions until meat is browned and onions are tender.
Drain fat.
Stir in the undrained tomatoes, undrained beans, uncooked rice, green pepper, chili powder, garlic powder, water and salt.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top with cheese.
Cover and heat about 3 minutes. Sprinkle corn chips around the edge.
Makes 6 servings.

title: watergate salad
directions: Fold pudding into Cool Whip.
Add pineapple with juice, marshmallows and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: cream of cauliflower soup
directions: Cook cauliflower in salted water until tender.
In a large saucepan, fry onions in butter until yellow, then blend in flour. Add broth, milk, Worcestershire sauce and cauliflower with cooking water.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: lock-in sausage gravy
directions: Brown sausage, stirring until crumbly and gray!
Add flour and cook on a medium-low heat, stirring until flour starts to brown. Add milk and heat until thick.
Adjust flour and milk as needed. Serve over biscuits.
Serves 25 to 30 kids!

title: beef brown rice
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish with butter or Pam.
Sprinkle rice in bottom of dish, slowly add consomme and water.
Sprinkle onion over ingredients.
Add ground beef.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove from oven and sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Serve while hot.

title: cabbage crunch
directions: Toast sesame seed and almonds until crunchy.
Combine sesame seed, almonds, cabbage, green onions and noodles from soup mix. Break up noodles into small pieces.

title: walnut crescent cookies(makes 9 to 12 dozen)
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add vanilla and flour; mix well. Add nuts.
Chill several hours or over night.
Shape into small half moons or round balls and flatten just a little and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hot shrimp dip
directions: Chop tomato, onion, peppers and garlic fine.
Add all together.
Serve warm or cold with chips or vegetables.

title: russian ground chicken cutlets
directions: Grind the chicken through a meat grinder or chop very fine. Combine with softened bread (squeezed dry), butter, salt and pepper and beat until smooth.
Shape into oval patties and roll in bread crumbs.
Fry 5 minutes on each side.

title: candied popcorn
directions: Cook the milk and sugar until syrup spins a 4 to 6-inch thread.
Remove from heat.
Add cake coloring and pour over popped corn.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Fry in oil 4 minutes on each side.

title: cranberry frost salad
directions: Combine berries and sugar.
Let sit 10 minutes.
Peel and section 1 orange; finely chop sections and set aside.
Squeeze remaining orange to make 1/3 cup juice.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Stir flour, juice from the lemons and baking soda with a spoon.
Add the sugar and grated lemon rind into the mixture. Roll thin and bake quickly at 350° for 5 minutes or until done.

title: german slaw
directions: Sprinkle sugar over chopped cabbage, peppers, celery and onion; set aside.
Bring to a boil the vinegar, oil, salt, dry mustard and celery seed.
Pour over sugared vegetables; toss well. Refrigerate, covered.
Keeps for up to 2 weeks.

title: honey mustard salmon
directions: In a small mixing bowl, whisk the first 5 ingredients together.
Brush both sides of the salmon.
Cover and refrigerate several hours.
Grill fish, turning once.
When fish flakes easily when tested with a fork, it is done.
Cooking time about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off any grease.
Add next 4 ingredients and heat slowly.
Do not boil.
Serve over cooked noodles.
Always good.
Very quick.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325`.
Grease two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.

title: kimona dip
directions: Cook egg yolks with vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper until thick.
Chop pepper and onion very small and add to egg yolk mixture.
Add this mixture to the cream cheese and blend in blender until smooth.
Make this one day ahead and let age in refrigerator.
Serve with chips for a party dip.

title: oyster cream puffs
directions: Heat pastry shells.
Over low heat cook oysters in oyster liquor until edges curl.
Drain and chop.
Over low heat, melt butter and stir in slowly for smooth consistency:
flour, green onions, half and half, and soup. Add oysters and seasonings and cook for 4 minutes.
Spoon into baked pastry shells.
Serve as hot appetizer.

title: ricotta pie
directions: Cream sugar and cheese well. Add salt, cornstarch; cream again. Add lemon juice, vanilla and eggs. Mix milk in last. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle nutmeg lightly on top. Lower temperature to 350° the last 15 minutes. Cool completely.

title: southwestern pizza
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Grease cookie sheet or 12-inch pizza pan. Mix baking mix and water; beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Turn onto floured surface. Knead about 60 times or until no longer sticky. Press into 13 inch circle sheet; pinch edge to form rim or press in pizza pan. Mix chicken and salsa.
Sprinkle crust with 1 cup cheese. Top with onion, chicken mixture and pepper; sprinkle remaining cheese. Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until crust is brown and cheese is bubbly.
Makes 1 pizza.

title: mimi's marshmallow mold
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Pack into angel food cake pan.
Put in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: overnite breakfast
directions: Grease large Bundt baking pan.
Add frozen dinner rolls. Cover and let rise overnight.
Mix sugar, cinnamon, brown sugar and butterscotch pudding mix.
Pour over rolls.
Top with oleo and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover with foil for first 15 minutes.
Remove foil for last 15 minutes to brown.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry jello
directions: Drain strawberries; reserve 1/2 cup juice.
Combine gelatin, sugar and salt in a bowl.
Add hot water.
Stir until dissolved completely.
Add cold water and reserve juice.
Chill until partially set.
Add whipped cream, strawberries and marshmallows.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in greased casserole and bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients lightly, then beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well until blended.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans or 1 Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until tests done with toothpick.

title: quick and easy peanut butter candy
directions: Melt butter, then add peanut butter, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Put in pan and refrigerate until cool.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box and cool. Prepare pudding as directed.
Break cake into pieces and layer half of it in the bottom of a punch bowl.
Layer half of the pineapple, pudding, pie filling and Cool Whip in the order listed, then starting with the cake, make a second layer.
Garnish with nuts and cherries. Refrigerate, preferably overnight.

title: barbecue sauce(diet)
directions: Mix all the ingredients together in a large pot; simmer for 1/2 hour.
Makes a generous amount.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: Brown chicken.
Arrange in baking dish.
Mix soup and milk. Pour over chicken.
Stir in onions.
Stir in chopped broccoli if desired.
Bake at 375° for approximately 1 hour, until done. Garnish with rest of onions.
Serve with rice.

title: lemon icebox cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Bake 2 round layers.
Cool and split into 4 layers.

title: southern peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all together.
Brush insides of unbaked pie shell with a small amount of beaten egg.
Prick bottom and sides with a fork. Pour in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: easy shrimp creole
directions: Saute vegetables in a little butter.
Add all other ingredients and cook over low heat for 3 minutes or until hot. Serve over a bed of rice or pasta.
Serves 4.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except blueberries.
When mixture is smooth, fold in blueberries.
Flour Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 325° for an hour to 1 hour and a half.

title: divinity
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, salt and water.
Cook stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking without stirring until a small amount dropped into cold water forms a firm ball.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Pour about half the syrup over egg whites. Cook remains of syrup until syrup forms a hard ball, but not brittle.
Add slowly to first mixture.
Beat until mixture holds its shape.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop by spoon onto wax paper.

title: equal pumpkin pie
directions: Beat pumpkin, evaporated milk and eggs in medium bowl; beat in remaining ingredients. Pour mixture into pie crust. Bake in preheated oven for 15 minutes; reduce oven temperature to 350°. Bake until knife inserted near center comes out clean, about 40 minutes. Cool on a wire rack.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Mix rice, tomato sauce, ground beef and seasonings.
Form mixture into 5 or 6 balls.
Wrap balls in the cabbage leaves using toothpicks to hold in place.
Put in large pot.
Cover with rest of tomato sauce and tomatoes and add 1 can of water.
Cook over medium heat for 1 hour.
Remove toothpicks before serving.

title: zucchini loaf
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Gradually add the sugar, beating well.
Add oil.
Sift all dry ingredients together and add slowly. Add vanilla and then the zucchini.
Fold in nuts and raisins. Grease and flour two loaf pans.

title: custard rice pie
directions: Butter 2
9x13 pans or pyrex dish.
Cook rice, rinse with hot water and drain.
In deep pan, add oleo and sugar.
Add hot rice, mix well until dissolved.
Add salt, vanilla and lemon extracts. Combine orange rind, juice and beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Then add milk.
Mix with rice, Pour into buttered pans.
Fill and bake at 350° for 45-50 mins.

title: balsamic salad dressing
directions: Mix in glass container all the ingredients, except the garlic. Peel garlic and carefully score the cloves on all sides with a sharp knife.
Drop scored garlic into glass container with other ingredients.
Shake well for best flavor; let sit overnight.
Do not store in refrigerator.
I leave garlic cloves in container for a stronger garlic flavor.
Delicious on salad, pasta, etc.

title: pull apart breakfast rolls
directions: Place frozen rolls in angel food cake pan.
Mix brown sugar, pecans, pudding and cinnamon and pour over frozen rolls.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Let rise overnight.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°; let sit a few minutes in pan, then turn out on platter.

title: shrimp in beer
directions: Wash shrimp in cold water and drain.
Place in crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Cover and cook on high for 1 hour.
If desired, turn to low until serving time, up to 2 hours.

title: cordon bleu sauce
directions: Mix and heat until hot and pour over serving of chicken.

title: sheet cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Bring next 4 ingredients to a boil and pour over dry ingredients.
Mix last 3 ingredients well with mixture.
Pour into greased 16 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese with 1 Tbsp milk.
Chop onions; include greens.
Chop beef fine.
Add to cheese along with garlic juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Form into ball and chill. Serve with crackers.

title: barb's crab cakes
directions: Stir until batter is well moistened. Form into cakes.
Fry until brown.

title: snickerdoodles(cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 400° and lightly grease baking sheets.
Cream sugar, butter or margarine and shortening.
Beat in eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour just until blended. Combine 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon in small bowl or plastic bag may be used.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and roll or shake in the sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Place on baking sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake 6 to 7 minutes or until set around edges.
The center of cookie will be soft.
Cool on wire rack. Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: escalloped eggplant
directions: Boil eggplant, onion and salt until tender. Drain and add 1 cup crumbs, milk, margarine and egg. Mix lightly, but thoroughly. Add finely diced cheese.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish and top with the remaining 1/2 cup crumbs which have been buttered. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until lightly browned and heated through.

title: quesadilla stack
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add taco seasoning.

title: dilled broccoli
directions: Cut broccoli into small flowerets.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over broccoli.
Marinate in refrigerator for 6 to 8 hours.
Drain and serve.

title: low-fat low-cholesterol chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour one (13 x 9-inch) baking pan or one Bundt form.
In a large mixing bowl, beat margarine and 1 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Add 1/3 cup cold water, cocoa and vanilla, mixing well.
Add flour alternately with 1 cup water, beating after each addition.
In a mixing bowl, beat egg whites lightly; gradually add 3/4 cup sugar.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold beaten egg whites into batter.
Dissolve soda in remaining 1/3 cup water; stir into batter.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool on racks before removing from pans.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain.
Add cheese and cracker crumbs and mix well.
Stir in rest of the ingredients.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian kabobs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes; let cool. Pour mixture into a shallow dish; add chicken, tossing gently

to coat. Cover and marinate at least 1 hour in the refrigerator, stirring mixture occasionally. Remove chicken from marinade, reserving marinade. Alternate chicken, pineapple, green pepper, mushrooms and tomatoes on skewers. Brush with marinade and grill over hot coals 20 minutes or until done. Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: grandma peck's peanut butter ponechi
directions: Mix together brown sugar, 1/3 stick butter, salt and milk. Boil until a drop makes a firm ball when dropped into a cup of cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add another 1/3 stick of butter and vanilla. Chop in peanut butter.
Beat with spoon until smooth. Pour into buttered dish.

title: crab quiche
directions: Mix together and put in pie crust.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: swiss potato soup with chicken
directions: Put the chicken in pot and fill with water. Cook until tender. Take out chicken; let cool, then pick it off the bone. Set aside. Save the chicken stock. Add to pot of chicken stock that you cooked the chicken in.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Blend Miracle Whip, lemon juice, onion, salt, pepper and sage.
Mix lightly with chicken, celery, almonds and 1/2 cup of the cheese.
Put into greased baking dish and sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese and potato chips on top.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes until heated through.

title: potato rolls
directions: Mix as given.
Let rise, then roll out as you desire.
Let rise again before baking.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Heat milk in saucepan until bubbles form around edge of pan; remove from heat.
Add sugar, salt and margarine.
Stir until margarine is melted.
Let cool to lukewarm.
In large bowl, sprinkle yeast over water; stir until dissolved.
Add remaining flour and beat until smooth.
Dough will be soft.
Cover; let rise about 1 hour.
Punch down and turn onto well floured board.
Turn over to coat with flour.
Knead 10 times to smooth dough.
Cover dough with bowl and rest 10 minutes.
Roll out 1/2-inch and cut; let rise about 45 minutes.
Fry in deep fat at 375°.
Dip into glaze and set aside.

title: quick start breakfast drink
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and whip until smooth.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water for 5 minutes. Add shortening, sugar, eggs, 4 cups flour and salt.
Stir and then beat until smooth (about 1 minute). Stir in remaining flour.
This will be a soft dough.
Cover tightly and store in refrigerator overnight.

title: golden parmesan chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix cheese, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken into butter, then coat with cheese mixture.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush cookies; reserve 1/3 cup.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour
1 stick melted margarine over crumbs and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar and blend in
1 carton Cool Whip; spread evenly over cookies and refrigerate
for
1 hour.
Prepare pudding according to directions. Spread
second carton
of
Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with cookie crumbs (reserved).
Keep refrigerated.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour water over the 100% Bran set aside, cream sugar and oil add eggs, sift flour, baking soda and salt together.
Add alternated with buttermilk to cream mix.
Add bran buds, raisins, and orange peel.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Mix well before using.
Bake at 375 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip glaze and cream cheese together, then add Cool Whip. Any fresh fruit, such as strawberries, bananas, peaches, pineapple or apples may be used for dipping.

title: chicken tortilla soup
directions: Boil chicken in water. Cut into bite size and return to broth. Add remainder of ingredients except tortillas. Boil 10 minutes, then add tortillas. Boil until tortillas are soft.

title: old fashioned lasagna
directions: Cut olives in large pieces.
Set aside.
Brown ground beef in olive oil.
Add onion and garlic to ground beef and cook until transparent.
Add next six ingredients.
Cover and simmer one hour or until sauce is thickened, stirring occasionally.
Stir in olives.
Meanwhile, cook lasagna in boiling salted water for 20 minutes.
Drain.
Grate Mozzarella cheese.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Parboil green peppers.
Brown hamburger, then add onion and tops from green peppers, chopped into small pieces.
Cook tomato juice, corn and hamburger mixture for approximately 20 to 30 minutes.
Stuff green peppers.
Can be frozen and warmed in microwave for fast meal.

title: hunter's stew
directions: Boil venison until tender. Brown hamburger meat and drain off grease. Then mix all other ingredients together. Cook until all vegetables are tender.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Combine with rest of ingredients and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: fudge brownie cake
directions: Sift together the flour and sugar.
Set aside.
Put in saucepan and bring just to a boil margarine, shortening, salt, cocoa, vanilla, water and cinnamon.
Add sauce to dry ingredients (flour and sugar).
Add slightly beaten eggs, buttermilk and soda.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in large 2-inch deep 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: onion rings
directions: Separate onions into rings.
Mix dry ingredients with egg, milk and oil.
Coat onion rings with batter until well moistened and drop into hot grease.
Fry until golden brown.

title: prize rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Add sugar and salt; mix well.
Combine flour and shortening in bowl; mix well. Add flour mixture to yeast mixture gradually to form soft dough. Place in greased bowl, turning to coat surface.
Let rise, covered, until doubled in bulk.
Punch dough down.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Shape into rolls.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Let rise, covered, until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield:
40 servings.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix Hi-C or Hawaiian Punch with 7-Up in punch bowl.
Float ice cream in punch.
Make about 1/2 hour before needed.
(Assorted flavors of Hi-C can be used with 7-Up for different punch for each occasion.)

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix water, cornstarch, syrup and salt.
Bring to boil; cook 4 minutes, stirring often.
Add Jell-O mix.
Place dry berries in pie shell.
Pour mix evenly over berries.
Chill and serve with Cool Whip.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Cook meat and drain the grease.
Put in casserole dish.
Pour mushroom soup over meat.
Cover with grated cheddar cheese.
Top with tater tots.
Put in oven and bake at 375° until tater tots are golden brown.

title: seafood roll-ups
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Soften cream cheese, thin with wine. Unroll crescents.
Spread cream cheese on crescents.
Place crab leg at one end or spread shrimp over cream cheese.
Sprinkle lightly with dill weed.
Roll up.
Brush on beaten egg.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
May be used whole as an entree or can be sliced as hors d'oeuvres.

title: artichoke dip
directions: With a fork remove artichoke hearts to a cutting board, reserving marinade in jar; chop fine.
Into small mixing bowl, turn the mayonnaise; with a fork, whisk in the marinade from the artichoke hearts.
Stir in the cheese and the chopped artichoke hearts.
Cover tightly and chill until serving time.
Makes about one cup.
Serve with a platter of fresh raw vegetables, sliced.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mash peeled avocados well or use blender.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving. Serves 4.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Lightly grease an 8-inch square baking pan.
In a mixing bowl, mix flour, sugar, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt. Stir in milk, oil and vanilla until just blended.
Fold in nuts. Pour mixture into prepared pan and spread level.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Bring to a rolling boil for 8 minutes the sugar and evaporated milk.
Add Marshmallow Creme, butter or margarine and chocolate chips.
Turn off heat.
Stir until lukewarm and melted.
Add chopped pecans.
Makes about 5 pounds of candy.

title: flounder flips
directions: If scallops are large, cut into quarters.
Melt butter.
With rolling pin, crush crackers.
Put in bowl, add scallops, part of butter and 3 to 4 drops of Worcestershire sauce; mix together. Divide mixture into fourths and put into the middle of each fish piece.
Roll up.
Connect with a toothpick.
Squeeze lemon into remaining butter.
Pour over and bake at 350° until done, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: crumb cake(great!  no baking!)
directions: Spread this over the first mixture and sprinkle more vanilla wafer crumbs over top.
Let sit in refrigerator 24 hours.
A total of 25 to 30 vanilla wafers will be necessary.
Cut and serve.

title: barbecue rice
directions: Tear a 3 foot length 18-inch foil.
Fold in half to make a square.
Make a pouch of foil.
Add all ingredients, except butter. Add mushroom liquid, too.
Seal and place on grill over hot coals for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients together in a large bowl; pour into a casserole dish. Mix corn flake crumbs with melted butter and spread on top of the potato mixture. Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes. You may used reduced fat soup, sour cream and cheese.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix this together and put over cooled mixture.
Top with one or two cans of blueberry pie filling.

title: turtle bars
directions: Blend cake mix, margarine and 1/3 cup milk in large mixer bowl. Beat until mixed.
Place half of cake mixture in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan and press into bottom.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool to room temperature.
Place caramels and 1/3 cup milk in saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until smooth.
Pour over cake; sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Press remaining dough into little pieces and cover nuts. Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Let cool before cutting.

title: caramel cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on box.
Cool.

title: seafood gonzales(one serving)
directions: In a 6-inch cast-iron skillet put the mushrooms, shrimp, crabmeat and green onion tops in the order listed.
Pour sauce ingredients in skillet over medium heat.
When shrimp are pink and firm, remove from fire and garnish with a liberal amount of grated Parmesan cheese.

title: bean relish
directions: Cut beans as for table use.
Boil not to done.
Cook the following until thick and pour over beans which have been drained: sugar, mustard, flour, turmeric, celery seed, vinegar and sweet pepper.
Put in hot canning jars and seal.
Can use cold pack method.

title: apple dessert
directions: Peel and dice apples fine.
Pour sugar over and let stand for 1 hour.
Mix together other ingredients; add apples.
Place in 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lemon herb grilled chicken with vegetable kabobs
directions: Place chicken and vegetables in heavy plastic bag.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken and veggies.
Marinate in refrigerator several hours or overnight.

title: antipasta
directions: Drain juice of olives and mushrooms and discard.
Combine remaining ingredients. Marinate with juice from antipasta red peppers.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: "hot" wings sauce
directions: Combine hot sauce and butter until butter is melted.
Add other ingredients.
Bring all to simmer.
Dip fried chicken wings.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix the ingredients all together.
Form into 1-inch balls. Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, cocoa, sugar and salt.
Add milk and melted butter.
Pour into 9-inch cake pan, sprinkle with brown sugar and cocoa.
Pour hot water over all.
Bake in moderate oven 45 minutes, or in microwave oven for about 15 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or milk.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients in order in oblong pan.
Mix cake. Mix as directed on package and pour over rhubarb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.
Turn upside down on platter or cookie sheet.

title: spaghetti alla bacon
directions: In a large skillet, brown garlic in butter.
Stir in cooked spaghetti, Parmesan cheese, cream and pepper; simmer over low heat until thick.
Place in heated serving dish, crumble bacon over top and serve immediately.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pan spaghetti
directions: Cook hamburger in skillet until medium brown.
Bring spaghetti to a boil for 5 minutes.
Combine spaghetti, hamburger and sauce in a 9 x 12-inch or 8 x 11-inch flat pan along with Mozzarella cheese. Flatten with frosting spreader.
Put Cheddar cheese evenly on top and Parmesan throughout.
Bake in oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.
Can serve 6 to 8 adults.

title: apricot fruit salad
directions: Drain all canned fruits and cherries of all juice.
Add apricot pie filling and sliced bananas.
Stir well.
Chill.
(Bananas will not turn brown.)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine
soup,	onions and seasoning in saucepan;
mix. Add water
and	blend.	Bring
to boil over medium heat; stir constantly.
Pour
mixture
in
3 quart saucepan.
Make 2 layers of each; add rice and chicken.
Top with remaining soup mixture.
Cover
and
bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir well after 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serves 8.

title: holiday wassail tea
directions: Boil the last 2 ingredients for 10 minutes, then discard cloves.
Add other ingredients. Simmer until ready to serve. Add sugar to taste. Can serve with a cinnamon stick in each punch cup.

title: champagne dessert
directions: Bake Jiffy cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan according to package directions.
Beat vanilla, pudding, milk and cream cheese together.
Spread over cake.
Spread drained pineapple on top. Spread Cool Whip on top of the pineapple.
Decorate with maraschino cherries after pieces are on serving plate.

title: orange-apricot salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; add pineapple juice; cool.
Add apricots (which have been cut), pineapple and marshmallows.
Mix and let set until thick.
In top of double boiler, add egg, sugar, salt, flour and apricot juice.
When thick, add butter.
Cool.
Add whipped cream and fold in.
Put on top of Jell-O layer.
Chill.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix first four ingredients and spread in a long baking dish, forming a crust.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown.
Cool.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Break eggs over apples.
Add sugar, cinnamon, oil and nuts. Mix with fork.
Sift flour, salt and soda; mix together with fork. Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cook for 55 minutes at 350°.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Drain canned carrots.
Arrange carrots, peppers and onion in layers.
Combine all remaining ingredients in a saucepan; bring to boil, stirring until blended.
Pour marinade over carrot mixture. Refrigerate until flavor is absorbed.
This will keep in the refrigerator for a long time.

title: rigatoni
directions: Chop pepperoni into small pieces.
Brown and drain hamburger. Combine pepperoni, hamburger, tomato sauce and chili salsa.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended and chill.
Use as vegetable dip.
Good alternative to Spinach or Dill Dip.

title: julia child's gratin and ham eggs quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Use a 12-inch baking dish or individual souffle dishes.
Take 3/4 cup chopped onions and cook slowly in 5 tablespoons butter; don't brown.
Add 1 1/2 cups diced cooked ham. Cook 5 minutes more.
Blend the ham and onions into the heated mixture (include the butter they were in).
Take 4 to 5 potatoes (peel and grate, using large holes of grater).
Squeeze out the water, then stir potatoes into egg mixture.
May be prepared ahead to this point.
Heat 2 tablespoons butter in pans.
Pour in egg-potato mix.
Set in upper 1/3 oven.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes until brown.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs; brown on all sides.
Drain excess fat.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over ribs.
Cook in oven 2 hours at 350°.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Drain pineapple.
Cream together sugar and oleo until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and salt; mix well.
Stir in pineapple and lemon juice.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: extra special fruit cake
directions: Do not chop nuts or dates, leave whole. Pour sugar over nuts and dates. Sift together and add cake flour, baking powder and salt. Add red and green cherries and juice.
Separate 5 eggs and add beaten egg yolks.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites last. Grease pans well. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 2 loaf size cakes.

title: diabetic's dessert
directions: Note:
I also use a small can of crushed pineapple in its own juice.

title: kate houston's cornbread
directions: In a bowl mix all dry ingredients. Add milk and egg. Melt the drippings or shortening in a skillet or baking pan. Add to the batter and pour in a hot skillet that is well-greased.
Bake at 450° about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spanish squash casserole
directions: Mix 1 stick oleo and dressing mix.
Mix all ingredients together, saving enough dressing mix to put on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Pour in whiskey slowly.
Add flour alternately.
Pour all this over fruit covered with flour.
Add nuts.
Fold in egg whites that are beaten until stiff.
Bake 1 hour at 200° and then 2 hours at 250°.

title: apple squares
directions: Beat 1 egg yolk with fork and add to mixture with 1/3 cup milk.
Place in refrigerator.

title: homemade chalk
directions: Mix water, plaster of Paris and paint in bowl.
Pour into small paper cups.
Air dry for 1 hour.
Peel away cup.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and beat well with mixer until smooth. Mix remaining ingredients together in a separate bowl. Gradually add to creamy mixture while mixing on low until well blended. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 350 degrees for 50
to 60 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until tender; cool and slice.
Slice onion and bell pepper and add to carrots.
Mix sugar, mustard, soup, oil, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce and pour over carrots, onion and bell pepper.
Soak 24 hours to marinate well.

title: crispix snack
directions: Melt margarine in 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan at 250°. Combine next 4 ingredients in small bowl. Stir to blend spices. Add cereal to melted margarine. Stir to coat thoroughly.
Then sprinkle spices on cereal. Stir to coat.
Bake 45 minutes. Stir every 15 minutes. Remove and cool. Put in large airtight container. Add Fritos and Cheez-Its.

title: diabetic fruit fluff
directions: Dissolve Jello in 2/3 cup boiling water. Add 2 cups ice cubes and stir until thickened. Using a wire whisk, add dessert whip. Fold in fruit. Put in pie shell or dessert dishes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pull chicken apart and place on bottom of pan.
Spread both cans of soup over chicken.
Cover top with stuffing mix.
Pour chicken broth over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: guatemalan fried rice
directions: Heat shortening.
Add rice and fry until nicely browned, stirring constantly.
Add onion and tomato.
Cook slightly.
Add water and other vegetables.
Cover and bring quickly to a boil. Lower heat and cook about 45 minutes or until done.
Do not stir. When serving, remove with a fork.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Add macaroni, tomatoes and onion. Do not add any water.
Cook for 10
minutes.
Pour in casserole dish and top with cheese. Add biscuits, arranged in a layer, and bake until brown.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, vanilla and butter.
Add soda, cream of tartar and flour.
Roll on floured surface with rolling pin.
Cut out with biscuit cutter or floured glass.
Bake on greased baking sheet at 400° until the cookies begin to brown.

title: chow-chow
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and soak with salt and water overnight. Drain and mix vinegar, sugar and spices. Boil 1 hour and put in hot sterilized jars.

title: isaiah 41
directions: Be not dismayed.

I will strengthen thee and you take righteousness to uphold thee and you take the water and oil, mixed the plants in the wilderness in a pool of water in the desert so it will grow that the hand of the Lord have done this.

title: john wayne cheese casserole
directions: Sauce:
Dice chilies and saute onions in butter.
Add tomatoes and cook until mushy.

title: almond fruited cheese ball
directions: *Measure and crush cereal in glass measuring cup.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: green chili dip
directions: Place drained tomatoes, onion, parsley, chiles, garlic, vinegar, oregano and salt into food processor with steel blade or into blender container.
Process mixture until smooth.
Transfer mixture to oiled heatproof serving dish, such as a deep bowl or crock.
Top with the cheese.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Before serving, bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until dip is hot and cheese is melted.
Offer with raw vegetable sticks for dipping.

title: chocolate oatmeal candy
directions: Melt margarine in a pan.
Add milk, sugar and cocoa.
Stir together and boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in peanut butter.
Add oats and vanilla.
Stir briskly until glossiness is gone.
Dip onto wax paper.
Refrigerate 15 minutes to harden.

title: green or red salad
directions: Drain pineapple and add juice to water to make 2 cups.
Add jello.
Heat until very hot.
Add marshmallows and dissolve.
Let congeal in refrigerator.
Beat mixture until it looks like whipped cream.
Fold whipped cream into jello with cheese, pineapple and nuts.
Chill this overnight.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of butter and saute onion until pale gold. Remove from heat.

title: crab imperial
directions: Add lemon juice to crabmeat, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco, salt and pepper.
Make a sauce over medium heat.
Blend flour, mustard and small amount of milk.
Add cream; cook until thick. Add melted butter; pour over crabmeat and pack mixture into shells.
Mash crackers; mix with 1/4 stick melted butter and sprinkle on top of crabmeat.
Bake in a hot oven (400° to 450°) until brown.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Mix shrimp, bread and cheese.
Add butter.
Add salt to eggs. Combine with shrimp.
Add milk.
Refrigerate mixture overnight. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon blueberry cream pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch. Add milk, yolks, butter and lemon peel. Cook and stir over medium
heat until thick. Remove from heat and add lemon juice. Put in bowl and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Add the sour cream and berries. Pour into a cooked pie shell. Top with whip cream and lemon slices.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Grease bowl or baking dish.
Put rice on bottom.
Cook broccoli.
Microwave other items until melted.
Pour over broccoli and rice.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake 30 minutes on 400° (uncovered last 10 minutes).

title: creamy apple squares
directions: Combine the cake mix and butter and mix until crumbly; reserve 2/3 cup for topping.
Add brown sugar and cinnamon to the reserved topping.
Mix well and set aside.
Press remaining cake and butter mixture into bottom of an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange apple slices over the base.
Blend sour cream and egg together and spread evenly over the apples.
Sprinkle the reserved topping mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly.
Serve warm and refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 12 to 15 squares.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and combine with milk, soup, pepper and 1/2 can onions.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: moist banana bread
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add egg and flour with the salt and baking soda.
Add ripe bananas.
Mix all with electric mixer.

title: chicken cordon bleu roll-ups
directions: In a glass baking dish, melt butter.
Set aside.
Between 2 pieces of plastic wrap, lightly pound chicken to flatten for even cooking; remove wrap.
Place 1 slice of ham, then cheese on each breast.
Start at narrow end and tightly roll up.
Roll in flour, then in melted butter, then in stuffing mix to coat.
Place in baking dish; cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes, rotating dish after 3 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes, then serve.
(Or bake, uncovered, in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.) Makes 4 servings.

title: pigs in the blanket
directions: Cut beef into 3 x 2-inch rectangles.
Place a slice of onion and 2 pieces of bacon on each rectangle of beef.
Roll up beef and secure with 1 to 2 toothpicks.
Roll beef rolls in flour and fry in large skillet until brown.

title: peanutty supreme squash
directions: Slice squash and cook in small amount of water until tender; drain and mash.
Add pimento, onion, carrot, soup and sour cream; blend together.
Toss stuffing mix, margarine and nuts together. Turn half of stuffing mixture into 9 x 11 x 2-inch casserole dish. Pour in squash mixture evenly.
Top with remaining crumb mixture. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Cook 1 cup butter, sugar 1/2 milk and egg, stirring constantly to a good boil. Remove from heat and add coconut, nuts and graham cracker crumbs. Line a 9 x 13 pan with graham crackers. Pour mixture over crackers and cover with another layer of crackers.

title: double peach gelatin
directions: In bowl, dissolve jello in boiling water; chill until thickened.
Fold in peaches, grapes and blueberries.
Pour in 4-cup mold and chill 2 hours or until firm.

title: eva's hash
directions: Mix together. Bring to boil, then cook slow for 6 to 8 hours.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: Mix eggs and milk.
Add rest of ingredients.
Put in buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: yuki's fried rice
directions: Trim all fat from meat.
Heat skillet to 350° and add oil (this is a medium hot frying pan).
Add chicken, quickly fry for 5 minutes.
Add sugar and carrots and fry medium-high 3 minutes. Add onions and celery; stir and cook 2 minutes.
Add green pepper and bouillon cubes (crush them in pan).
Add soy sauce.
Add cooked rice.
Serves 4.

title: corn meal pie
directions: Mix sugar, meal and butter.
Add eggs and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Makes 2 pies.

title: instant seekh kababs
directions: Mix all the ingredients together, except oil.
Marinate in refrigerator for 1 hour.
With oiled hands, shape the beef mixture into seekhs and slide onto wooden or steel skewers.

title: cavitania
directions: Brown sausage or hamburger with onion and green pepper.
Add tomato sauce and tomato puree to meat.
Add 1/2 can water (puree can).
Put in Italian seasoning and salt.
Stir.
Cook 30 minutes, uncovered.
Boil noodles; add noodles to sauce.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with cheese and pepperoni.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: mother's hot biscuits
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder together.
Mix in shortening as for pie dough.
Put in milk and mix lightly.
Put on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until done to the touch.
Very good for strawberry shortcake.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in
9 x 13-inch pan.
Add cracker crumbs, coconut, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and walnuts in layers. Drizzle milk over top.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: eloise's carrot and raisin salad
directions: Wash, peel and grate carrots.
Add remaining ingredients to carrots.
Moisten with salad dressing. Chill and serve as a side dish.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients in large container.
It makes a little over a gallon.
Simmer until very hot, but do not boil.
Sweeten tea to taste.
If you use ground spices, mix in as tea heats so it won't swim on top.
This will keep about a week in the fridge.

title: beefy jalapeno cornbread
directions: Combine 1 cup cornmeal, milk, eggs, salt, soda, bacon drippings and corn in bowl; mix and set aside.
Saute ground beef until lightly brown; drain and set aside.
Sprinkle remaining cornmeal in greased 10 1/2-inch iron skillet; pour half of cornmeal batter in skillet.
Sprinkle evenly with beef; top with onion, then cheese.
Add peppers evenly on top.
Pour remaining batter over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: oatmeal rolls
directions: In a large bowl, pour boiling water over oats and margarine. Stir and cool to lukewarm. Dissolve the yeast in a third cup of warm water, with one teaspoon sugar. Add sugars, salt and dissolved yeast to oatmeal mixture. Knead in the flour one cup at a time. Allow dough to rise in a warm place for 1 hour. Punch down. Form into rolls and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Allow to rise again for 20 to 30 minutes. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: zezzie's squash
directions: Wash and cut ends of squash (discard ends), then slice. Dice onion.
Using
a
skillet cook onion and squash in Crisco or Wesson oil	until
brown.
Add
water,
bouillon
cubes and sugar. Cover and	simmer	until flavor blends and very little water is left.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix oleo, peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Shape into balls and place in a refrigerator.
Melt chocolate and paraffin together.
Dip peanut butter balls into chocolate with toothpicks. Place on cookie sheet to cool and dry.

title: mystery pie
directions: Gradually add sugar and baking powder to beaten egg whites; mix with remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased pie pan and bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool 30 minutes or longer; cover with whipped cream.
Refrigerate 4 hours.

title: pork chops-n-mushroom soup
directions: Coat pork chops with flour and place in hot oil to brown. After chops have browned, place them in a baking dish.
Mix soup, celery, carrots, onions and drippings from browning pork chops with 1/2 cup water.
Pour over pork chops.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°, covered with foil.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes or until brown.

title: flavored butter
directions: Blend honey with butter or margarine.
Makes 1 cup.

title: easy chicken pot pie(serves 4 to 6; can be doubled according to family size.)
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
Juices from the boiled chicken may be used to replace the chicken broth.
Boil eggs.
Mix the cream of chicken, mixed veggies, eggs and chicken together.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add vanilla and water.
Add flour; mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Shape into small balls or "fingers." Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in slow oven (325°) for about 20 minutes.
Remove to rack.
Cool slightly.
Roll in confectioners sugar (sifted).
Makes 3 dozen.

title: granola
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix honey, oil, water and vanilla together.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix well. Spread thinly in baking pans.
Bake at 200° until dry, stirring occasionally.

title: spicy coffee
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine coffee, 2 inches stick cinnamon and orange peel.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove solids from coffee with a slotted spoon. Pour coffee into coffee cups.
If desired, garnish with cinnamon sticks.
Makes six 5-ounce servings.

title: infallible chili
directions: Brown meat on high.
Add onion and pepper; cook until tender. Add chili powder, flour, salt, sugar, pepper, crushed tomatoes, tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Reduce heat to simmer; cover and cook 1 hour.
Stir in chocolate and beans.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes or until you remember to turn it off.

title: sausage cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into balls or drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: kiss cookies
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar together.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour and baking soda together in a separate bowl.
Gradually add to mixture.
Roll into balls.
Roll balls into sugar.
Bake at 375° for about 8 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Press a kiss into middle of cookie.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix flour, salt, sugar and cornstarch thoroughly in top of double boiler.
Add 3/4 cup hot milk and stir until smooth.
Add remaining milk and cook for 15 minutes.

title: corn scallop
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
In a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch glass pan place mixture and spread, top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm in center and brown on top.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix beans, sugar, mustard, molasses, onion and ketchup thoroughly.
Place in an ovenproof baking dish.
Place bacon slices on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until bacon has browned.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Use plastic container. Sift powdered sugar and cocoa together. Pour milk over the sugar mix.
Place sliced margarine over the mixture. Do not stir.
Microwave on High power for 3 minutes. Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan. Refrigerate.

title: e-z brownies
directions: Grease an 11 x 17-inch pan with butter.
Mix all ingredients together and smooth in pan.
Cook at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel and wash potatoes.
Cut potatoes into slices, but not all the way through.
Use a handle of a spoon to keep knife from cutting all the way through.
Put potatoes in baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter; sprinkle with herbs.

title: easy jerky
directions: Combine all ingredients, except meat, in a large covered bowl and set aside.
Trim meat to remove fat and slice into strips 1/8-inch thick.
Mix meat with marinade.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove racks from oven and preheat to lowest possible setting, 150° to 175°.
Spray oven racks with cooking spray and lay meat strips directly on racks.
Foil in the bottom of oven may be helpful to catch drips.
Place racks with meat in oven and leave oven door cracked open to provide air flow over meat.
Allow meat to dry in oven for 4 to 6 hours.

title: crab salad
directions: Toss together and serve on lettuce.

title: chicken soup
directions: In an 8-quart pot add chicken parts.
Cut up onion, celery and carrot, add to pot and fill to 1 1/2-inch from top.
Bring to a boil, then simmer on low for 4 hours with lid.

title: "three bean casserole"
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until onions are done.

title: pretzel salad
directions: First layer:
Mix together pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and melted butter and save 3 tablespoons crust for garnish.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 8 minutes at 400°.

title: easy chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine chicken and taco sauce in a large saucepan.
Cook over low heat for 15 minutes, stirring often.
Dissolve bouillon in half and half in a large skillet over low heat (do not boil). Cook tortillas, one at a time, in an ungreased skillet, about 10 seconds on each side, or until softened.
Dip each tortilla in half and half mixture.

title: beef burgundy
directions: You can buy a rump roast or stew beef as this gets tender because it cooks so long.
You combine all ingredients and you never have to stir it again.
Cook at 250° for 5 hours, uncovered. Serve over rice or noodles.
This recipe can be doubled.
It never goes to waste.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and granulated sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to creamed mixture.
Place flour in a large bowl and add dates, chopped orange slices and nuts.
Stir to coat.
Add flour and fruit mixture and coconut to creamed mixture. This makes a very stiff dough that should be mixed with the hands. Put in greased 13 x 9 x 3 inch cake pan.
Bake at 250° for 2-1/2 to 3 hours.
Combine orange juice and powdered sugar. Pour over hot cake.
Let stand in pan over night.

title: pineapple muffins
directions: Combine flour and baking soda.
Set aside. Cream together cream cheese and sugar in a large mixing bowl. Add vanilla and egg.
Mix. Add dry mixture alternately with sour cream.
Stir in pineapple.
Pour into lightly greased muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 24 muffins.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Cream together eggs, oil, applesauce, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Combine dry ingredients together and add to muffin batter.
Mix until just combined.
Can keep batter in refrigerator for 2 to 3 weeks.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add enchilada sauce; simmer for 20 minutes.
In a separate pan, heat peppers and soup.
Grease baking dish and line with tortillas (quartered).
Add in layers the meat, soup and water (mixed) and cheese.
Start over with tortillas; end with cheese.
Cover; allow to set 30 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and sugar into mixing bowl.
Put cocoa, water and oil in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over dry ingredients while hot.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to mixture along with eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Grease and flour a large sheet pan, 18 X 12 X 1. Pour into pan and bake 18 minutes at 400.

title: hot curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit in colander.
Melt butter and add brown sugar and curry.
Pour fruit into sugar mixture and stir to coat fruit. Place in glass baking dish and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: lemon fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add egg yolks one at a time. Beat well each time.
Alternate lemon extract, 2 cups flour and baking powder. Dredge cut up fruit and nuts with the remaining 2 cups of flour.
Add to mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Let stand overnight.
Bake in tube pan lined with greased and floured wax paper.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 250°.

title: sausage pie casserole(great)
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Crumble and drain.
Mix cheese and sausage; put in pie shell.

title: cocktail tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes and while wet, sprinkle with Jane's Krazy Mixed-Up salt.
Delicious when dry.

title: refrigerator rolls(melt in your mouth)
directions: Pour
boiling
water
over
shortening, sugar and salt. Blend and let cool.
Add eggs.
Let yeast stand in cold water 5 minutes,
then
add
to mixture.
Mix in flour.
Put into a greased bowl.
Cover and place in refrigerator 4 hours.
About 3 hours
before
needed, roll the dough into shape on floured board, using
extra
flour,
if
needed, to handle.
Place on greased baking
sheet or in muffin tins.
Let biscuits rise 2 hours at room temperature.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: ham and carrot sandwich filling
directions: Combine all ingredients together and chill.
Spread on your favorite bread.
Makes 2 cups.

title: lomein rice
directions: Melt the margarine and brown noodles in a large pot until golden brown; remove from heat.
In a second bowl, combine the next 6 ingredients.
Twenty minutes before serving, add rice and liquid mixture to the noodles.
Bring to a boil, then cover, lower heat and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Combine ingredients with beater.
Drop by teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Bring all to boil, except cornstarch.
Thicken with the cornstarch, blended with cold water.
Add to beets; simmer for 10 minutes.

title: french cherry pie
directions: Combine cold milk, sour cream and almond extract in bowl.
Add pudding mix; mix at low speed until blended (about 1 minute). Pour into pie crust.
Chill 2 hours.
Spoon cherry pie filling over pie.

title: pea soup
directions: In Dutch oven cook celery, carrot and onion in olive oil until crisp-tender.
Stir in water, peas, salt, thyme and pepper.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, 45 to 60 minutes or until peas are tender.
Add parsley.
Simmer, uncovered, for 45 to 60 minutes or until thick.
Place 1/2 cup cooked brown rice atop individual servings.
Makes 8 (1 cup) servings.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Add lemon and eggs, one at a time. Gradually add flour, alternately with 7-Up, beating until smooth. Pour into greased and floured tube pan or large loaf pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Place egg in 1 1/2-quart casserole and beat well with fork. Stir in milk, sugar, corn, crackers and butter.
Microwave at Medium-high for 7 minutes.
Stir well.
Sprinkle with paprika. Microwave at Medium-high for 11 to 14 minutes.
When done, center will be just barely set.
Serves 4.

title: lemon pie(3 minutes)
directions: Stir together and put in graham cracker crust.

title: black magic cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in oblong pan 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: grandma's salami
directions: Mix well and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Form into 6 rolls about 3 inches in diameter and 7 inches long.
Place rolls on rack in pan.
Bake at 170° for 8 hours.
Turn rolls every hour.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Combine sugar and flour. In a separate mixing bowl, mix together eggs, butter, vanilla and buttermilk. Slowly add the sugar and flour mixture while mixing. Pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake for 10 minutes, then reduce oven to 325° and finish baking until golden brown or tester comes out clean (about 20 to 30 minutes).
Yield: 2 pieces.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Mix together the salt, flour and vanilla.
Add together.
Mix dough until soft.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Shake in bag, approximately 10 at a time, in 10x sugar.
Cool completely. Yields 6 dozen.

title: holiday mashed potatoes
directions: Add all ingredients to the mashed potatoes; beat until light and fluffy.
Place in a greased 9-inch round casserole and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cut up potatoes, onions and celery and put in medium size pot. Add water, tomato soup and other ingredients and cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with toast or saltines.

title: party dip
directions: Mix all together.
Bake
at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serve with Escort or Triscuit crackers.

title: caramel sweet potatoes
directions: In a 2-quart baking dish, peel sweet potatoes and slice into wedges.
Sprinkle sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Slice margarine and dot over potatoes.
Pour enough milk over potatoes to half cover potatoes (about 2 cups).
Place dish in center of preheated oven at about 275° for 2 to 3 hours or until potatoes have caramel covering potatoes.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in cereal.
Blend together banana, milk, egg and shortening.
Add flour mixture, stirring just until all flour is moistened.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
