Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center of the loaf comes out clean.
Cool in the pan for 10 minutes, then remove from pan and cool on a wire rack.
The bread slices and tastes better if it is wrapped and stored overnight.

title: cherry dessert supreme
directions: Mix well:
flour, sugar, nuts and butter.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven about 20 minutes or until a little brown.
Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Prepare whipped topping as directed on package.
Blend into cheese/sugar mixture.
Spread over cooled crust.
Pour cherry pie filling over the top.
Chill.
Serves 10 to 14.

title: pineapple preserves chicken
directions: Wash chicken breasts and drain.
Salt and pepper to taste. Place in lightly buttered casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken breasts.
Cover and cook at 350° for about 1 hour or until tender.

title: pasta garden salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed; drain.
Rinse pasta with cold water and drain.
Run cold water over frozen vegetables in strainer until thawed.
Drain.
Prepare salad dressing mix as directed on envelope.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, honey and oil.
Mix well and press into a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: banana split muffins
directions: Combine
biscuit
mix
and
1/4 cup sugar.
Combine egg yolks, milk
and shortening.
Add the milk mixture all at once to the dry
mixture,
stirring
just to moisten.
Place 1 1/2 tablespoons of
batter
in each of 12 cups of a greased muffin tin.
Cut
the banana
into 12 cubes.
Place a banana cube, a cherry half
and
a walnut
half atop the batter in each cup. Cover
with
a tablespoon more batter.
Beat egg whites until soft
peaks
form. Gradually
add
the 1/3 cup sugar, beating until stiff
peaks form.
Fold
in
the coconut.
Place 1 1/2 tablespoons of this meringue on each muffin.
Top with remaining cherries.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: virginia eakman's chicken terrapin
directions: Make a cream sauce with flour, butter and milk.
Mash the egg yolks with mustard and add to the sauce.
Let this stand over hot water for 1 hour.
Add lemon juice, chicken, olives and pimientos and cook until heated through.
At the last minute, add egg whites.

title: oreo ice cream pie
directions: Let
ice
cream sit at room temperature until softened. Mix all
ingredients
together
and pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Freeze and serve.

title: taco salad(perfect for a hot summer night)
directions: Combine Ready Hamburger Mix and green chili salsa in a medium skillet.
In a large salad bowl, combine lettuce, tomatoes, avocado, green onions, grated cheese and kidney beans.
Add hamburger mixture.
Toss gently.
Add tortilla chips and top with salad dressing of your choice.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spinach soup
directions: Put all ingredients, except cottage cheese, in a pot.
Cook over medium heat until spinach boils.
Remove from heat.
Add cottage cheese and puree in blender.
Return to pot, bring to a boil and simmer for 30 minutes.
(Can be frozen.)

title: knoedel(egg dumplings)
directions: This is one of the "old time" recipes where your mother told you it was a "little" of this and that; you can see and feel when it's right.
So good luck!

title: merry berry punch
directions: Combine lemonade concentrate, grenadine and strawberries in a punch bowl.
Slowly add 7-Up and ice cubes.
Makes 30 (4 ounce) servings.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook dry beans until done.
Add smoked sausage, Ro-Tel tomatoes and stew tomatoes.
Let simmer on low for 30 minutes, then add Minute rice.
Cook until rice is done.

title: dip for fresh vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients and keep in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar; blend in one egg at a time until mixed well.
Add vanilla; stir in salt, baking powder and flour. Chill dough.
Drop teaspoons of dough into powdered sugar.
Shape into balls.
Place 2-inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.
Yields about 50 cookies.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice up potatoes into small pieces.
Add water to cover potatoes and add salt.
Add onion and bacon or ham.
Cook until potatoes are done.
Then add a can of evaporated milk.
Let cook another 10 minutes on a low heat.

title: beef brisket
directions: Put brisket in crock-pot.
Cover with onion soup and beer. Cook on low 8 to 10 hours.
Slice diagonally and serve.

title: baked chicken with dressing(and giblet gravy)
directions: Boil chicken in a large pot.
Salt and pepper to taste. Remove chicken from broth.
Add livers and giblets to broth and cook 20 minutes.
Set aside.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Bring to boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Pour over rhubarb and add remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Boil veggies in salted water 5 minutes. Drain well. Fold in sour cream, soup, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix stuffing and melted butter together.
Put half of stuffing in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Pour in veggie mixture and cover with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Cook bacon and break into pieces. Mix all ingredients and put into pie shells. Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Drain meat well. Mix meat and soups well. Put 1/2 of the Doritos on bottom of large casserole dish. Pour 1/2 of meat mixture on top of this. Repeat these steps for second layer. Top with lots of grated cheese. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chili cheese dip no. 1
directions: Cube cheese and mix with chili, canned tomatoes and onion in top of double boiler.
Heat until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle tomato on top.
Serve with tortilla chips. Can also be cooked in crock-pot or microwave.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook potatoes, diced onion, salt and pepper until almost done. Add chopped clams.
Cook 15 minutes.
Heat milk and butter.
Add parsley flakes.
Add to mixture and remove from heat.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream soft butter and sugar for 2 minutes.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
In another bowl, add baking powder to flour.
Add flour, one-third at a time, to creamed mixture.
Chill 10 minutes.
Roll out and shape or cut out.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Combine in a bowl the sugar, ketchup,
molasses and mustard. Add all of the beans to it. Brown bacon and crumble pieces.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: kim chee(korean pickles)
directions: Bring 2 cups water and salt to a boil; pour over cucumbers. Let stand 1 1/2 hours.
Drain the water from the cucumbers and pour mixture of remaining ingredients over cucumbers; let stand 1/2 hour.
Refrigerate 24 hours before eating.
Can be put in canning jars, if you wish.
Will keep about 6 to 8 weeks. Delicious with sandwiches.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Mix all ingredients together with a fork until moistened; beat vigorously about 1 minute.
Turn into loaf pan. Bake, until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: easy enchilada casserole
directions: Cut tamales crosswise into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Line a 1 1/2-quart casserole with half of tamale slices.
Spread half of chili over tamale slices.
Top with half of onions, half of chips and half of cheese.
Repeat layers, except for remaining cheese. Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Top with cheese. Bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes more.
Makes 4 servings.

title: beef porcupines
directions: Mix beef, rice, onion and seasoning.
Form into small balls. Fry in oil until light brown on all sides.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer about 45 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Flatten biscuits and place one slice of cheese on each one.
Place frankfurters on cheese and roll biscuit and cheese around them.
Secure with a toothpick and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes or until biscuits are brown.

title: state fair meatballs
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients, then add to the ground beef.
Shape into balls.
Brown in margarine and place in a flat baking dish.
Mix together the soup and water; pour over the meatballs.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: crisp sweet pickles
directions: Place cucumbers in deep crockery pot and pour boiling water over them each day for 4 days.
On the 5th day, slice cucumbers into chunks.
Mix the vinegar, salt, sugar and spices, keeping the solution cold.
Pour over cucumber chunks and let stand 2 days. On 3rd day, pour vinegar solution into large saucepan and heat. Do not let it boil.
Pack pickles into jars and pour hot solution over them to fill jars; seal.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine butter with the sugar and beat until smooth.
Beat in eggs, one egg at a time, and then add the flour a little at a time.
Beat mixture until smooth.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: coconutty oat bars
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy. Blend in egg and vanilla. Add combined flour, baking powder and salt; mix well. Stir in remaining ingredients. Spread onto well greased 15 x 10 x 1 inch jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Cool; cut into 2 x 3 inch bars. Makes 25 bars.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and place in casserole.
Sprinkle with potato chips and nuts.
Bake at 325° until mixture is bubbly and top is brown.

title: debbie's award winning chocolate truffles
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar together until very smooth. Beat in melted, cooled chocolate and add flavoring.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cocoa covered cookie sheets.
Roll in cocoa and shape into balls.
Let set until almost firm.
Dip into more melted chocolate and let set until firm, or roll balls in powdered sugar or sprinkles.

title: pineapple flop cake
directions: Mix by hand the flour, soda, sugar and pineapple (juice and all).
Bake at 325° in long pan.
Mix sugar, Pet milk, oleo and coconut; bring to boil and boil for 4 minutes.
Pour over cake while warm.

title: chili hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix well.
Store in refrigerator.
Spread mixture on cocktail rye bread; heat in oven until bubbly.
Serve hot.

title: barbecue hot dogs
directions: Saute onions in a little butter.
Add remaining ingredients. Put desired amount of hot dogs in a pan or casserole.
Pour sauce over.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together the mayonnaise, cream of chicken soup, egg, cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Combine mixture with the broccoli.
Put in shallow casserole dish and top with crumbs. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: black-eyed pea and rice soup
directions: In a large saucepan, stir together the undrained black-eyed peas, the water, sliced onion, sliced celery, diced bacon, chicken bouillon, garlic salt, pepper and bottled green pepper sauce. Bring mixture to boiling.
Stir in the uncooked rice.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is done.

title: pickled zucchini (squash)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a saucepan, bring to a boil and pour over squash.
Let stand for 1 hour, stirring occasionally. In saucepan, bring mixture to a boil for 3 minutes.
Continue to simmer while putting mixture in jars.
As each jar is filled, clamp at once.

title: avocado salad
directions: Blanch chopped pepper; boil in water for 1 minute, rinsing in cold water.

title: granny's apple cake
directions: Chop the apples. Sprinkle the sugar and cinnamon over the apples. Stir and set aside. Combine the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour in a greased and floured tube pan.
Layer batter, then apples, ending with apples on top.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen strawberry squares
directions: Cool well before covering cooked bottom.
Then cover with 1 cup whipped cream; sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.
Keep in freezer.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put butter and peanut butter in a microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on High for 3 minutes. Remove. Stir in the confectioners sugar. Chill for about 2 hours. Cut into pieces and serve.

title: pam's green beans
directions: Heat green beans.
Drain and put in a bowl.
Put sugar and vinegar in a saucepan and heat on medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Pour over green beans.
Put in refrigerator until chilled.
Drain off liquid.
As an option, you can cut up onion and place on top.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut apricots, pineapple, pears and cherries into chunks. Place in bowl.
Add peaches (cut into chunks) and peach juice. Add sliced bananas, kiwi, Tang and instant pudding.
Mix until combined.

title: parmesan appetizer spread
directions: Mix all ingredients and spoon into glass pie size pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: apple crunch
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam.
Fill with the apple pie filling.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over the pie filling.
Pour melted butter evenly over all the cake mix.
(Make sure all the cake mix is moist.)
Top with pecans.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour. You can top with vanilla ice cream.

title: oven omelet
directions: Put 3 slices of cheese on bottom of greased pie dish.
Crumble up 5 slices of bacon and sprinkle on top of cheese.
Mix eggs and milk together and pour over bacon and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put rest of bacon and cheese on top and bake 10 minutes longer.
Let set for 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Spread cookie sheet with cream cheese.
Brown ground beef and mix in taco seasoning.
Drain meat and seasoning with salsa and spread over cream cheese.
Sprinkle Mozzarella and Cheddar cheese on top.
Put in 325° to 350° oven until cheese begins to melt. Serve with nacho chips.

title: tuna and cheese casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain.
Mix noodles with remaining ingredients.
Cover aluminum foil and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: roast beef salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve in stuffed tomatoes or make sandwiches.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg, flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Add nuts, apples and vanilla.
Place in greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: bite sized mushrooms
directions: Remove stems and hollow out with melon baller. Stir together remaining ingredients in order and stuff mushrooms.
Broil 3 to 4 minutes. Serve.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Place apples, drained pineapple and nuts in bowl; mix. Combine cornstarch, sugar, vinegar and reserved pineapple juice. Cook over low heat for 1 minute, then add beaten egg.
Cook until thick.
Cool.
When cool, stir in apple mixture and mix well. Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.

title: opal's cornmeal dumplings
directions: In saucepan, combine water, cornmeal and salt; bring to boil. Cook and stir until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir a moderate amount of the hot mixture into 1 beaten egg.
Return to hot mixture.
Stir together the flour, baking powder and pepper.
Add to the cornmeal mixture; beat well.
Stir in the corn.
Drop batter by rounded tablespoons into boiling stew mixture.
Cover; simmer until dumplings are done, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Blend butter with sugar.
Cream until fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs, one at a time; mix well.
Add flour and baking soda.
Mix well until creamy.
Spread evenly in a 12 x 16-inch greased pan. Place sliced apples on top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake at 350°, approximately 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together the soup, onion powder, lemon juice and dressing. Place in casserole dish the broccoli on the bottom, the chicken next, soup mixture, then cheese, then bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add molasses, sour milk and soda, baking powder, salt and spices sifted with flour, well beaten egg and raisins.
Drop from teaspoon to greased pan. Bake in moderate oven 7 to 10 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook squash. Cool, drain and mash.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in casserole dish and bake at 400° until done or desired thickness.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns and crumble by hand.
Mix together with the remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: onion dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Great served with chips or vegetables.

title: chili for four
directions: Heat oil and fry the 2 chopped onions and garlic for 5 minutes, until softened.
Add the ground beef; stir over moderate heat until lightly browned.
Stir in chili powder; cook for 1 minute.
Add all the remaining ingredients, except the kidney beans, sour cream and 1 chopped onion.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Discard the bay leaf.
Add the kidney beans; simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve in bowls alone or on top of a bed of rice.
Top each serving with a spoonful of sour cream and chopped raw onion.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place in pan and add chicken.
Refrigerate for 4 to 5 hours.
Grill over charcoal.

title: buttermilk waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Add buttermilk and egg yolks.
Mix lightly.
Stir in melted butter.
Then fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: baking powder cinnamon rolls
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cream of tartar.
Using pastry blender, cut butter into dry ingredients.
Add milk, mixing with a fork.
Roll out dough onto floured board in large rectangle.
Spread filling over dough. Roll up dough and cut into 16 sections.
Place sections in greased muffin tins and bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until a light golden color.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Saute beef and onion until brown.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer slowly for a few minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: oven burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Spread on bread slices that have been buttered.
Put buttered side down on cookie sheet and spread the above mixture on the slices.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes and serve hot.
(The bread will be a little toastie and you don't need buns!)

title: burrito casserole
directions: Cook hamburger meat and drain.
Add chopped onion, bell pepper, taco seasoning, tomato sauce, cheese soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Cook together about 15 minutes, then layer in a casserole dish with cut tortillas, meat and grated cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini according to package directions; rinse and cool.
Mix dressing ingredients together.
Toss with tortellini and sliced vegetables.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and set aside.
Cream together sugar and butter.
Add egg to creamed mixture; beat well.
Add milk alternately with dry ingredients.
Break up cranberry sauce and fold into batter with nuts.
Then put into greased and floured bread pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream marshmallow cream with cream cheese.
Slice fresh fruit, such as apples, pears, bananas, strawberries, blueberries, grapes, peaches, etc.
Place in Lazy Susan with dip mixture in middle. Makes a colorful dish.
Great for pool parties.

title: shrimp omelet
directions: Cook according to directshuns macaroni; drain.
Beat aigs. Add salt 'n peppa to taste.
Add mix'n then mix up.
Layer half the macaroni in a bakin' dish, then half the onion'n chez. Repeat.
Now pore aig'n milk mixture ovah all 'n dot with buttah. Bake (until firm) at 350° fur 'bout 30 minutes.

title: savory grilled potatoes
directions: Mix salad dressing and seasonings in large bowl until well blended.
Stir in potatoes and onions to coat.
Onion should come apart while mixing.
Divide potato mixture evenly among 6 (12-inch) square pieces of heavy-duty foil.
Seal each to form packet.
Place packets on grill over medium-hot coals.
Grill, covered, 25 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 6.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together (macaroni should be cooked and drained) and pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
This can be cut in half to make a smaller portion.

title: artichoke rice medley
directions: Cook rice according to package directions, using 2 1/2 cups water.
Remove to large bowl.
Drain artichoke hearts, reserving marinade.
Chop coarsely the hearts, olives and
drained and rinsed water chestnuts; add to rice.
In a small bowl, mix reserved marinade, mayonnaise, curry powder, salt and pepper; stir into warm rice.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: crab dip
directions: Place cream cheese in small serving dish.
Combine cocktail sauce, horseradish and crab meat.
Pour over cream cheese.
Serve with Ritz or Triscuits crackers.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Blend sugar, brown sugar and fat.
Add eggs.
Blend well.
Add flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Add oatmeal, vanilla and chocolate bits and nuts.
Make large cookies and bake in oven at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: carrot muffins
directions: Beat sugar, oil and egg.
Add baking soda, water and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix until moistened.
Stir in grated carrots. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen carrot muffins.

title: piccolo pizzas
directions: Brown sausage or hamburger; drain and add oregano and garlic. On a greased baking sheet, flatten biscuits to 4-inch circles; leave rim.
Fill with tomato paste, then sausage.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake at 425° for about 10 minutes.
Garnish with olive slices.

title: rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 12-cup Bundt pan. Sprinkle half of the nuts on bottom of pan.
Mix all cake ingredients together.
Pour batter over nuts.
Bake 1 hour. Cool.
Invert on a large serving plate.
Prick top with a fork. Drizzle glaze over cake until used up.
Best if left to sit overnight.

title: yeast bread
directions: Mix all together.
Let rise 1 hour.
Put in muffin pans.
Bake at 350°
until brown.

title: dick's broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Cook onion, celery and potatoes in 4 cups water until done, approximately 10 minutes.
Add broccoli and bring to a boil and boil for 10 minutes.
Strain and save liquid.
If not 4 cups, add enough water to make 4 cups.
Put liquid in pot; add 4 cups milk. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
In small pot, melt margarine; add flour to margarine.
Stir until smooth.
Add salt, pepper and cheese to liquid, stirring constantly.
Add flour mixture; stir until smooth.
Add broccoli mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and serve.
Do not let boil when you add milk.
Turn off as soon as (mixture) soup begins to boil.

title: party dip
directions: Early in the day, blend cream cheese, light cream, chili sauce, onion, salt, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and pepper. Blend until smooth and creamy. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Makes 1/2 cup.

title: poppy seed sherry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 5 minutes.
Pour into greased 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool in pan on rack 25 minutes, then turn out onto serving plate.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together. Put into a greased 9 x 12-inch cake pan. Pour rhubarb over cake dough. Sprinkle gelatin on top of rhubarb. Mix together 1 cup sugar, 1/2 cup flour and 6 tablespoons butter until crumb-like.
Sprinkle over rhubarb. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter a 10 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Cover the bottom of dish with bread (remove the crust).
Cook and drain sausage. Sprinkle over bread.
Cover with cheese.
Mix eggs with half and half (salt and pepper to taste).
Pour over cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cheddary scalloped potatoes
directions: In skillet over medium heat in hot margarine, cook onion until tender.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Add potatoes.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until hot and bubbling, stirring occasionally.
Yields 4 servings.

title: baklava
directions: Combine sugar and water in a large saucepan.
Cut lemon in half and squeeze juice into sugar and water, then drop the lemon halves into the pot.
Add cinnamon and cloves and bring to a boil; simmer until mixture thickens and reaches a syrupy consistency. Remove from heat and cool to room temperature.
Remove lemon peel, cloves and cinnamon sticks.
Set aside.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 11 baking pan with tortillas or chips, dipped in broth.
Cover tortillas with bite size chicken pieces; top with onion, then 1/2 the cheese.
Mix tomatoes with soup. Pour soup and tomatoes over chicken and top with remaining cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix milk, pie filling and pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip. Chill thoroughly or freeze slightly.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper; pound into steak.
Brown steak in hot oil.
Saute onions and mushrooms in butter.
Add tomatoes. Heat to boiling.
Place steak in baking dish.
Pour tomato mixture over steak.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add next 5 ingredients; simmer 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil evaporated milk and sugar together about 20 minutes until forms hard ball in cold water.
Add Marshmallow Fluff, peanut butter and vanilla.
Put in 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: beef soup
directions: In a huge pot, combine all the ingredients.
Bring to boil, stirring occasionally.
Cook until vegetables are tender to your liking.
Serve over cooked rice if desired.

title: apple pie
directions: In saucepan, put sugar, orange juice, lemon juice and water. Bring to a boil.
Let cook 5 minutes, then put apples in and cook 5 minutes more.
Then lift apples out into a pie crust.
Pour juice over apples and dot with butter.
Then stir together sugar and cinnamon.
Put over apples, then put pie crust on top.
Press edges together.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad(ingredients for 10 to 12 servings)
directions: Preparation:
Soak broccoli and cauliflower in cold water with 1 teaspoon salt 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Cook noodles until tender; drain. Layer noodles, vegetables, soup and tuna.
Repeat.
Top with crumbled chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: asparagus peking style
directions: In a pan, heat oil, chicken stock, water, sherry, soy sauce and cornstarch.
Stir constantly until it boils.
Add asparagus; heat thoroughly.
Serve hot.

title: creamy pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sifted sugar thoroughly.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, on high speed.
Beat well.
Add flour which has been sifted 3 times alternately with whipping cream, adding flour first and last.
Add vanilla, lemon and almond extracts.
Cook in greased and floured pan at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until tested done.
Do not open oven during first hour.
Cool slightly before moving from pan.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into a ball.
Sprinkle parsley on top.

title: old south pralines
directions: In large 3 1/2 quart heavy saucepan, combine sugar, soda, buttermilk and salt.
Cook over high heat about 5 minutes (or to 210° on candy thermometer).
Stir often and scrape bottom of pan. Mixture will foam up.
Add butter or margarine and 2 cups pecan halves.
Over medium heat, continue cooking, stirring constantly and scraping bottom of pan, until candy reaches 234° on thermometer.
Remove from heat and cool slightly, about 2 minutes. Beat with spoon until thick and creamy.
Drop from tablespoons onto waxed paper.
Let cool.
Top each candy with remaining pecan halves.
Makes about 20 pralines, 2-inches in diameter.

title: peanut butter chocolate kisses
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix cup sugar, brown sugar, peanut butter, margarine and egg thoroughly.
Stir in flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar. Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until edges are light brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Immediately press candy kisses firmly in each cookie; cool.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: my biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco with pastry blender.
Add buttermilk and knead well to soft dough.
Cut out into biscuits and bake at 400° until brown (12 to 15 minutes).
Makes 12 to 15 biscuits.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Melt chocolate and paraffin in double boiler on low to medium heat.
Mix together peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme, melted margarine and vanilla.
When well blended, gradually add 10x sugar.
Shape eggs, dunk on fork in chocolate.
Place on waxed paper and refrigerate for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Peel potatoes; cook in small amount of salted boiling water until tender.
Drain and refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Next day, grate potatoes coarsely, mix with remaining ingredients and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Put in shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fluffy mud cake
directions: Melt chocolate in a double boiler over hot water (not boiling); stir until chocolate appears smooth.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into chocolate mixture.

title: gooey vanilla cake
directions: Mix dry cake mix, 1 egg, nuts and margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over first layer. Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook beef in kettle; add the remaining ingredients and simmer until done (10 to 15 minutes).
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown ground chuck; mix in chili powder.
Mix chili beans and chili sauce in pan with 2 cans of water.
After chuck is browned, mix with the chili sauce in pan.
Let simmer for about 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli until done.
Drain very well, at least 1/2 hour.
Mix all ingredients except butter and dressing.
Pour into casserole baking dish.
Melt butter; add dressing.
Toss until lightly, but completely coated.
Spoon on casserole.
Bake approximately 30 minutes or until golden brown. (Can use covered casserole dish if you wish.)

title: liver "bait" for dogs
directions: Put liver and 1/4 cup salt in pot.
Cover with water and soak for 5 to 10 minutes to remove blood.
Drain and rinse 2 or 3 times.
Place liver in cooking pot.
Cover with water.
Add olive oil, garlic powder and thyme.
Bring to boil and boil for 20 minutes.
Remove from pot and drain.
Freeze or store in refrigerator until needed.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Brown meat until lightly browned.
Add all other ingredients except
spaghetti and simmer at least 30 minutes.

title: coconut pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake in a 13 x 9-inch pan according to directions.
Make pudding.
Heat pineapple and sugar
(do not cook).
When cake is cool, punch holes with a wooden spoon handle.
Spread pineapple over cake, then pudding, then Cool Whip.
Sprinkle coconut on top. Refrigerate.

title: oatmeal sugar cookies
directions: Mix together and refrigerate 4 to 5 hours.
Drop by teaspoonful.
Can flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: marvelous fresh strawberry pie
directions: In large saucepan, combine sugar, water and cornstarch.
Cook over medium heat until clear and thick.
Stir in gelatin.
Let cool.
Fold in strawberries.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells.
Chill pies until ready to serve.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: spicy crackers
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Mix seasoning with oleo.
Put crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mix over crackers.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Pour onto wax paper to cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix in dressing.
In a large baking dish, place 1/3 of the dressing, 1/2 of the chicken, can of mushroom soup and 1/2 can broth. Add another layer of dressing.
Mix rest of chicken, then the can of chicken soup and 1/2 can broth. Top with rest of dressing mix and bake at 350° for 50 or 60 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken wings(bake at 350~)
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Dip chicken in melted butter, then in cheese mixture.
Arrange in shallow baking dish on foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage until tender, about 10 minutes.
Mix cheese, flour, butter, salt and pepper.
Put into greased casserole alternating layers of cabbage and cheese mixture.
Pour milk over all.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until water is gone.
Mix raisins, eggs, applesauce and oil.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake in loaf pan or angel food pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Top with cheese slices.
Combine soup and wine and stir well.
Spoon sauce over chicken and sprinkle with stuffing mix. Drizzle butter over crumbs and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Garnish with parsley.
Yields 8 servings.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients. Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, garlic powder and celery. Pour over vegetables and toss gently. Refrigerate overnight. Stir in bacon bits just before serving.

title: caramels
directions: Melt butter in 3-quart saucepan.
Add brown sugar and salt. Stir until thoroughly combined.
Stir in corn syrup; mix well. Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir over medium heat until candy reaches firm ball stage, 245°, about 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Pour in buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool and cut in squares.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel
the potatoes and cut into small quarters;
wrench the potatoes and cover with sufficient amount of water; bring to a boil
and boil until tender, not mushy.
Drain and rinse with cool water for about 5 minutes.

title: peach pickles
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, water and spice.
Bring to boil. Simmer peaches until color changes.
Seal peaches and syrup in sterilized jars.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt oleo.
Beat eggs.
Combine all ingredients and stir together.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Arrange cooked broccoli in bottom of a lightly greased shallow casserole.
Cover with cooked chicken.
Blend together soup, milk and broth; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over all. Top with mixture of stuffing and melted butter.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all except crust, milk and pudding and spread in crust. Next, beat milk and pudding until well blended (2 minutes).
Mix well and pour over top of cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 3 hours or more.

title: hot tuna or chicken sandwich
directions: Mix ingredients well, except for rolls.
Spread on rolls. Wrap in boil and bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: jan's cheesecake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a bowl; blend well.
Press into bottom of ungreased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.
Combine cream cheese and one cup of sugar; beat at medium speed until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add lemon rind and lemon juice; mix well.
Spoon cream cheese mixture over crust.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until cheesecake is set.
Remove from oven, cool on wire rack; chill for 8 hours. Serves 8 to 10.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries in food chopper using fine blade.
Add sugar mixture and let stand 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Soften gelatin
in orange juice 5 minutes.
Stir over hot water until dissolved.
Mix
gelatin
mixture with other ingredients and fold in container greased with mayonnaise.
Chill.

title: grandma bierbach's parker house rolls
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add egg and beat well.
Add milk, cooled to lukewarm.
Then add yeast and flour.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Form and let raise about one hour.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Garnish with maraschino cherries on top.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pastel cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the sugar, shortening, gelatin, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Shape in 3/4-inch balls.
Put 3 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets. Flatten each with drinking glass with an etched design on bottom for design on cookie.
Dip glass in sugar.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes about 6 1/2 dozen.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Brown ground beef in a skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Place in a crock-pot with remaining ingredients and 1 cup water. Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Garnish with chopped red onion and green pepper.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: apple and peanut salad
directions: Cook the first 6 ingredients until thick; pour over the chopped apples and peanuts.
Roll peanuts with rolling pin before mixing.

title: barbecue pork steaks
directions: Mix ketchup, barbecue sauce and Coca-Cola.
Pour over steaks. Sprinkle brown sugar on each steak.
Cook at 375° for 1 hour.
May add chopped onions if desired.

title: oatmeal refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape in a long roll and wrap in wax paper. Chill overnight. Slice and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: banberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar in a saucepan.
Stir in the salt and liquid.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and cool.
Add lemon juice and berries.
Slice bananas into pie shell.
Pour berry mixture over them and chill at least 2 hours.
Just before serving, top with sweetened whipped cream.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: peach crunch
directions: Mix flour, sugar, pecans and margarine well.
Pat into bottom of a 9 x 13 inch glass baking dish.
Bake about 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool completely.

title: spoon bread
directions: Put cornmeal, milk, butter, sugar, salt and egg yolks in a 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until mixture boils and thickens.
Stir constantly.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into cooked mixture.
Blend thoroughly.

title: mexican layered appetizer
directions: Layer ingreds. in order given in square 8 or 9 in. dish. Refrigerate until served. Can use more or less Picante sauce as desired.

title: barbecue ham
directions: Fry bacon in Dutch oven.
Add onion and saute.
Add remaining ingredients, except cornstarch.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add cornstarch to 1/2 cup water; add to mixture and boil 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve over buns.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Stir together Miracle Whip, Dijon mustard and honey.
Place chicken breasts on grill or rack of broiler.
Brush with half of sauce.
Grill or broil 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn and brush with remaining sauce.
Continue grilling 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.

title: evergreen punch
directions: Mix together and top with lime sherbet. (Also good with lemon or orange sherbet.)

title: terri's poppy seed bread
directions: Mix and beat sugar, eggs, oil and milk.
Sift dry ingredients and blend well to the milk mixture.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° if using a glass loaf pan.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except preserves and sour cream. Combine sour cream and preserves; mix into batter.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: applesauce oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, egg and applesauce.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Add nuts and raisins if you like.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheets for 10 to 12 minutes in oven that's been preheated to 375°.

title: chocolate layered dessert
directions: Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Gently stir in 2 cups of whipped topping.
Arrange 1/2 of the cake cubes in bowl.
Drizzle with 1/2 of the chocolate syrup.
Layer with 1/2 of chopped candy and 1/2 of pudding.
Repeat layers, ending with pudding. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Garnish with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped candy.

title: stuffed flank steak
directions: Heat first the oil and butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add bread cubes and saute until browned on all sides. Remove from heat.
Combine ground beef and next 8 ingredients in a large bowl; mix well.
Gently stir in sauteed bread cubes.
Cut a large pocket lengthwise in flank steak.
Stuff steak with ground beef mixture.
Secure with string at 2-inch intervals.
Heat remaining butter and oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat.
Sprinkle steak with salt and pepper and brown in oil.
Add bay leaves, carrot, onion, tomato and thyme.
Cook, uncovered, 5 minutes over medium heat.
Add broth and wine; bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Transfer meat to serving platter.
Remove string and keep warm.

title: drawn butter sauce
directions: In double boiler, melt butter.
Stir in flour, pepper, salt and paprika until smooth.
Slowly stir in water.
Cook until thickened.
Just before serving, stir in lemon juice.
Use on broiled or fried fish.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Saute onions and green peppers.
Mix remaining ingredients and simmer for a few minutes.
Add leftover chopped beef.
Makes about 6 sandwiches.

title: waikiki meat balls
directions: Drain pineapple, saving the syrup.
Mix the cornstarch and brown sugar in the saucepan.
Add syrup, vinegar and soy sauce and stir until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickens.
Boil 1 minute.
Add pineapple, chopped green pepper and meat balls.

title: lord's chili verde
directions: Put stew meat into crock-pot with tenderizer and water.
Add garlic chips and onion, chopped.
Cook onion for 1/2 hour.
Chop green chilies; add to meat.
Add the rest of the ingredients except for the toast and tomatoes, then cook on low for about 2 hours.
When almost ready to serve, add the toast and tomatoes. Let stand for a few minutes.
Serve with warm tortillas.

title: pig pickin' cake*
directions: Blend well.
(I find it easier to mix the pudding powder and the pineapple together first, then mix in the Cool Whip.)
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cinnamon and 2/3 cup sugar in paper or plastic bag.
Quarter biscuits and shake 10 to 15 pieces at a time until all are covered with cinnamon and sugar.
Press biscuits lightly into well-greased Bundt pan.
Place butter (margarine) and 1 cup sugar in saucepan.
Heat until boiling. Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Invert on platter or plate.
Keep lightly covered.
(Good warmed up in the microwave.)

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Bake at 400 ° for 45 minutes. May be frozen uncooked.

title: calico beans #2
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add sugar, catsup, mustard and vinegar.
Stir and add all beans.
Combine and simmer 15 minutes. Serves 6.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and mix by hand.
Roll into meatballs.
Cook in frying pan over medium heat.
When medium brown in color, remove from pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts
in
water
until	tender;
drain. Pull meat off bone into	small bits.
Save broth.
Melt margarine and pour over crumbs.
In
square, Pyrex dish, put a thin layer of crumbs and then a layer of chicken.

title: hollandaise snack mix
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. In a small saucepan, melt butter over medium heat. Stir in next 3 ingredients. In a large bowl, mix together peanuts, crackers and pretzels. Pour butter mixture over peanut mixture. Toss until well coated.
Spread evenly on a baking sheet. Bake 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Transfer to paper towels to cool completely. Store in airtight container. Yields about 6 cups snack mix.

title: spinach and artichoke casserole
directions: Cook spinach. Drain well. Cut artichokes into small pieces. Combine all ingredients. Bake in buttered 2-quart casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: truffles
directions: Heat semisweet chocolate in heave 2 quart saucepan on low heat, stirring constantly, until melted. Remove from heat. Stir in margarine. Stir in whipping cream.

Refrigerate 10 to 15 minutes, stirring frequently, just until thick enough to hold a shape. Drop mixture by teaspoon fulls onto foil covered cookie sheet. Shape into balls. Freeze for 30 minutes. Heat shortening and chocolate chips on low heat, stirring constantly until chocolate is melted and is smooth. Remove from heat. Dip truffles one at a time into chocolate and place on foil lined cookie sheet. Immediately, sprinkle with finely chopped nuts if desired. Refrigerate until set. Drizzle some with with a mixture of 1/4 cup powdered sugar, 1/2 tsp. milk. Refrigerate just until set. Serve at room temperature. Store in air tight container.

title: microwave sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if the skin is tough. Otherwise, just rinse and pat dry.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through.
Use a handle of a spoon to prevent knife from cutting all the way.
Place potatoes in a microsafe dish or pan.
Sprinkle with melted butter and chopped parsley or chives.

title: waffle iron cookies
directions: Melt chocolate squares and butter or margarine.
Add sugar, eggs, vanilla, salt and flour.
Drop 1/2 teaspoon amounts on waffle iron.
Bake 2 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Bring sugars and Karo syrup to a boil and then add peanut butter.
Pour quickly over corn flakes and peanuts.
Press into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Break Hershey bars on top.
Place pan in oven a few minutes until chocolate
can be spread evenly on the top.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk and sugar.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add dry ingredients to the milk mixture.
This batter should be thin enough to run through a funnel.
Drop from funnel into hot, deep fat.
Fry until golden brown.
Remove from oil; drain.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: italian meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into balls and bake in oven at 350° to 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: dark chocolate parfait
directions: To boiling water in blender, add chocolate, sweetener, egg yolks and salt; blend for 1 minute.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Add chocolate mixture to egg whites and fold carefully until well blended.
Chill for a few minutes while you prepare Whipped Topping 2.
Alternate chocolate and topping layers in parfait glasses and chill until ready to serve.
Serves 6.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine ham, onion powder, pork, eggs (slightly beaten), salt, pepper and cracker crumbs; mix well.
Shape mixture into a loaf. Place in a greased baking dish.

title: chocolate peanut balls
directions: Melt butter.
Add peanut butter and sugar; blend well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Roll in balls.
Melt chocolate and paraffin.
Dip balls in this, then put on rack to cool.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Roll out and cut into thin biscuits.
Dip in melted butter. Stack 2 biscuits together.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 400°.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drop cream cheese mixture by spoonfuls into chocolate cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan. Simmer 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend together cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce and garlic. Chop onion and beef slices; mix all together.
Roll into a ball. Roll over chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cocoa krispies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Blend butter and sugar thoroughly. Add egg and vanilla. Beat well. Stir in sifted dry ingredients.
Mix in Cocoa Krispies.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased baking sheet. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 13 minutes.
Yields about 3 1/2 dozen cookies 2 1/2-inches in diameter.

title: rancho beans
directions: Fry ground beef in skillet until well done.
Add pork and beans, mustard, ketchup, salt and pepper.
Stir together.
Turn on simmer for a minute until evenly heated.
Makes 6 servings.

title: marcia's breakfast casserole
directions: Generously butter a glass dish (9 x 12-inch).
Mix and beat eggs and milk together.
Add seasonings.
Brown and drain sausage. Squeeze 8 slices of bread on bottom of dish and add layer of sausage and cheese.
Put on 8 more slices of bread and add remaining sausage and cheese.
Pour egg and milk mixture over bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°. Uncover to brown the last 15 minutes.

title: caviar pie
directions: Combine eggs and 3 tablespoons mayonnaise and spread in an 8-inch spring-form pan.
Add onion over top.

title: dutch leek soup
directions: Melt margarine in a pan.
Add leeks and stew for 5 minutes. Add hot water and bring to a boil.
Stir in macaroni and cook 20 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.
Just before serving, sprinkle some grated cheese over soup.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter, sugar and milk together.
Bring to a boil exactly 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and marshmallow.
Pour in buttered 12 x 7-inch pan.
Place in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Then cut into small pieces.

title: german chocolate cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Add flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Add chocolate chips, then fold in German chocolate frosting.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until cookies are golden brown.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Make a mixture of food coloring, cocoa and salt.
Add buttermilk and flour alternately. Add vanilla.
Sprinkle soda over batter.
Pour vinegar over soda. Fold into batter.
Do not mix!!! Pour into pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost with Vanilla Frosting.

title: pastel bavarian
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water.
Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Fold into whipped topping, blending well.
Spoon into individual dessert dishes or bowl.
Chill until set, at least 2 hours.
Garnish with fresh fruit if desired.
Makes 7 servings, approximately 40 calories per serving.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and sprinkle generously with garlic salt.
Combine meat and all other ingredients and heat until bubbling.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Taste during cooking and add salt and pepper to taste.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix together cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder.
Melt butter or margarine in baking dish. Stuff mushrooms with cheese mixture and put in baking dish. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: taco surprise
directions: You need to chop up cooked chicken.
(You can use leftover chicken or stir-fry some.)
Chop up broccoli, cauliflower and onion.
Stir-fry chicken and all vegetables.
Meanwhile, cook some rice.
When rice is done, mix everything together.
Start cooking taco shells.
You can fry them with butter spray or warm in microwave.
Fill taco shells just like a regular taco.

title: devilish delight
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
While cake is still warm, poke holes in it with a fork.
Pour the jar of ice cream topping over the cake.
Pour the can of sweetened condensed milk on the cake. Refrigerate the cake or cool completely.
Before serving, spread whipped topping on the cake and sprinkle the Heath bar bits on top.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites and vanilla until stiff.
Gradually add sugar. Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Heat oven to 350°.
Turn off. Drop batter on aluminum foil on cookie sheet by teaspoonfuls. Place in turned off oven and leave overnight.

title: spinach pie i
directions: Mix together and pour into 9-inch uncooked Pet-Ritz pie shell. Generously sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Dot with butter and lightly sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes. May cover edges of pie crust with foil.
Also good cold.

title: mexicali sausage casserole
directions: Remove casing from sausage.
In large skillet, brown sausage, breaking up with a spoon as it cooks.
Remove from skillet; set aside.
In same skillet, saute zucchini and onion until crisp-tender.

title: jello dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add 1 cup juice and fruit, drained well.
Mix. Pour into glass pan.
Refrigerate until set. Soften cream cheese.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Spread on jello that has set.
Sprinkle nuts on top. Chill one-half hour before serving.

title: clams parmesano
directions: Cook noodles as package directs; drain.
In same pan, saute onion in margarine.
Add clams, milk and contents of seasoning packet; heat through.
Toss noodles with clam sauce and parsley. Makes 3 (1 cup) servings.

title: easy shrimp scampi
directions: Melt butter and spices.
Saute shrimp until pink.
Serve over noodles.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Beat together with mixer.
Spread frosting into two cooled cookies, sandwich-style.

title: super corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and pour off all but 2 tablespoons drippings.
Add chopped onion and cook until lightly brown.
Add remaining ingredients and a dash of pepper.
Heat to boiling and then simmer a minute or two.
Serve topped with bacon and butter.
Serves 6.

title: crab-n-cheese fondue
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart saucepan and heat slowly. If mixture seems too thick, it can be thinned with more white wine.
After mixture is well blended, pour into fondue pot. Double recipe if serving a large group.
Serve with French bread, cut into 1/2-inch cubes.

title: ice cream salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water until dissolved (2 minutes). While it is still hot, add ice cream and stir until it is melted. Add pineapple and nuts.
Put in refrigerator until salad.

title: one pan pork chop dinner
directions: In 9 x 13-inch glass pan, line the bottom of pan with pork chops.
Pour the cans of stewed tomatoes evenly over chops. Sprinkle garlic powder, onion powder, salt, pepper and assorted flaked Italian seasonings over mixture to taste.
Cut onion in thin rings and layer evenly over recipe.
Cut potatoes in thin slices and place edge first in between tomatoes and chops.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry butter
directions: Combine all ingredients, blending well.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Yields about 1 3/4 cups of butter.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach.
Drain water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix gently.
Using 1 can onion rings, put 1/2 of the onion rings in the casserole and 1/2 on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Yummy!

title: ham ball
directions: Lightly grease a pan, 10 x 15 x 1-inch.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Place balls 2 inches apart in pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°, or until brown. Serve warm.

title: clam and horseradish dip
directions: Mix and store in refrigerator.

title: frozen punch base
directions: Mix sugar and hot water, stirring until dissolved.
Let cool. Add orange juice, lemonade and apricot juice.
Freeze.
To serve, spoon the desired amount of this slush into your glass filled with 7-Up and enjoy.
This can be kept in your freezer and used to make individual servings of punch.

title: cheesy biscuits
directions: Cut biscuits into 2 or more pieces.
Dip in melted oleo or butter.
Roll in grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake as directed on biscuit can.

title: caramel corn crunch
directions: Combine popped corn and nuts; keep warm in 225° oven.
In saucepan, combine sugar, butter and corn syrup.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir until mixture turns caramel color (about 280° on candy thermometer). Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Place popped corn mixture in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; carefully pour sugar mixture over.
Mix well; turn out.
Quickly break into clusters with 2 forks.
Store in a tightly covered container.
Makes about 9 cups.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven 350 degrees. Combine cheese, flour, and seasoning in a flat dish, set aside. Mix egg and milk. Dip chicken in egg mix then in cheese mix, place in a 9 x 13 bake dish. Pour melted butter over chicken and bake for 30 - 35 minutes, or until chicken is no longer pink.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: In 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, in hot oil, cook carrot, celery and garlic until tender-crisp, stirring occasionally.
Add broth and orzo.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cook 15 minutes or until orzo is tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in chicken and parsley; heat through.
Serve with crackers.

title: cherry fluff dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients at once.
Pour into glass bowl or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
May freeze leftovers.

title: french raisin pie
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and melted oleo and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients (except pie shell) and mix well again. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix together and freeze according to directions of freezer.

title: chicken, rice and biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Heat margarine in a large saucepan on medium-high heat.
Add onion and celery; cook and stir until tender.
Stir in water, soup, vegetables, paprika, poultry seasoning and thyme.
Cover; boil.
Stir in chicken and rice. Pour into greased 3-quart casserole.
Top with biscuits.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: marinated italian chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in shallow pan.
Pour dressing over; marinate for 15 minutes.
Place chicken on rack of broiler pan. Broil for 5 to 7 minutes on each side or until juices run clear. Serves 4.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Cream together sour cream, sugar and eggs.
Bring to boil 2 sticks butter, 1 cup water and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Add to creamed mixture.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix well. Pour in greased cookie sheet; bake 20 minutes at 350°.
While hot, ice with the following icing.
Bring to boil 1 stick of butter, 6 tablespoons milk and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Add powdered sugar to mixture. Spread on cake while hot.

title: greg's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown sausage, onion, green pepper and garlic.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: lime cucumber salad
directions: Prepare jello with water.
Add vinegar and let thicken slightly.
Combine cheese, vegetables and salt; add to thickened jello.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Whip with eggbeater.
Pour into bowl or mold.
Chill for several hours.
Makes from 4 to 6 servings.

title: coca-cola chicken
directions: Put chicken in skillet. Pour cola and barbecue sauce over chicken. Let come to rolling boil; lower heat and simmer until chicken is done, about 1 hour.

title: chocolate butter frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl. Whip until icing is smooth.

title: artichoke and rice salad
directions: Cook rice as directed (omit butter).
Cool in bowl.
Add onions, peppers and olives.
Mix some of the artichoke liquid (about the amount in one 3-ounce jar) with the mayonnaise and curry powder.
Add mayonnaise and artichokes.
Toss well.
Chill and serve.
Serve 6. It can be made the night before.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix and bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown and season hamburger.
Add rest of ingredients and bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Add Season-All salt, according to taste preference, to boiling water.
Add chicken.
Boil until tender, approximately 45 minutes. Add rice.
Follow directions on rice box.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together flour, soda and salt; add to fruit cocktail, sugar and slightly beaten eggs.
Pour into greased and floured baking dish (preferably a glass dish).
Sprinkle over batter 1 cup brown sugar and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Bake 35 or 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Scramble beaten eggs in butter and set aside.
In a large skillet, heat cooking oil and stir in sliced scallions and cooked rice; stir quickly to coat rice with oil.
Mix in the soy sauce, sugar and cooked ham.
Stir in scrambled eggs, which have been cut into small pieces.
Heat for about 5 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: biscuits - low cholesterol
directions: Measure flour and baking powder into 1-quart bowl.
Measure 1/3 cup liquid oil into 1-cup measure; 2/3 cup milk will then just fill the 1-cup measure.
Pour into center of flour.
Mix as little as possible until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn onto floured bread board.
Press out to about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with cutter. Bake on ungreased baking sheet in preheated 425° oven for about 10 to 12 minutes, longer if more browning is desired or if large cutter was used.
Yield:
16 or more biscuits.
Serve hot.

title: tequila shrimp
directions: Mix together 3/4 cup tequila, lime juice, oil, pinch of cilantro, 4 garlic cloves, pinch of chilies, sugar, salt, pepper and cumin. Place shrimp in mixture; marinate at least 1 hour. Drain, reserve marinade.

title: pineapple strata
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, eggs and milk in bowl; mix well. Stir in pineapple.
Cut bread into cubes.
Layer half the bread and half the pineapple mixture in greased 2-quart casserole. Repeat layers.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Chill, covered, for 12 hours to overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown and bubbly.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: praline coffee cake
directions: Blend brown sugar, 3/4 cup flour and cinnamon.
Cut in 1/2 cup butter until crumbly.
Stir in pecans; set aside.
Sift 3 cups flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir lemon juice into evaporated milk.
Cream 1/2 cup butter and 3/4 cup sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition. Add flour and milk alternately; beat well after each addition. Fold in raisins and spread about 1/3 of praline mix into bottom of well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Cover with half of batter mix. Sprinkle remaining praline mix over batter and press gently.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Let stand in pan 10 minutes before removing.

title: dutch oven pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Blend ingredients thoroughly in a blender (except for butter).
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in large cast-iron skillet.
Pour in batter and bake in hot oven until puffed and brown, about 25 minutes.
It will rise up like a giant popover.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or serve with fruit and whipped cream.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour the boiling water over the quick oats, stir and let stand for 20 minutes.
Cream together the shortening, brown sugar, white sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and eggs.
Add this to the oatmeal mixture.
Stir together and bake for 35 minutes at 375 degrees. This is an old fashioned cake, from before the time of electric mixers, please mix by hand.

title: basmati rice pilaf with peas(matar pulao; serves 8)
directions: Spray a large casserole with nonstick vegetable spray.

title: mama woodard's chili sauce
directions: Chop and peel tomatoes and onions.
Chop and add peppers. Combine remaining ingredients (except vinegar).
Add and bring the mixture to boiling.
Cook to desired consistency, about 2 hours. Add vinegar and boil a few minutes longer.
Put in jars and seal.

title: sour cream and dill chicken
directions: Place chicken in single layer in a 13 x 9 x 2 pan. Sprinkle with pepper. Combine soup, soup mix, sour cream, lemon juice, dill and mushrooms. Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake, uncovered, 1 hour or until tender. Serve over buttered noodles.

title: pee salad
directions: Heat pan of water to boiling with salt.
When it's boiling put noodles in and stir until cooked.
Drain noodles when cooked in cold water.
Cook juices from cans with sugar, flour and eggs until thick.
Refrigerate overnight.
Put fruit, noodles and Cool Whip all together and serve.

title: ruby raspberry jello
directions: Prepare jello with boiling water and add applesauce and raspberries.
Chill.
Cut in squares.
Serve on lettuce leaves. Top with softened cream cheese.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Add all ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: pepper cabbage
directions: Dice pepper (use red and green for more color).
Grate cabbage.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Let set overnight for best taste.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and bell pepper with garlic salt, pepper and chili powder.
Add soup, tomatoes and milk.
Place Doritos in bottom of casserole dish; pour meat mixture over Doritos.
Top with cheese.
Bake in preheated 375° oven 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: nuteena casserole
directions: Saute the first 5 ingredients until soft.
Add Nuteena.
Stir in the soy sauce, lima beans and white sauce or mushroom gravy. Pour into
casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs or cracker crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: court's cooler
directions: Mix everything together, adding sherbet last.
Mix with an eggbeater/hand mixer.
Pour and enjoy!

title: chicken and rice surprise
directions: Prepare rice.
Combine rice, chicken, cream of chicken soup, mushroom soup, sliced water chestnuts, celery, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: easy, delicious cheesecake
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs, melted butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Pour into lightly greased spring-form pan (9-inch size). Reserve 5 tablespoons for topping.

title: cherry berry fruit mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cold water.
Chill until set.
Fold in cranberry sauce and apple.
Pour into oiled mold and chill.

title: sourdough bread without starter
directions: Use leftover biscuit dough or you can use canned biscuits. Roll dough thin to the size of Pyrex or casserole dish you are using.
Put sugar, cocoa and butter on dough.
The amounts vary, depending on amount of dough being used.
Fold ends over to meet in center of dough.

title: crock-pot chicken and stuffing
directions: Place chicken on bottom of crock-pot. Pour broth over the chicken.

title: hamburger-vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef and onions in large saucepan. Stir while browning. Add other ingredients.
Simmer until done.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in tight container. When serving, use two heaping teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: strawberry pound cake
directions: Mix margarine, Crisco and sugar well.
Add eggs, mixing until smooth.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, strawberries and juice. Beat until smooth; add vanilla.
Start with a cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour to 1 1/2 until golden brown.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix salt, pepper and onions.
Mix soup, sour cream and grated cheese.
Mix together and add hash browns.
Place in a 3-quart or rectangular casserole dish.
Melt margarine and mix with corn flakes.
Put on top of casserole last 20 minutes of baking time. Bake a total of 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Parboil onion and zucchini for 5 minutes.
Mix together sour cream, grated carrots and soup.
Fold in zucchini and onion mixture.
Melt butter and pour over stuffing.
Put half of stuffing on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour on all of zucchini mixture and top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: mexican relish
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pepper to taste.
Chill and serve with Fritos for dipping.

title: barley vegetable soup
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Prepare all veggies for the soup. Mix all together; cook about 30 minutes after it comes to a boil or until veggies are tender.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Blend well and use with any kind of fresh fruit.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together the crackers and melted oleo.
Line a greased casserole dish with half the butter crumb mixture.
Clean and chop the broccoli.
Cook until tender in salted water (for frozen broccoli cook according to directions); drain.
Put a layer of broccoli over crumb mixture.
Put a thin layer of Velveeta cheese slices over broccoli, another layer of broccoli, another layer of cheese.
Top all with remaining crumbs and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Brown beef in skillet; add onion and cook until clear.
Add tomato sauce and tomatoes; stir and add macaroni.
Cook until macaroni is tender.
Add cheese; stir and serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chili burger supper
directions: Cook macaroni or spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
Brown ground beef in skillet.
Add the chili-beef soup, tomato soup and cooked macaroni.
Heat, stirring occasionally, for 5 to 7 minutes or until mixture bubbles.
Halve the cheese slices diagonally and overlap cheese triangles atop hot mixture.
Cover for a few minutes to melt cheese slightly.
Serve at once.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: veal marengo
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons butter or margarine and oil in heavy saucepan or Dutch oven over medium heat.
Brown veal on all sides, in several batches, removing meat as it browns.
Add onion and garlic to fat left in pan.
Cook 1 minute.
Sprinkle with flour. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Return meat to pan.
Add wine, chicken broth, tomato sauce, bay leaf and thyme.
Cover.
Bring to boiling.
Lower heat.
Simmer 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter or margarine in skillet over medium heat. Saute mushrooms until tender, stirring or tossing occasionally. Remove from skillet; reserve.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter or margarine in same skillet; add onion and saute until glazed a golden brown.
Add mushrooms, onion and olives to veal five minutes before meat is cooked.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Transfer meat and vegetables to serving dish with slotted spoon.
Keep warm.
Bring sauce to boiling.
Simmer 5 minutes, skimming fat as it comes to surface.
Correct seasoning with salt and pepper.
Strain sauce over meat and vegetables.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Garnish with toast points, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grandma's applesauce cake(not your "usual" highly-spiced applesauce cake.)
directions: Boil to "soft boil" on candy thermometer.
Beat and frost cake.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Put chicken in large baking dish.
Mix other ingredients. Pour over chicken.
Marinate overnight.
When ready to use, bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can use chicken breasts.

title: rocky road squares
directions: Mix chips, butter and milk in double boiler.
Pour over peanuts and marshmallows.
Pour on waxed paper in baking dish. Refrigerate for 2 hours or overnight.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients (except for sugar and oil), and mix well.
In small bowl mix sugar and oil together and then pour over vegetables and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 8 hours.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Mix pineapple juice, soy sauce, chicken stock, garlic, parsley and pepper.
Marinate chicken breasts 3 to 4 hours or overnight. Grill chicken breasts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mallow fruit dip
directions: Gradually add Marshmallow Creme to softened cream cheese.
Mix until well blended.
Add orange rind and ginger.
Whip until fluffy.
Serve with fresh fruit such as strawberries, apple wedges, bananas and grapes.

title: mama's old time tea cakes
directions: Sift flour in bowl (make hole in flour and mix like biscuits). Roll on floured board and cut out cookies.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until done, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: holiday fudge
directions: Combine butter, evaporated milk, sugar and salt in saucepan over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Bring to full boil.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir vigorously until marshmallows melt and blend.
Pour into 8-inch square buttered pan.
Cool until semi-firm.
Lightly score fudge into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Gently press maraschino cherries and walnuts on top.
Cut in squares after fudge has cooled completely.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs and flour alternately. Add cream and vanilla. Put into tube pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
This makes a large cake.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Mix pie filling, sugar and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add Jell-O; mix well.
Remove from heat and add Coke.
Mix well and add pineapple.
Pour into mold and chill until set.

title: veggie dip
directions: Combine all ingredients until smooth.
Serve in shell of green or red bell pepper with seeds removed.
Wonderful dip for fresh vegetables.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Sprinkle half the cake mix in a cake pan.
Add canned fruit, including juice.
Sprinkle remaining cake mix on top.
Dot with butter and bake at 350 degrees until done.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and beat about 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: herbed focaccia bread
directions: Brush 15 X 10 jellyroll pan with 1 Tbsp. olive oil, set aside. Turn bread dough out onto lightly floured surface, and knead 3 to 4 times or until smooth.
Stir together margarine, 3/4 Tbsp. rosemary and dill, and parmesan cheese. gradually knead mixture into bread dough until dough is smooth; and elastic, adding additional flour if necessary.
Press dough evenly into prepared pan. using fingertips, press small indentations in top of dough; sprinkle with garlic, rosemary, and dill.
Drizzle with remaining 3 Tbsp. oil, sprinkle with kosher salt, if desired and pepper.
Cover and let rise in a warm place, free from drafts, 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 400 degrees for 20-25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: reese cups
directions: Break Hershey bars into small pieces.
Add 1/2 cup peanut butter and melt over very low heat.
In another pan, melt 3/4 cup peanut butter.

title: carrot relish
directions: Boil 1 hour and pack in jars and seal.

title: chocolate kiss peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate kisses.
Roll into small balls (about twice as big as a marble) and roll in white sugar. Cook at 350° for 10 minutes.
As soon as you remove from oven, put an unwrapped chocolate kiss in the center of each cookie.
Let cool on pan for a minute or two and remove to wax paper.
Let cool until chocolate kiss is set.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Mix and pour in buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cracker crumbs and cheese may be sprinkled on the top.

title: fruit salad cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Drain fruit salad; save juice. Add dry and wet ingredients together.
Whip.
Fold in fruit salad.
Pour in ungreased pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: turketti
directions: Saute bell pepper and onion in oil.
Cook spaghetti.
Mix all ingredients together and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: veal and mushrooms marsala
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge veal in flour.
Heat oil; add veal and cook on each side.
Drain on paper towels. Saute mushrooms and remove.
Saute green onions in 2 tablespoons oil.
Stir in tomatoes and basil.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes.
Add wine and simmer 8 minutes.
Return veal and mushrooms and heat through. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and parsley.

title: no boil, lower fat lasagne
directions: Brown meat in skillet. Pour just enough spaghetti sauce to cover the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add the rest to the browned meat with the water to heat on low.
Spread 1 layer of uncooked noodles with Ricotta. Add a layer of grated Mozzarella and then a layer of meat sauce.
Repeat until you have filled the baking dish.
Finish with a layer of noodles and a light covering of sauce.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil. Bake in a 400° oven for 1 hour.
Let set, uncovered, for 10 minutes before serving.

title: caramel marshmallows
directions: Heat and stir until smooth.
Insert a toothpick into marshmallows and dip in sauce.
Roll marshmallows in Rice Krispies cereal.
Set marshmallows in cupcake papers.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, cherries and oranges.
Set aside.
Use juice to cook the pudding.
Cook until pudding thickens.
Cool; pour over fruit.
Gee, it's really good.
(Beautiful.)

title: strawberry butter
directions: Drain juice from strawberries and mix all ingredients together well using a mixer. Store in the refrigerator in covered jar or container. Serve on toast, bread or biscuits.

title: egg roll
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly with mixer, except for the frozen green peas.
Heat small square electric skillet to 325°. Oil lightly.
Pour mixture into skillet until egg starts to firm. Sprinkle a few frozen green peas on top of egg mixture.
Starting closest to you, roll the egg away from you like a jelly roll, using 2 spatulas.
Cool slightly in pan to shape.
Place on cutting board.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.

title: sally's coconut impossible pie
directions: Beat all together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Needs no crust.
Check with blade of knife for doneness or when golden brown.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix flour, sugar, egg, vinegar and pineapple juice in small saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture is thick. Refrigerate until cold.
Add cold mixture to apples and pineapple. Fold in Cool Whip and 3/4 cup nuts.
Sprinkle remaining nuts on top.
Chill for several hours and enjoy.

title: tropical rum and champagne punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in large container.
Chill for 2 hours.
Place ice ring with gardenias in punch bowl and pour in chilled mixture.
Add chilled champagne and serve.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs quickly covered.
Let eggs stand in hot water off stove for 15 minutes,
Then run cold water over the eggs to cool them down.
Peel the eggs and cut lengthwise in half.
Scoop out yolk into a small bowl and mash with fork adding mayonnaise, salt, mustard, pepper, relish.
Mix well.
Put some mixture into the center of each egg half and sprinkle with paprika.
Refrigerate.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
