Pour into a 9-inch pie pan. Bake 20 minutes at 450°, then at 350° until knife inserted into pie comes out clean.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and cut up chicken.
Add broth and soup.
Mix well and pour into baking dish.
Melt margarine.
Add crushed crackers. Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Peel and chop tomatoes.
Cook over constant heat, stirring often, until thick, about 1 1/2 hours.
Add chopped onions and peppers, then rest of ingredients except tomato paste.
Cook 1 more hour or until onions and peppers are soft and sauce is right consistency.
Add tomato paste.
When sauce is bubbling, pour into hot cans and seal.
Makes approximately 14 to 16 pints.
Delicious also for spaghetti sauce or Sloppy Joes.

title: cooked cabbage
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and add 5 cups cabbage, carrots and onion.
Stir
and
add
water.
Cover
and	steam
to 5 minutes or	until moisture is gone.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and a dash
of pepper,
a	dash
of paprika and a small amount of mustard (optional) just before serving.

title: potato cake(from the 1909 coupeville cookbook)
directions: Beat sugar and butter very light; add spices.
Beat egg yolks; add.
Beat whites well; add.
Stir in chopped fruits and lastly the flour and whole raisins alternately.

title: grandmother's crustless egg pie(1940)
directions: Mix all ingredients well, but don't beat.
Grease pie pan and sprinkle with flour.
Turn upward; flour will fall off.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cranberry fluff
directions: Grind berries; add sugar and marshmallows. Mix, cover and chill overnight. Add apples, grapes, raisins and salt. Fold in whipped cream. Top with nuts in serving bowl. Cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: 6 weeks bran muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients and pour mixed liquid ingredients over.
Mix well.
Store in covered container in refrigerator. Bake as needed for breakfast or snacks at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: roladen
directions: Will also need toothpicks.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper.
Coat with pancake mix. Heat shortening in a large skillet. Brown chops well on both sides.
Remove to shallow baking pan.

title: fruit sparkles
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add beverage.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add fruit.
Pour into individual dessert dishes.
Chill until firm, about 1 hour.
Garnish with additional fruit and mint leaves, if desired.

title: green pepper steak
directions: In bowl, combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Add beef. Toss well.
Set aside.
Allow to marinate about 15 minutes.
In wok or large frying pan, heat oil.
Add beef with liquid.
Toss over high heat until browned; taste.
If not tender, simmer, covered, for about 30 minutes.
Turn up heat; add veggies.
Toss 10 minutes or until tender-crisp.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind and mix apples, cranberries and oranges.
Dissolve cherry jello in 1 cup cold water.
Combine gelatins, add sugar, nuts and fruit mixture.
Pour into a large mold or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill. Yield:
15 servings.

title: creamy cole slaw
directions: Blend well.
Pour over 1 head of chopped cabbage.

title: date nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over chopped dates.
Add butter or shortening, sugar and salt; mix well and let cool.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix; sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture. Add nuts and mix well.
Makes one large loaf or 2 small loaves; bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: shrimp or scallop stew
directions: Start with bacon drippings, onions and potatoes and add enough water to cover.
Cook until tender.
Add tomato soup, raw shrimp or scallops and season to taste and cook about 5 to 10 minutes, until seafood is done.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Combine caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in top of double boiler; stir until melted.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix well.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Place 3 tablespoons shortening in 9-inch black skillet.
When grease is hot, dust with thin layer of cornmeal on bottom and sides of skillet.
Pour in batter and cook until done.
Brown top with broiler.
Cooks in about 25 to 30 minutes.
Cornbread needs to go through sweat, so turn bread out of pan when it comes out of the oven.
Put bread back into skillet, bottom side up.
Let sit and cool.
Can be cooked in black 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Place cottage cheese in a large bowl.
Sprinkle dry gelatin over the top; stir until mixed.
Stir in whipped topping and marshmallows.
Gently fold in orange segments.
Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Season and brown meat with onions.
Add celery; simmer for 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: cherry winks
directions: Sift dry ingredients and set aside.
Combine shortening and sugar.
Cream well.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well. Blend in dry ingredients gradually.
Mix thoroughly.
Add nuts and dates.
Shape into balls, using 1 level tablespoon of dough per cookie.
Crush corn flakes.
Roll each ball into crushed flakes.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Top each cookie with 1/4 maraschino cherry.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together, make sure sugar is dissolved, then add Ginger ale.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in casserole baking dish.
Cut butter into pats and place over top of mixture.
Bake, uncovered, 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: make-ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender; drain.
Mash potatoes with remaining ingredients.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: gone all afternoon stew
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Put all ingredients into a large casserole with a lid to fit.
There is no need to brown meat first.
Mix ingredients together, cover tightly and bake for 5 hours.

title: autumn apple salad
directions: Heat crushed pineapple and sugar for 3 minutes, then add jello and stir well to dissolve. Add cream cheese which has been softened. Let cool. Add celery, apple, walnuts and Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: easy cream cheese clouds
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed in electric mixer, gradually adding heavy cream.
Mix well.
Whip until thickened, using the back of a spoon.
Shape into 10 (3 1/2-inch) shells; place on waxed paper lined cookie sheet.
Freeze two hours or overnight.
When ready to serve, fill with cherry pie filling. Sprinkle chopped nuts on top, if desired.
Substitute fruits, such as blueberry, strawberry, etc.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut the shortening into the flour and salt mixture until it resembles fine bread crumbs.
Combine slightly beaten egg with vinegar and water; sprinkle over dry ingredients.
Mix with fork. Makes 3 or 4 crusts.
Can refrigerate dough one week or freeze.

title: quick mix(for indian fry bread, sugar cookie, impossible pie)
directions: In a large bowl, mix in dry ingredients; blend well.
With pastry blender, cut in shortening until evenly distributed. Mixture will look like cornmeal in texture.
Put in large airtight container.
Label.
Store in cool dry place.
Use within 10 to 12 weeks.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces.
Pat dry with paper towels; set aside. Keep at room temperature for at least 1 hour before grilling.

title: mint julep
directions: To cold water, add sugar until it seems like oil.
Take your glass and crush mint with spoon all around inside of glass and its border.
Discard mint.
Fill glass with ice.
Add bourbon to taste.
Fill with sugar water.
Let stand until cool.
Don't stir.

title: french peas
directions: Melt butter in a small saucepan. Add all remaining ingredients. Cover and cook until the peas are tender, stirring occasionally. Yield: 2 servings.

title: tartar sauce
directions: In a small bowl mix all ingredients. Chill at least 30 minutes to blend flavors.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat the butter and sugars; add egg and vanilla.
Mix flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to butter mixture. Stir in oats.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes.

title: mixed vegetables
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions for 5 minutes. Put cauliflower in last as it gets mushy.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan or 3 to 4-quart casserole.
Heat undiluted soup and Cheez Whiz slowly.
Pour over vegetables. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Can sprinkle Durkee onion rings over top and bake 10 minutes more.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef. Drain. Peel and cube potatoes. Cover with water. Add chopped onion. Cook until tender (about 20 minutes). Add ground beef, canned vegetables (with liquid), and seasonings. I also add instant potato flakes to thicken.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease (not oil) bottom only of Bundt pan. In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Stir in sugar, zucchini, oil and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients, by hand; blend well. Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake at 325°
for 50 to 60 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top, if desired.

title: ratatouille
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease shallow earthenware or other casserole.
Slice zucchini and celery.
Cut onion and green pepper into large squares.
Cut eggplant into large cubes.
Scald tomatoes in boiling water for 60 seconds.
Drain, remove skin and cut in half.
Squeeze out and discard tomato juice and cut each half into 4 pieces.
Reserve.
Blanch separately in boiling salted water the zucchini, celery, green pepper and eggplant.
Reserve.

title: david's seafood linguine
directions: Melt butter in oil in wide frying pan.
Cook peppers, garlic and crushed red pepper for 1 minute.
Remove peppers.
Add broth and lemon juice; bring to boil.
Add scallops and shrimp; cook until opaque.
Add lobster.
Remove fish from pan.
Add cooked pasta to liquid mixture in pan until coated.
Transfer pasta and sauce to serving dish; top with fish mixture, peppers and parsley. Top with fresh lemon zest.
Serves 4.

title: chicken pinwheel casserole
directions: Mix butter and flour over medium heat.
Add salt, pepper and stock while stirring constantly.
Add evaporated milk; continue to stir until thickened.
Add chicken, carrots and peas.
Stir together and pour into baking dish.
Mix 1 1/2 cups flour and baking powder.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk; mix lightly with fork.
Roll out dough to a rectangle, 1/2-inch thick.
Spread cheese over dough.
Roll long side up, like a jelly roll.
Cut into pieces 3/4-inch thick.
Place on top of chicken mixture. Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: prella's cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and then add vinegar, oil, vanilla and water. Bake 350 degrees for 40 - 45 minutes.

title: pineapple pie(heritage recipe)
directions: Cook until thick and add 1 can pineapple cubes.
Pour in baked pie shell.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix and make into loaf in baking dish.

title: onion meatballs(6 servings)
directions: In a large bowl, combine beef with milk and 2 tablespoons of the onion soup mix.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into 24 meatballs. Place in a 3-quart oblong microproof baking dish.
Cover with waxed paper and cook on High (max power) for 3 minutes.
Turn meatballs over.
Cover and cook on High (max power) for 2 minutes. Remove meatballs.
Stir flour into drippings in dish.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups water, parsley and remaining soup mix.
Cook, uncovered, on 60 (Bake) for about 5 minutes, or until mixture comes to a boil.
Add meatballs.
Cover and cook on 60 (Bake) for 6 minutes, stirring occasionally during cooking time.
Gradually blend in sour cream.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: onion pretzels
directions: Put pretzels in oblong pan.
Sprinkle soup mix on top.
Pour melted butter over soup and pretzels and stir.
Bake at 250°. Stir after 15 minutes; bake 15 minutes more.

title: kaci's bean dip
directions: Mix well in a microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave until melted, stirring several times.
Put in fondue pot to stay hot.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Layer all in a 9 x 13-inch pan (vegetables).
Now sprinkle dry package of Italian dressing over this.
Last you pour a bottle of Italian dressing over all.

title: cucumber onion salad
directions: Peel and slice thinly cucumbers and onion.
Separate sliced onion into rings.
Place onion rings and cucumber slices in bowl. Cover with cold water.
Stir in about 1 tablespoon salt.
Allow to soak about 1 hour.
Drain off all water.
Add sour cream and salt and pepper to taste.
Stir gently to coat all of the cucumber and onion with sour cream.
Serve.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening; add sugar and salt.
Blend and cool.
Add eggs.
Let stand in cold water 5 minutes, then add to mixture.
Blend well.
Cover and refrigerate.
Make into rolls 1 or 2 hours before baking at 350° for 20 minutes.
Dough keeps 10 days in refrigerator.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix flour, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper together.
Dip chicken in eggs.
Roll chicken in flour mixture.
Put chicken on cookie sheet; pour melted margarine over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: kapusta
directions: In a large pot, melt 2 tablespoons of butter on medium-low heat.
Add onion and salt pork.
Saute until onion is light brown (do not burn).
Add cabbage; stir and cover.
Cook on low until cabbage starts to get limp.
Mix in sauerkraut.
Cook, covered, on low for an hour, stirring occasionally.
Add a cup of water if mixture starts to dry out.
Water may be added throughout cooking. Add kielbasa and cook for at least 2 hours on low.
The longer you cook it, the more flavorful it will be.
Add butter, salt and pepper to taste.

title: lemon custard cakes
directions: Coat six 6 ounce ramekins (6 ounce custard baking cups) with oil.
In small bowl, whisk egg yolks and milk.
In bowl with electric mixer, beat butter and sugar until combined well.
Beat in flour, lemon juice and zest with a pinch of salt.
Beat in yolk mixture well.

title: swiss biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a food processor, combine Swiss cheese, butter, flour, pepper and cayenne.
Process until well blended.
On a flat work surface, roll out dough 1/4 inch thick and cut into desired shapes.
Brush with beaten egg white and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Transfer to a baking sheet.
Bake until biscuits are lightly browned, about 15 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Wash rice until water is clear.
Cover rice with water; add butter.
Bring to boil for 20 minutes and set aside.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Melt the fat; fry the chopped onion.
Add the sauerkraut and cook for a few minutes.
Add the water and apple and cook until done.
Thicken the cooking liquid with the grated raw potato and cook briefly.
Season with salt.
Cooking time:
1 hour.

title: asparagus au gratin
directions: Cook asparagus by directions on package.
Add cheese and Worcestershire sauce to white sauce.
Place some asparagus on hot buttered toast.
Place one half deviled egg on either side of the asparagus; cover with cheese sauce.
Serves 5.

title: cream of peanut soup
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter; stir in flour.
Add chicken broth, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat and puree in blender.
Add peanut butter and cream.
Stir.
Return to low heat.
Serve with a sprinkling of chopped peanuts on top.

title: finger jello
directions: Mix Jell-O, sugar and water together; bring to the boiling stage, but do not boil.
Dissolve gelatin in 1 1/4 cups water in large bowl.
Add Jell-O mixture from pan and 1 1/4 cups more water.
Mix well; pour into a 7 x 12-inch jelly roll pan.
Chill, cut and peel off!

title: summer salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: medium white sauce
directions: Mix cornstarch and milk until smooth.
Add margarine, salt and black pepper.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil one minute.
Makes 1 cup.

title: strawberry deluxe
directions: Break cake into bite size pieces and place in dish.
Cream sour cream, cream cheese and softened Cool Whip.
Beat pudding and milk until smooth and thick.
Mix with cheese mixture and pour over cake.
Cover and refrigerate.
Partially thaw strawberries. Heat in juices very fast with food color and sugar to taste.
Add enough cornstarch mixed with water, when hot enough, to thicken to medium thickness.
Remove from heat immediately.
Completely cool. Pour over cake.
Keep refrigerated.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix together cake mix and sugar. Add sour cream, oil and eggs, one at a time. Mix well. Pour in a Bundt pan sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: linda pye's peach crunch
directions: Place peaches in baking dish and sprinkle with lemon juice. In separate bowl, mix butter, sugar and flour until crumbly. Spread over peaches. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Crumble up crackers; put in 9 x 13-inch pan along with melted oleo.
Mix well; pat out smooth.
Put into 350° oven for 5 minutes. Remove and let cool.
Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions and set aside.
Beat cream cheese and sugar, add 1 tablespoon milk if too thick.
Fold in Dream Whip until well blended.
Spoon over crumb crust.
Chill.
Spread pie filling over top.
Serve.

title: caramel walnut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar and egg. Cut in 1/2 cup margarine until crumbly.
Stir in walnuts. Reserving 2 cups crumb mixture, press remainder firmly on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake 15 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, salt, milk, water and vanilla. Mix well. Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake 10 minutes at 420°; reduce heat to 350° and bake 25 minutes.

title: hot rolls
directions: Empty yeast into pint container add ward water.
Let set while mixing and scalding the milk, sugar, salt and oleo.

Pour into large mixing bowl and let cool to warm temperature. Add the beaten eggs and yeast and gradually stir in flour. Brush with oil and oleo and let rise till double in size. Punch down and work in extra flour, empty on flour board and work down, pinch off into balls and place on greased baking dish. Let rise again till double in size. Bake at 375°.

title: butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In a medium saucepan melt morsels and butter.
Stir in crumbs and nuts.
Press half the mixture firmly into bottom of baking dish.
In a large mixing bowl, beat cheese until fluffy; beat in condensed milk, vanilla and egg.
Mix well. Pour over crumb mixture and top with remaining crumb mixture. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool to room temperature.
Chill before cutting into bars.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Yield:
24 bars.

title: scripture cake
directions: Follow Solomon's advice for making good boys and you will have a good cake.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour over butter.
Add peaches.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli, ham and cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook broccoli; drain and spread in ungreased 9 x 13 casserole. Layer ham, then cheese. Beat remaining ingredients together and pour over casserole. Bake 1 hour until knife comes out clean. Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Cut wings, rinse and dry.
Sprinkle with salt.
Heat oil in large saucepan to 375° on deep fry thermometer.
Roll wings in cornstarch, then dip in egg to coat evenly.
Deep fry 3 or 4 at a time until golden brown, about 5 minutes.
Drain.
Place in shallow baking pan.

title: sweet carrots
directions: Peel and cut carrots into 1-inch pieces.
Place in saucepan of water.
Cook until almost tender.
Pour off water.
Add butter and sugar to carrots.
Place over medium heat.
Stir constantly until carrots are glazed.
Serve immediately.

title: cowboy's lunch
directions: Make a hamburger patty and place it on foil.
Cut up potato, carrots

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter and saute shallots until transparent.
Add rice and garlic and cook, stirring, about 5 minutes. Don't brown.
Add boiling chicken stock.
Cover and cook over low heat for 15 to 18 minutes. Serves 2 to 3.

title: chinese chicken fingers
directions: Mix ginger, garlic powder and soy sauce in a 1 gallon zip lock bag, shake well. add chicken and marinate at least one hour in refrigerator. In a shallow pan combine rice crispies and sesame seeds. Remove chicken from marinade, coat in rice crispy mixture. Place on foil lined cookie sheet that has been coated with vegetable spray. Bake at 400 for 10-15 minutes or until chicken is tender. Do not cover when baking. Serves well with sweet and sour or hot mustard sauce. Serves 6-8.

title: yummy banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, milk, flour and dry ingredients.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Add bananas, nuts and vanilla. Beat and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: quick candy
directions: Mix sugar and syrup and bring to boil.
Add peanuts and stir until creamy.
Add corn flakes and stir.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.

title: creamy brown rice
directions: Mix together.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cinnamon blueberry jam
directions: Crush blueberries; measure 2 1/2 cups and place in a large kettle.
Add the sugar, lemon juice, cinnamon and cloves; bring to a full rolling boil.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from the heat; stir in pectin.
Skim off foam.
Pour hot into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Adjust caps.
Process 15 minutes in a boiling water bath.
Yields 4 half-pints.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Bring to boil 2 cans of chicken broth.
Combine sugar, nutmeg and pepper.
Add to pumpkin, mixing well.
Slowly add pumpkin mixture to hot broth and bring just to a boil, stirring constantly.
Enjoy!
Hearty and flavorful!
Serves 4 or 5.

title: jon's prize winning gringo chile
directions: Brown hamburger, but do not strain. Add all ingredients and bring to a boil slowly, then cover and let simmer for as long as possible.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Sprinkle the grated cheese on top of mixture.
Top with the crushed crackers, mixed with the margarine.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: meat loaf with sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, mix well.
Place in a greased loaf pan.

title: tasty veggie spirelli salad
directions: Combine onion and vinegar and let it stand a few minutes.
Add mayonnaise, salt, pepper and paprika.
Mix well.
Mix the veggie spirelli, tomatoes, green pepper and olives in a large salad bowl. Pour mayonnaise mixture over all.
Toss lightly.
Chill several hours before serving.
Garnish with egg slices and parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pie crust for fried pies
directions: In large bowl, cut Crisco into the flour after salt and baking powder mixed with it.
Add milk and mix until you can form ball. Pinch off amounts to make size pies desired.
I usually make 13 to 15 pies.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Take off heat and add sugar, dates, nuts and eggs; mix.
Reheat until it boils and add 1/3 of the coconut, vanilla and Rice Krispies.
Mix and drop by spoonful into the rest of coconut and roll into balls.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter biscuits and roll in sugar and cinnamon.
Boil remaining ingredients for 1 minute.
Put quartered biscuits in greased Bundt pan.
Pour liquid over biscuits and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Line an oblong cake pan with apple slices.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over apples.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: chocolate chip torte(cookie)
directions: Sift flour, cocoa and salt.
Mix dates, boiling water and soda.
Cool.
Cream the butter and shortening.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs.
Alternately add flour and date mixture, blending well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 1/2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts and chips.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 25 minutes or until done.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: mr. hendrickson's favorite coconut cake
directions: Add the 2/3 package coconut and 1 teaspoon coconut flavoring to the cake mix.
Bake as directed until done.
Take from oven and punch holes in cake.
Mix the sugar, coconut flavoring and evaporated milk with water until you have 2 cups.
Spoon over cake and cool.
Frost with the Cool Whip.
Cover.
Add remaining coconut.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: rolled dumplings
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk to make a stiff dough.
Roll out to about 1/8 inch thickness and cut into 1-inch squares, 1 to 1 1/2-inch strips or diamonds. Sprinkle lightly with flour and drop into boiling ham broth.
Cover loosely and boil gently for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: annie's chocolate cream pie
directions: Melt chocolate bar in top of double boiler.
Stir in milk and marshmallows.
When smooth, remove from heat.
Let cool.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.
Top with whipped cream.
Serve.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine crumbs and 1/2 cup oleo in bowl; mix well.
Spread and pat mixture into bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch shallow baking dish. Drizzle chocolate syrup over crumbs.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour.

title: herbed rice
directions: Mix all ingredients, except margarine, in a greased casserole. Top with margarine, cover and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Stir when half done.
Do not overcook, will be too dry.

title: crab and cheese appetizer
directions: Mix together all ingredients and spread on 6 split English muffins, cut into 4 sections each or fingers.
Bake at 425° for a few minutes.
Can freeze ahead.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix jello as directed and congeal. Whip Dream Whip and fold in nuts, coconut and jello.
Fold in strawberries.

title: date bars
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and vanilla; cream.
Add dry ingredients.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Check often until light brown.
Remove from the oven.
Cut into squares while still warm, rolling in powdered sugar.
Serve.

title: crab stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until tender. When cool enough to handle, halve potatoes lengthwise.
Carefully scoop out pulp into a bowl, leaving a thin shell.
Set shells aside.
Beat or mash potato pulp with butter, cream, salt and pepper until smooth.
Using a fork, stir in onions or chives and cheese.
Gently mix in crab.
Stuff potatoes shells; sprinkle with paprika.
Return to oven for 15 minutes or until heated through. Serves 8.

title: veal with mustard sauce
directions: Place veal on a flat surface and pound thin.
Blend flour with salt and pepper.
Dredge veal on both sides.
Heat the butter in a large skillet until it is quite hot, but not brown.
Add veal (they shrink as they cook). Cook until golden, about 1 minute on each side. Remove the veal to a warm dish and keep warm by covering the dish with foil.

Add shallots to the skillet and cook briefly, stirring. Add wine and cook, stirring until it is almost totally evaporated. Add the cream and let boil up, stirring. Cook about 1/2 minute and turn off heat. Stir in mustard. Do not cook further. Spoon sauce over meat. Serve with thin buttered noodles. Serves 3 to 4 people.

title: fresh strawberry ice cream
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt at high speed until thick and frothy, about 5 minutes.
Turn mixer to low and add Pet milk.
Beat well.
Remove mixer beaters and add strawberries by hand.
Place dasher in churn and pour mixture in gallon churn.
Add milk to within 3 inches of churn top.
Stir mix with dasher and place on top of churn.
Freeze as directions given for freezer used.
Makes one gallon.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Stir until well blended.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: apple cuts
directions: Mix like pie crust. Divide into 2 crusts and roll on cookie sheet.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Arrange broccoli.
Pour rice over broccoli.
Mix milk and soup.
Pour over broccoli and rice.
Pour Cheez Whiz over this mixture.
Top with mushrooms. Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk cornbread
directions: Mix cornbread, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar. Add buttermilk, eggs and fat or oil.
Beat well.
Fill a greased baking pan half full.
Bake at 475° (hot oven) for about 20 minutes until browned.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Saute onion in butter; add mustard,
Worcestershire sauce and poppy seed.
Refrigerate until spreading consistency.

title: chicken in wine
directions: Shake chicken, flour and seasonings in a bag.
Brown chicken in oil. Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Pour in wine. Add a little water. Cover and simmer until tender, about 45
minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 24 individual muffin cups.
In a large mixing bowl, sift the flour with the baking powder and salt. Add the Crisco.
Rub the mixture together.
Add milk; stir with fork until soft dough forms.
Turn dough on floured cutting board and knead a few times.
Divide dough in half.
Roll out half of the dough into a long rectangle about 1/8-inch thick.
Spread the dough with soft butter and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar (and raisins and nuts if desired).
Roll up dough, jelly roll style, and pinch the ends.
Cut into 12 pieces.
Place each piece into a greased muffin cup.
Repeat this procedure with the other half of the dough.
Bake the rolls for about 15 minutes.
Cool in pans for 5 minutes, then turn out onto wire racks.
Serve warm, with butter if desired.

title: easy german chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake slightly longer than directed on box.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: german hot potato salad
directions: In skillet, fry bacon until crispy.
Pour off all but 1/4 cup of drippings.
In drippings stir in onions, vinegar, sugar and pepper.
Cook and stir over low heat until mixture simmers.
Pour over potatoes and toss to combine.
Garnish with crumbled bacon. Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain well. Transfer to a large mixing bowl.
Meanwhile, saute onion in butter and salt until tender.
Remove onion with slotted spoon and add to broccoli with cream cheese and soup.
Mix well and transfer to greased casserole.
Add crushed crackers to remaining butter until well coated and top casserole.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 45 minutes.

title: mandarin sherbet salad
directions: Prepare jello according to directions on package.
Let sherbet soften at room temperature and mix with jello.
Add drained orange slices to mixture and pour into mold.
Refrigerate until set.

title: chickpea salad
directions: Simply mix all ingredients.
Chill and serve.
May be prepared a day in advance.
Great for a colorful holiday side dish or a summer salad.

title: chicken cerise
directions: Season chicken with paprika and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Saute chicken in butter until brown.
Remove chicken.
Blend flour, sugar, spices and 1/2 teaspoon salt in butter remaining in skillet.
Drain cherries and pour the liquid into the skillet. Return chicken to skillet.
Add pineapple, rum, bouillon cube and food coloring.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add cherries and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: carrot jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed on package and set aside.
Add carrots and pineapple to Jell-O.
Pour into salad bowl and chill until firm, then serve.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken and let cool. Take meat off bones. Cook onion, celery and bell pepper in margarine until done, but not brown. Blend in flour, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Add 2 or 3 cups chicken broth and milk. Cook over low heat until thick enough for a sauce, then add vegetables and pimientos.
Place chicken in bottom of baking dish. Slice eggs over chicken.
Pour sauce over that.
Place biscuits on top. Brush with margarine.
Bake at 400° until biscuits are brown.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake according to direction on cake box.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms, celery, onions and green peppers in 2 tablespoons butter or oleo until soft but not brown.
Add pimento and soup.
Mix well.
Add shrimp, crabmeat and cooked rice.
Mix well.
Stir in milk.
Heat in 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add milk, beaten eggs, flour, salt and melted chocolate.
Then add nuts and vanilla.
Blend thoroughly and spread 1/4 inch deep in a shallow greased pan. Bake about 15 minutes in a moderate oven.
Cut into squares while still warm.

title: electric skillet fried chicken
directions: Preheat electric skillet to 260°.
Add margarine and let melt completely.
(For extra crispy chicken, cook at 300° but watch closely.)
Meanwhile, prepare chicken, wash and cut up.
Salt and pepper chicken to taste as usual; flour parts.
Drop chicken into hot margarine.
Cover with lid, making sure vent is closed.
Let cook 15 to 20 minutes until brown on one side and turn.
Cook, covered, 20 minutes or more until done.

title: pork chops with rice
directions: Add uncooked rice into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Brown onion and green pepper in a small amount of butter in saucepan.
Then put over rice.
Brown chops in same pan as onion and place over pepper and onions.
Add brown sugar to drippings and enough water to dissolve.
Pour over chops.
Pour 1 cup of water over chops and tomato sauce.
Sprinkle salt over top of sauce.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for 15 minutes longer.
Serves 4.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring to a boil and cook 1 minute.

title: perfect tuna casserole
directions: In 1-quart casserole, blend soup and milk.
Stir in tuna, eggs and peas.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot; stir.
Top with chips.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: tomato soup
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter until tender. Blend in flour until smooth. Add remaining ingredients and stir over medium heat until slightly thickened. Reduce heat and cook slowly for additional 15 minutes.

title: italian stew sensation(serves 8)
directions: In a Dutch oven, add oil and butter.
Dredge beef cubes in flour and salt; brown on all sides.
Remove from pan.
Add olive oil and onions to pan drippings in Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat about 5 minutes, until onions are translucent.
Add tomatoes and Vermouth; stir, scraping up browned bits.
Add beef cubes to pan.
Add basil, bay leaf, garlic, and if necessary, enough hot water to cover meat, about 1-inch.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, about 1 1/2 hours, until meat is tender.
Add peppers; cook and simmer another 15 minutes.
Discard bay leaf and season with salt and pepper.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook ground steak, onion, pepper and celery in margarine until meat turns gray. Add tomato soup, mushrooms, salt and pepper. Simmer until heated.
Put a small amount of sauce in bottom of 2 1/2-quart casserole. Alternate layers of cooked spaghetti, meat sauce and shredded cheese, making 2 layers.
Top with mushroom soup.
Cover and bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until bubbly. Place sliced olives on top after baking.

title: brownie like chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl except hot water.
Then alternate mix and hot water.
Mix for 2 minutes.
Batter will be very thin. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out of center clean.

title: dijon pork chops
directions: Mix together mustard and salad dressing.
Coat chops with this mixture and sprinkle with pepper.
Cover and cook in a skillet on medium-low heat for 20 minutes.
Turn and add onions around chops. Cover and cook 5 to 10 minutes more.
Serve topped with onions and pan juices.

title: chicken stuffed shells
directions: Prepare all of the ingredients separately.
Mix together cut-up chicken, Stove Top stuffing and mayonnaise.
Stuff cooked shells with this mixture.

title: barbecue sauce for beef
directions: Cook together until thickened.
Good used on leftover roast beef and heated in oven
30 to 45 minutes.
Also as a steak sauce. Keeps in refrigerator a long time.

title: jewell one pot dinner
directions: Brown ground beef and drain; add other ingredients.
In crock-pot or slow cooker, cook on high for 1 hour, then cook on slow heat for 4 to 6 hours.

title: ice cream sandwiches
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg, shortening, butter, vanilla and 1/2 of the cake mix until smooth.
Then stir in remaining cake mix until smooth.
Roll dough out and cut in any desired shape or square.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pea picking cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Pour into three 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Let cool.
Mix pineapple, sugar and Cool Whip together well.
Put on cooled cake.

title: crock of gold
directions: Combine half butter with celery, onion, mushrooms and parsley; saute.
When onion and celery are transparent (not brown) add milk, cream and desired amount of seasonings.
Heat to warm temperature.

title: my best chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round pans. In large bowl, combine all the dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk, oil, vanilla and almond.
Beat on medium speed for 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in boiling water; it will be thin.
Pour into pans and bake 30 to 35 minutes. Cool and frost with favorite icing.

title: sweet 'n' sour chicken
directions: Boil all ingredients except chicken 2 to 3 minutes.
Add chicken pieces, small.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over hot rice, noodles or Chinese noodles.
Expect compliments!

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Peel and core tomatoes; place in a large pot. Peel and finely chop onions. Finely chop bell peppers and hot peppers, then add spices, sugar and vinegar. Stir ingredients thoroughly. Cook until thick. Stir often to keep from sticking. It will take about 3 hours to cook down. Pour in jars and seal.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Stir in pineapple.
Fold in bread cubes.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart greased casserole pan.
Bake uncovered 1 hour at 350°.
Serves approximately 10 to 12.

title: sausage & potato casserole
directions: Melt cheez whiz, sour cream and Velveeta in milk.
Add parsley, sausage, salt and pepper.
Pour this mixture over potatoes and onion flakes.
Bake at 350 degrees until cheese melts and is bubbly.

title: strawberry pineapple jello mold salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water and gelatine.
Add crushed pineapple, strawberries juice and all.
Pour half of this mixture into 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish putting the reserve aside.
Refrigerate mixture in pan until firm (about 30 minutes).
Remove from refrigerator.
Spread sour cream onto firm mixture evenly with rubber spatula.
Add remaining reserve.

title: mexican rice
directions: In large skillet, brown onion and bell pepper until tender; add ground beef and brown, then drain grease.
In same skillet, add cooked rice.
Sprinkle chili powder (about 3 tablespoons); salt and pepper to taste.

title: clam chowder
directions: Drain liquid from clams and add water to make 3 cups.
Crumble crackers into milk to soak.
Cook finely diced salt pork in large kettle until crisp and golden.
Remove and drain; pour off all but 2 tablespoons drippings.
Add onion and cook gently until soft. Add clam liquid, potato, salt and pepper.
Simmer until potato is tender, about 15 minutes.
Stir in milk, clams and butter, cut in bits.
Heat very slowly until soup is hot and flavors well blended, but do not boil.
Add salt pork bits and ladle into warm bowls.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar and allow to cool slightly.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add sifted flour, powdered sugar and salt.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into a jelly roll pan, spreading the dough out.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: one step cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch round pie plate.
Put the first 5 ingredients into blender.
Cover and blend on high 15 seconds.
Add cream cheese, cut in 1/2-inch squares and softened. Cover and blend on high 2 minutes.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes until center is firm.
Cool.
Spread on your favorite fruit topping or cheesecake topping (mix remaining ingredients). Enjoy!

title: crepes
directions: Combine egg, milk and flour.
Beat with a whisk.
Melt butter in frying pan and pour batter, using 1/4 cup for each crepe into pan.
When finished, fill crepe with jelly.
Roll it up and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Enjoy!

title: orange candy slice cake
directions: Cut up candy slices and dates.
Add 1/2 cup of the flour. Toss to keep from sticking together.
Add nuts and coconut; mix well.
Cream butter.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Combine soda with buttermilk.
Add alternately with flour; blend well.
Add candy mixture.

title: hamburger and noodle bake
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Cook noodles and drain.
Melt cheese in milk, but do not cook.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hurry up yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Combine biscuit mix and sugar.
Gradually add to yeast mixture.
Stir well.
Turn onto floured board and knead until smooth (10 minutes).
Roll dough into 12-inch circle.
Cut into 12 wedges. Roll up, beginning at wide end.
Place on greased baking sheet point side down.
Cover and let rise in warm place for 1 hour or until double in bulk.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12.

title: butterscotch delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, margarine and 1/2 cup pecans and spread on bottom of pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix pudding, milk and vanilla until thick.
Spread over previous layers.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with 1/2 cup pecans.
Chill and serve.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored.
Cream with sugar, adding milk and dry ingredients, stirring as little as possible.
Use a heavy wax paper to line bottom of large, shallow pan.
Bake at 350° until brown around the edges.
Sprinkle a towel with sugar to take it up on.
Hurriedly, trim the brown edges off and spread with jelly. Roll at once and keep rolled in towel as you eat it.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Put all together in a plastic bag and shake very well to coat all.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 450° for about 40 minutes, until tender and golden brown, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with parsley and enjoy.

title: jalapeno relish dip
directions: Combine in blender or mix with electric mixer.
Serve with Doritos.

title: baked aunt bill's fudge
directions: In large Dutch oven, combine the first 4 ingredients.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours and 15 minutes.
Stir in oven several times during cooking time.
Cook to firm ball stage.
Let cool 1 hour.
Beat with electric mixer for approximately 10 minutes.
Add nuts and vanilla; pour into buttered pan.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix together 2 sticks margarine, 1/2 cup powdered sugar and 2 cups flour.
Spread evenly on ungreased cookie pan which has sides.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Beat eggs; mix remaining ingredients and pour into cooked pastry.
Bake again at 325° for 20 minutes or until browned.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over top.

title: coney island hamburgers
directions: Brown 6 to 8 hamburgers; put in casserole or let in pan. Cover with sliced onion and pour sauce over top.
Either cover and simmer or bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Place sherbet and ice cream in bowl; over this pour lemonade and orange juice that have been diluted in water.
Stir to break up and slightly melt ice cream and sherbet.
Add ginger ale last.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients, stirring until thick; let cool. Slice bananas in pie shell.
Add vanilla to custard and pour over bananas.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Add 4 tablespoons sugar.
Put on top of pie and brown in hot oven.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and corn meal; toss lightly.
Add remaining ingredients in this:
eggs, margarine, lemon rind, milk, lemon juice, lemon flavoring and salt.
Beat with mixer until smooth and thoroughly blended.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Lower heat to 300°.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cinnamon sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and 1 1/2 cups sugar, then mix all ingredients except nuts and 2 teaspoons sugar together.
Cream well.
Put 1/2 of the batter in tube pan.
Mix nuts with cinnamon and 2 teaspoons sugar.
Then put 1/2 of the nut mixture on top of batter.
Pour in other half of batter and the rest of nut mixture on top.
Start in cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: takes two days to make macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain the macaroni.
Mix together the sugar, vinegar, oil and pepper well and pour over the macaroni.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and shortening over hot water.
Blend in sugar and eggs; add vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together, then add to chocolate mixture.
Mix well, but do not beat.
Add pecans.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichokes.
Coarsely chop artichokes.
Put artichokes, cheese and mayonnaise in a bowl and mix thoroughly.
Put mixture in a baking dish and bake in a 350°
oven for 20 minutes.

title: jello dessert
directions: Prepare jello as directed.
If canned fruit is used, the juice may be used as the cold water.
Add sliced strawberries.
Break angel food cake into medium sized chunks and place into jello mix, do not stir as cake turns to mush.
Chill to set.
Spoon into dessert dishes and top with whipped cream.
Easy and good!
Any fruit can be used with a complementary jello.

title: rave coconut cake
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients and bake in three 9-inch cake pans at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Put in greased baking pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: zesty lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven 359 degrees. Grease and flour 10 cup bundt i pan. Melt morsels in medium microwave safe bowl, for one minute. Microwave at additional 10 to 20 second intervals, stirring until smooth; cool slightly.

title: cracker fudge
directions: Boil milk and sugar together for three minutes.
Add vanilla, saltines and peanut butter. Mix well.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Use enough flour to make a stiff dough that you can handle. Bake at 350°.
Roll in 4x sugar.

title: butter balls(smor bullar)
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla well.
Add flour and nuts and form into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Roll into powdered sugar while warm.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix apples with sugar.
Add oil, nuts and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt into apple mixture.
Batter should adhere together.
Add water if moisture is needed.
Mix well and bake about 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with whipped topping or cream.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine in 2-quart casserole. Mix stuffing with margarine, saving some for topping.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: In large skillet, cook beef and drain.
Add salsa, Miracle Whip, corn and chili powder and mix well.
In 2-quart casserole dish, layer meat, chips, cheese.
Repeat this sequence.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Can top with lettuce and chopped tomatoes.

title: onion roasted taters
directions: Place all ingredients in large plastic bag. Shake until potatoes are evenly coated. Empty potatoes into baking pan.
Cook at 450° about 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Be sure to stir potatoes occasionally to keep from sticking.

title: jamaican corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat egg.
Melt margarine and mix both with milk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Beat/mix until well blended. Pour into greased 8 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: tex-mex chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine; add chicken soup, broth, chilies and onions.
Mix well.
Line buttered 9 x 12-inch casserole with Doritos.
Pour in chicken mixture; top with additional Doritos. Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or bubbly. Serves 8 to 10.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown hamburg and onion.
Add water and stir until mixture is fine in texture.
Add other ingredients and simmer about 3/4 hour. Makes about a quart.
Can be frozen.

title: clara's oatmeal fudge cookies
directions: Put sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in a saucepan.
Boil for 2 minutes, stirring frequently.
While still hot, pour over oatmeal mixture.
Mix well and let stand for 3 to 4 minutes.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Slice the potatoes and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Add butter to cover potatoes, not heavily, and spread mushroom soup over the top.
Cover and cook for 40 minutes at 350° with pan covered tightly.
Then add cheese on top and bake for an additional 10 to 15 minutes.
For a different taste add onions.

title: cherry fruit salad
directions: Mix together ingredients and put in serving bowl.
Put in refrigerator overnight or 6 hours at least.

title: molasses taffy(pull candy)
directions: Boil in heavy iron skillet the sugar, water, vinegar and molasses.
Stir frequently.
Add cream of tartar.
Cook until brittle testing in cold water.
Remove from heat; add butter, soda and vanilla.
Pour into buttered pan until cool, then butter hands and pull until you can't.
Twist and cut.

title: pheasant
directions: Remove feathers.
Skin and split the bird by cutting along the full length of the back bone with a sharp knife.
Spread open and clean out.
Cut breast bone in center and divide bird in halves. Wash bird in cold water and dry with a cloth.
Place in a dish and moisten with milk.
Let stand 1 1/2 hours or so.
Remove from milk and season with salt and pepper.
Add a few drops of lemon juice. Roll pieces in flour.
Fry slowly in butter (with some chopped onion) until golden brown.
Pour cream over it.
Add lemon juice. Cover pan tight and let simmer for 1/2 to 1 hour, depending upon tenderness of the bird.
Serve as a casserole.

title: burger bundles
directions: Prepare dressing according to directions.
Combine milk with meat.
Divide into 10 patties.
Place one spoonful of dressing in center of each patty.
Draw meat up over dressing and pinch to close.
Place in casserole.
Combine soup and other ingredients and pour over bundles.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water.
Dissolve and add 1 1/2 cups cold water.
Then add 1/2 can pineapple juice.
Mash bananas and add to Jell-O.
Also add pineapple.
Top with marshmallows. Let cool.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a casserole dish. Top with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle with oregano.
Bake in a covered casserole dish in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: "what's up doc?" cake
directions: Beat oil and eggs together.
Add flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; mix together.
Mix in carrots.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: layered tuna salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, green onion and mustard.
Set aside. Toss tuna with dill.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix together milk, juice and egg yolks.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Make meringue with egg whites beaten stiff with sugar. Top pie and bake at 325° for about 20 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: individual fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into balls about size of ping-pong balls. Cook on greased cookie sheet at 325° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from sheet while hot. Store in Tupperware or tummy! They better with age.

title: tuna casserole
directions: In large skillet, saute celery and onion in butter.
Stir in tuna, soup, mayonnaise and milk, mushrooms and pimento. Meanwhile, cook noodles according to directions on bag.
Drain in colander.
In a 2-quart greased casserole, combine noodles and tuna mixture.
Top with bread crumbs, tossed with 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until browned and bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: peach cream pie(old german recipe)
directions: Peel and slice peaches and arrange, cut side up, in unbaked shell.
Combine sugar and cornstarch, then add cream, vanilla and salt and stir well.
Pour over peaches.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° for 30 minutes or until peaches are tender.

title: potato fajitas
directions: Slice chicken into strips.
Marinate in Fajita Marinade about 1 hour.
Saute chicken and onion in oil until onions are tender. Add peppers and cook about 3 minutes or until chicken is thoroughly cooked.
Slit top of potato, squeeze to fluff, spoon mixture over.
Serve with cheese and sour cream.

title: happy rice
directions: Dice bacon and cook; drain.
Reserve 2 to 3 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Saute celery and onion in drippings.

title: asparagus in its own juice
directions: Cut off tough bottom ends of asparagus and discard.
Peel stocks with vegetable peeler (optional).
Place asparagus in skillet or any pan large enough so spears can lay flat.
Barely cover with cold water.
Add butter and salt and bring to boil, uncovered, over high heat.
Stir so they cook evenly.
They are done when water has evaporated, leaving only concentrated buttery juice of asparagus.
If not tender, add a little more water and continue cooking.
Grind fresh pepper to taste over asparagus. Serves 2.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients well.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press crisscross in each cookie with a fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool, then remove to racks.

title: cottage cheese cookies
directions: Melt margarine.
Add flour, cottage cheese, eggs and salt. Mix all together and refrigerate overnight.
Then roll out and cut into strips.

title: polynesian smoked sausage with rice
directions: While rice cooks, cover and cook sausage whole in 1/2 cup water for about 5 minutes.
Remove and cut in thin slices.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend in blender on high for 1 min., makes 4-5 glasses.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and put in an ovenproof pie plate or dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with crackers and tortilla chips.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until cheese melts.

title: chocolate banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs, bananas, milk, and vanilla. Combine dry ingredients, add this to banana mixture and mix just until combined.

title: no such thing as too many strawberries
directions: Place cake on serving plate.
Cut 1-inch slice crosswise off top of the cake.
Set aside.
With a sharp knife cut around cake 1-inch from center hole and 1-inch from outer edge, leaving 1-inch thick cake walls and 1-inch thick base on bottom.
Remove cake from center and bottom (think of it as scooping cake out of a bowl). Reserve cake pieces.
In a large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice, almond extract and food coloring.
Stir in reserved torn cake pieces and chopped strawberries.
Fold in 1 cup whipped topping.
Fill cavity of cake with strawberry mixture.
Replace top of cake.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Frost with remaining whipped topping.
Garnish with strawberries.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: company casserole(adapted from the brabson house)
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain and rinse.
Cook meat in butter until brown.
Add seasonings, onions and tomato sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in cottage cheese, sour cream and noodles.
Pour in casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: crunchy hot chicken salad
directions: Saute onions and celery until tender.
Combine first 8 ingredients; set aside.
Combine mayonnaise and water.
Beat with wire whisk until smooth.
Pour over chicken mixture; stir well. Add eggs and toss gently.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with potato chips and cheese. Bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: blackberry wine cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in Bundt pan which has been greased well and sprinkled with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Glaze when cool.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 12-inch pan according to directions, adding 1 cup of coconut to the cake mix.
Let cool.
Poke holes with end of spoon, pour milk and cream of coconut over cake.
Let sit about 10 minutes; spread whipped topping over cake.
Sprinkle remaining coconut over this.
Keep refrigerated.

title: english toffee bars
directions: Cook butter, sugar and water in a very heavy skillet, stirring constantly until mixture turns a coffee color.
Pour into a lightly buttered, flat 13 x 11-inch pan.
Lay Hershey bars on top and spread chocolate over brittle using a spatula.
Cover top with finely chopped pecans.

title: texas size almond crunch cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, blend sugar, powdered sugar, butter and oil until well mixed.
Add almond extract and eggs; mix well.
Lightly spoon flour in measuring cup, level off.
Slowly blend in flour, wheat flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar at low speed.
By hand, stir in almond and brickle chips.
Chill if desired.
Shape into large balls, roll in granulated sugar.
Place 5-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
With fork dipped in sugar, flatten in crisscross fashion.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 18 minutes until brown around edges.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen large cookies.

title: mushrooms and more
directions: Chop and saute mushrooms with 2 tablespoons butter.
Butter 3 slices bread and cut in 1-inch squares.
Place in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: *I increase these some.

title: cheesy ricotto ziti
directions: Melt butter and bread crumbs together.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with salad.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Sift flour and mix together with sugar and baking soda. Add pineapple,	vanilla, walnuts and eggs to dry ingredients. Pour into
a 9 x 12-inch ungreased casserole pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown meat, onions, and green pepper.
Drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat and pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Bring to a boil, but DO NOT boil.
Place in jars and seal.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine in oblong baking dish.
Sprinkle 3/4 package of dressing mix over this and press evenly over bottom and sides to form a crust.
Layer chicken pieces over crust.
In bowl, mix together soups and broth.
Pour evenly over chicken.
Cover with 1/4 package dressing mix.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meal-in-a-muffin
directions: Blend dry ingredients and stir in remaining ingredients. Spoon into cupcake cups and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes approximately 3 dozen muffins.
Allow to cool completely.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar.
Add onion juice and stir well.
With mixer set on beating setting, add oil very slowly, beating constantly.
Continue beating until dressing is quite thick.
Add poppy seed and food coloring.
Continue to beat 3 to 5 minutes longer.
Put into glass container with tight fitting lid.

title: jalapeno sausage corn bread
directions: Combine 1 cup corn meal, milk, eggs, salt, soda, bacon drippings and corn in a bowl; mix and set aside.
Saute sausage until lightly browned; drain thoroughly and set aside.
Sprinkle remaining corn meal in a greased 10-inch iron skillet; pour half of corn meal batter into skillet and sprinkle with sausage.
Top with onion, then cheese.
Add pepper evenly on top; pour remaining batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until slightly tender, about 25 minutes.

title: famous dump salad
directions: Empty fruit cocktail (drained) into a bowl.
Sprinkle strawberry Jell-O over fruit cocktail and stir well.
Add cottage cheese and stir again.
Fold Cool Whip into this mixture and chill 2 or 3 hours.

title: curry vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Use with raw veggies.
Keeps well in refrigerator.
Makes 1 cup.
Easily doubled.

title: pasta asparagus
directions: Saute for 2 to 3 minutes:
olive oil, garlic, hot sauce and red pepper flakes.
Add asparagus, cut into 1-inch pieces.
Cook until tender.
Toss over cooked noodles.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.

title: cornbread pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Add soup and water, 1 teaspoon salt, pepper, chili powder, corn, green pepper and mix well.
Simmer 15 minutes and pour into a greased casserole dish. Sift the cornmeal, sugar, flour and remaining salt and baking powder into a bowl.
Add egg and milk; stir lightly.
Add fat and mix.
Spread over beef mixture and bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: quick and easy gumbo
directions: Put gumbo mix and tomatoes in a pot and bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Stir and simmer 15 minutes.
Add the chicken with rice soup and the shrimp and simmer 10 more minutes.
Ready to eat now.
So good!

title: angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy; add vanilla and cream of tartar, beating slightly.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar, beating well after each addition; continue beating until stiff and glossy.
Do not underbeat.

Spoon meringue into well-greased 9-inch pie plate. Use a spoon to shape meringue into pie shell, swirling sides high. Bake at 275° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 250° and bake an additional 30 to 35 minutes or until meringue is lightly browned. Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually beat in 1/4 to 1/2 cup sugar, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Cook in top of double boiler, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened. Cool slightly.
Combine whipping cream and 2 tablespoons sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Spoon half into meringue shell. Spread with lemon filling and top with remaining whipped cream. Cover and refrigerate at least 24 hours.
(A heavenly dessert.)

title: himmel und erde (heaven and earth)(mashed potatoes with apples)
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water for 15 minutes; drain off most of the water and add the apples.
Cook until both are soft.
Put mixture into a bowl and mash with salt, sugar and butter.

title: fruit bars
directions: Boil raisins, water and Crisco for 10 minutes and let cool to lukewarm.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Ice with powdered sugar and milk.

title: "black joe" cake in pan
directions: Mix all ingredients together in mixer or by hand.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Frost when cool with icing of your choice.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Stem, wash and scoop out centers of green peppers.
Blanch in boiling salt water for 5 minutes.
Combine ground beef, onion, 1/2 can tomato sauce, salt, pepper and rice.
Stuff peppers with mixture.
Cover with 1 1/2 cans tomato sauce.
Can add grated cheese, if desired.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: hidden valley ranch pinwheels
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, and spread on tortillas. Drain vegetables and blot dry on paper towels. Sprinkle equal amount of remaining ingredients on top of cream cheese.
Chill 2 hours. Cut into 1 slices, spirals up.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and cocoa.
Bring to a boil.
Mix with eggs, vanilla and milk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: milky way cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Melt candy bars and butter, stirring frequently, in a large, heavy Dutch oven over low heat.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar. Combine egg yolks, buttermilk and baking soda in small bowl until blended.
Combine flour and salt in another bowl.
Add to candy mixture alternately with buttermilk mixture, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Stir in pecans.
In clean mixer bowl, beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into batter.

title: root beer
directions: Fill 2-quart pitcher almost full of water.
Measure 3 teaspoons McCormick root beer and dump in pitcher, swishing teaspoon each time in pitcher.
Then add sugar and stir.
Quick and easy.

title: grandma d's goulash
directions: Combine.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peach cobbler(makes 10 servings)
directions: Line a 16 x 9-inch glass baking dish with 5 pie crusts. Crusts will overlap and should completely cover dish bottom and sides.
Mix peaches and their juice, sugar, brown sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon, vanilla, lemon extract, butter and walnuts.
Pour into pastry-lined dish.
Cut one pie crust in strips and decorate the top of the filling.
Place in preheated 350° oven and cook 1 hour or until top is brown and edges are beginning to brown.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add nuts, oil, apples, eggs and vanilla.
Stir with spoon, do not use electric mixer. Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cheese manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti to package directions.
Cool in single layer on wax paper.
Combine Parmesan cheese, 1 cup of Mozzarella cheese, spinach, salt and pepper.
Spoon into manicotti shells.
Spread single layer of spaghetti sauce on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Arrange manicotti shells in pan in single layer.
Cover with remaining sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350°
for 40 minutes, covered, with aluminum foil.
Then remove foil and bake 15 minutes longer.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mexican chicken and rice
directions: Over medium-high heat, in a large skillet, heat oil. Add in chicken, onion and pepper. Cook and stir until chicken is cooked. Add corn, broth and salsa.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice. Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes. Fluff with a fork. Top with cheese. Serve when cheese is melted.

title: baked alaska pie
directions: Mix coconut and melted butter and press into 8 or 9 inch pie pan.
Bake at 300 until golden brown.
Melt marshmallows and chocolate in milk over hot water.
Remove from heat, add vanilla and cool.
Pack slightly softened ice cream into crust and swirl in cooled chocolate sauce.
Freeze until VERY firm.
Make meringue of 3 egg whites and 6 Tbsp. sugar.
Seal to edges of crust. Sprinkle on 2/3 c. coconut (optional).
Place on board or large cookie sheet.
Bake at 500 about 2 minutes.
Serve IMMEDIATELY.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix dry gelatin and pineapple with juice.
Add Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch bits in double boiler.
Add nuts and noodles. Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper or foil.
When cool, store in an airtight container.

title: mexican casserole
directions: In large skillet, brown hamburger meat and onion.
Add Ranch Style beans, soup and Ro-Tel.
Heat until hot.

title: texas cornbread
directions: Mix corn meal, baking powder and sugar together.
Add one egg at a time, blend.
Add sour cream, corn, cheese, pepper and oil. Blend until mixed and pour into 8 x 8
baking dish.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in a small pan or in microwave.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in milk.
Continue cooking on stove or in microwave until thickened and smooth, about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour melted butter in large mixing bowl.
Put layer of corn flakes in casserole pan.
Mix shredded cabbage with melted butter.
Place on top of corn flakes. Mix soup, milk, onion, mayonnaise and water chestnuts.
Pour on top of cabbage, then top with grated cheese.
Crush remainder of corn flakes and spread on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: oriental quick chicken
directions: In a saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add toasted almonds. Serve over hot, fluffy rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Let broccoli thaw and mix all together. Bake at 400° until brown.

title: barbecue sauce for pork
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes; strain to remove the lemon slices.

title: "i can do" cashew clusters
directions: Place 3 blocks of almond bark in a glass dish and microwave for 2 minutes or until creamy smooth. While cooking, put a piece of wax paper on a tray.
After bark is ready, slowly mix in cashews. Cover cashews thoroughly, then drop on the wax paper by the teaspoonfuls.

title: mushroom cheese appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2 pan.
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms; beat vigorously 20 strokes. Press dough in bottom of pan with floured hands.
Cook and stir sausage in skillet until brown.
Drain.
Mix sausage, onions and mayo.
Remove stems of mushrooms.
Finely chop stems of mushrooms. Stir into sausage mixture.
Fill mushroom caps with sausage mixture.
Place mushrooms in a row on the dough in the pan; sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Cover pan loosely with aluminum foil.
Bake 20 minutes; remove foil.
Bake until cheese is bubbly, 5-10 minutes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix cheese, flour, salt, pepper and garlic powder together in a plastic bag.
Toss wet potatoes to coat with cheese mixture. Place butter in an 8 x 10-inch baking dish to melt in a preheated 350° oven.
Add potatoes to melted butter and bake uncovered for 45 to 50 minutes or until tender and golden brown.
Turn potatoes once during baking time.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: caramel corn(microwave)
directions: Heat the first 6 ingredients until warm.
Pour syrup over popcorn and place in a brown paper bag.
Microwave on High for 1 minute; shake.
Microwave on High 1 minute; shake.
Microwave on High 1/2 minute; shake.
Microwave on High 1/2 minute; shake. Place on cookie sheets to dry.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and "dump" in bowl or freeze and cut in squares.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Scrub and rinse potatoes.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through.
Use a handle of a spoon to prevent knife from cutting all the way.
Place potatoes in a baking dish.
Fan them slightly.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter. Sprinkle with herbs.
(Try to get herbs in between slices.)
Bake at 425° for about 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake for another 10 to 15 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onions and green chilies and saute 2 minutes.
Add all other ingredients and layer with tortillas (tortillas torn in half work best) in a 13x9 inch dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: chocolate spiders
directions: Break candy bar in small pieces into a small bowl.
Set in a larger bowl filled with hot water.
When melted, add coconut and cereal; stir.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Set in refrigerator.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: oyster stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients together.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: super bubble loaf
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine yeast and warm water.
Let stand for a few minutes.
Add milk, egg, honey, salt and thyme. Add about 1 cup flour.
Beat until batter is smooth.
Gradually add rest of flour until a rather stiff dough forms.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in bowl.
Cover.
Let rise 1 hour.
Punch down. Put on lightly floured surface; knead a few times.
Divide in half.
Cut each half in 8 even pieces.
Shape in a small ball. Place 8 rolls in a greased loaf pan.
Drizzle with melted butter. Repeat with other pan.
Cover; let rise 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 400° for about 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight. Serve with crackers.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter, margarine and chocolate chips in saucepan. Put Chex in large bowl with a lid.
Pour melted mixture over Chex and stir to coat evenly.
Pour powdered sugar over hot coated mix. Put lid on container and shake well until coated.
Store in airtight container.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Fry ground meat in shortening until brown. Add onions, celery, green pepper, garlic and eggplant. Fry until wilted. Add salt and pepper; add water and cook tender and still juicy. Add 1 cup bread crumbs; mix well. Place in casserole dish. Sprinkle remaining bread crumbs on top. Bake at 400° until brown, about 40 minutes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add baking powder and salt with flour and sift.
Add to other mixture and add vanilla and mix lightly.
Roll out in thickness desired or biscuit thickness.
Cut out.
Bake on cookie sheet until slightly brown. Add nuts, if desired.

title: banana bran loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray an 8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with vegetable oil cooking spray or oil lightly.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Dredge nuts and raisins in flour. Beat eggs and applesauce. Combine all ingredients and bake at 350 degrees for 35-40 minutes in shallow pan or muffin tins. Batter can be frozen for use later.

title: creamy onion soup
directions: Coarsely chop onion and saute in butter in a medium stock pot. Add potatoes and carrot and saute 2 to 3 minutes before adding broth to the pot.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add cream cheese, stirring to blend.
Cool slightly and puree, in batches, in a blender.
Return puree to the pot.
Add milk and Cheddar cheese and heat on low until well blended.
Season with salt and white pepper to taste.
Serve warm, topped with croutons or toast rounds. Serves 4.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, milk, soda, flour, vanilla and bananas.
Mix by hand.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and then add all liquids.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in Bundt pan.

title: mexican beef delight
directions: Brown meat and pour off fat.
Add salt, pepper, onion, garlic powder, soup, tomato sauce, chilies, water, beans and chestnuts. Simmer about 5 minutes.

title: knock you naked
directions: In a large bowl mix cake mix, nuts, 1/3 cup milk and melted butter.
Press 1/2 of batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop 1/2 cup popcorn and pour into large bowl.
In a medium saucepan, melt 1 stick butter.
Add Karo syrup and brown sugar. Cook on medium-high heat.
Bring mixture to boil.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add 1 tablespoon baking soda.
Mix and pour over popcorn; mix quickly.
Cool and break apart.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: Roll in nuts if desired and form into ball.
Serve with crackers.
Refrigerate a few hours.
Can be made a day ahead.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Mix 3/4 cup dairy sour cream and 1 tablespoon of sugar and put over fruit.

title: love apple pie
directions: Blend ketchup and lemon juice.
Combine with apples.
Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Cut in butter until thoroughly mixed. Fill pie shell with apples.
Top with sugar mixture.
Bake in a 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until apples are cooked.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Prepare jello according to package directions, reducing water by 2 cups, to use a total of 6 cups water.
Add strawberries and juice.
Chill.
Prepare cake according to package directions.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
When cake is done, remove from oven and, while still hot, cut into random squares (1 to 2-inch squares). Pour slightly thickened jello over cake and gently press cake into pan and flatten top.
Chill until firm.
Spread whipped topping over cake and serve.

title: cold spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package.
After spaghetti is cooked, drain and rinse well in cold water.
Add all the vegetables together with noodles.
Add seasonings (such as seasoned salt, Lawry's 17 seasonings, etc.) and mix.
Add Italian dressing; mix well.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: jello angel cake
directions: Pour boiling water over Jell-O, sugar and lemon juice; let set until quite thick, but not completely set.
Whip evaporated milk and add Jell-O mixture, beating all the time, until thoroughly mixed and like whipped cream.
Put a small amount of Jell-O mixture on bottom of large angel food cake pan.
Put 1 layer of cake on top, then another layer of mixture, layer of cake, layer of mixture and layer of cake (top).
Let set in refrigerator until firm (overnight), then unmold on large plate and decorate top and sides with whipped cream.

title: lemon squares
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix flour and powdered sugar.
Stir into melted oleo.
Press down firmly.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese chicken
directions: In skillet over medium heat in hot margarine, cook chicken until brown on both sides, about 10 minutes.
Stir in soup and water.
Add broccoli and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover.
Cook 10 minutes or until broccoli is done and chicken no longer pink.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with tossed green salad and hot rolls.

title: deep dish taco squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix baking mix and water; press into a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake 10 minutes.
Brown meat with green pepper and onion; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and seasonings; spoon over warm crust.
Mix sour cream, cheese and dressing. Spoon over meat mixture.
Top with paprika, if desired.
Bake 25 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes; cut into squares.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch chunks.
Steam potatoes in a steamer for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, cut the beans into 2-inch lengths.
Add beans to steamer and cook for 8 minutes longer.

title: turtle cake
