directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour half of batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 minutes.
Combine milk, butter and caramels, microwave 2 1/2 minutes and beat.
Pour caramel mixture over cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and then nuts on top.
Pour remaining batter on top and bake 20 minutes.

title: cocktail sausages
directions: Melt jelly and chili sauce in a large skillet. Add sausages and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: pickled beets or eggs
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar and spices.
Bring to a boil and add eggs or beets.
Bring to boil again, then turn down.
Put in jars and seal.

title: hidden hot dogs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Separate rolls into triangles; flatten slightly.
Wrap hot dog into roll.
Add 1/2 slice of cheese, if desired.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden.

title: breading for fried fish
directions: Beat egg and milk together.
Combine crumbs, salt and pepper. Dip fish in crumbs, then egg, then again in crumbs.
Cook fish, skin side down, in 1/8-inch shortening.
Brown on one side then the other.
About 10 minutes or until flaky.

title: lemon sweet potatoes
directions: In a bowl, combine sweet potatoes (cooked, peeled and mashed), lemon juice and salt.
Beat in the butter, egg yolks and pepper to taste.

Transfer the mixture to a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole, top it with lemon slices and brush the top with melted butter. Bake the casserole in a preheated, moderately slow oven (325°) for 45 minutes or until it is heated through.
Serves 8.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix the ingredients in order and bake 1/2 hour in greased Pyrex baking dish (8 x 12-inch) at 325°.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Combine cake mix and dry pudding.
Mix well.
Mix beaten eggs, milk and oil together.
Add dry ingredients mixture.
Fold in chocolate chips and 3/4 of the grated German chocolate.
Cook 45 to 60 minutes (until done).

title: southern spice cookies
directions: In cup dissolve baking soda in water.
In bowl mix flour, salt and spices.
In another bowl blend butter, sugar and eggs.
Add dissolved baking soda.
Blend thoroughly with flour mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Using a teaspoon, form individual cookies on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Yields 5 1/2 dozen.

title: caesar chicken
directions: *Important:
Make with olive oil and balsamic vinegar.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Thaw potatoes and mix with other ingredients.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Top with cornflakes and bake for 25 more minutes.
If you want this dish to be served as main dish, you can add hamburger meat or sausage.

title: green beans and mushrooms
directions: Drain beans and mushrooms liquid into saucepan.
Boil liquid rapidly until reduced to about 1/2 cup.
Add drained beans, mushrooms and butter (margarine).
Heat to serve.

title: cranberry pork chops
directions: Crumble beef into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add onion. Microwave, uncovered, 6 minutes.
Drain off as much fat as possible.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Cover. Microwave 7 to 8 minutes until heated through.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Heat broiler.
Mix salad dressing, mustard and honey in a small bowl.
Place chicken on rack of broiler pan.
Brush with 1/2 of the dressing mixture.
Broil 5 inches from heat for 16 to 20 minutes or until chicken is cooked through, turning once and brushing with remaining salad dressing mixture.
Makes 4 servings.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Cream butter and sugar. Add egg and vanilla. Add flour mixture in 4 parts, beating just until smooth, after each addition. Mix in oats and coconut. Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with additional coconut. Bake at 350° for 9 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Yields 4 dozen.

title: saucy steak skillet
directions: Pound flour into round steak and cut into 2-inch squares. Brown; set aside.
Add chopped onion and cook until tender. Drain and save juice from potatoes.
Add enough water to potato juice to make 1 cup.
To meat, add juice, water, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, chopped peppers, salt, pepper, beef bouillon and marjoram leaves.
Simmer 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Rinse the frozen beans or canned beans.
Add to skillet.
Also, add potatoes and pimento.
Simmer until beans are tender (10 to 15 minutes). Serves 4.

title: chocolate tea cookies
directions: Cut cake into 2-inch strips.
Cut each strip into 4 equal pieces.
Cut each piece into 2 triangles.
Combine corn syrup, water and butter in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Heat until butter melts.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips until they melt.
Cool to room temperature.
Place each cake triangle onto 2 prong frying fork.
Spoon cooled chocolate glaze over cakes until well covered.
Place on cooling rack to allow excess chocolate to drip from cake.

title: fudge candy
directions: Cook to soft ball stage!
Remove from heat.
Add 1 tablespoon butter and 1 teaspoon flavoring; stir in.
Pour in buttered pan to cool; cut in squares.

title: frozen banana split salad
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Fold in fruits and pecans.
Turn into ring and freeze.
Let stand to thaw 30 to 45 minutes before serving.

title: peas and baby onions
directions: Fresh onions should be sauteed in butter until translucent. Add peas and 1/4 cup water.
Cook until tender.
If using canned onions, cook peas first until tender; add onions and butter until warm.
This is a traditional dish with baked or poached fish.
It is especially complimentary to salmon.
Makes 4 servings of 1/2 cup at 75 calories per serving.

title: oat muffins
directions: Mix oats and buttermilk.
Let set overnight.
Add to oats and buttermilk, egg, oil, brown sugar, nuts and raisins.
In separate bowl, mix together flour, baking powder, soda, and salt.
Fold into wet mixture until dry ingredients are just moistened.
Pour into greased muffin tin (12).
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.

title: peaches and cream squares salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add peaches, stirring until thawed.
Add bananas and walnuts.
Pour half of peach mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm (about 1 1/2 hours). Spread sour cream over jello.
Chill about 30 minutes.
Pour remaining jello over sour cream.
Chill until firm.

title: bourbon cake
directions: Combine cherries, raisins and bourbon; cover and soak overnight in refrigerator.
Then drain and reserve bourbon.
Cream sugar and shortening; add yolks.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to cream mixture alternating with bourbon.
Dust pecans with flour and set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into batter.
Add drained fruit and floured pecans.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in 275° oven 4 hours or until done.
Cool 2 to 3 hours in pan.
Wrap in cloth, wet with bourbon and wrap in foil.
Store in refrigerator at least 1 week.
Make at Thanksgiving and eat at Christmas.

title: french bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and put in casserole.
Mix with soup and 1/2 can of onion rings.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, covered.
Add rest of onion rings and cook for 10 more minutes, uncovered.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into biscuits.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: chili verde(green chili)
directions: Cut fat off steaks.
Cut steaks into bite sized pieces.
Fry until well done.
Remove meat and fry garlic and onion.
Remove garlic and onion.
Make gravy with drippings, flour and water. Return meat, garlic and onion to gravy with all other ingredients. Simmer.
Add 2 or 3 hot Fresno chilies, if desired.
Enjoy!!!!!

title: pecan patties
directions: Grind all together (except eggs and butter).
Mix with eggs and butter.
Make into patties and brown.
Pour 1 cup tomato juice over it and let simmer until tomato juice is used up.

title: egg strada
directions: Make 24 hours in advance.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Pour mixture evenly over ingredients in pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Shred cabbage and pack in sterile jars.
Pour in hot liquid and seal.

title: party dip
directions: Cut cheese in small chunks.
Put in crock-pot.
Add picante sauce and meat.
Cook on low heat, stirring occasionally.

title: young homemaker's pretzel
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate until dough is firm.
Roll dough into cylinders and bend into pretzel shapes.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: ham and broccoli bake(party fare)
directions: Cook frozen broccoli according to package directions; drain well.
In saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together soups and milk; add cheese.
Add drained broccoli, cooked onion, ham, uncooked rice and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.

title: crescent cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Press one package crescent roll dough over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pull up sides to make 1/2 inch rim.
Seal perforations.

title: white chocolate fudge
directions: In a heavy saucepan, bring sugar, milk and butter to a boil over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cook until mixture reaches 234° (soft ball stage) on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat; stir in Marshmallow creme, chocolate chips and nuts until they are melted.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Cool before cutting.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Add milk and eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in molasses and shortening. Pour into 8 x 8-inch shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lenora's quick spanish rice
directions: Melt 1/4 cup of bacon drippings in saucepan.
Add sliced onion, green pepper and Minute rice.
Stir over high heat until lightly browned.
Add the tomato sauce.
Mix mustard, pepper and salt with 1 1/2 cups of hot water and add to saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.

title: spring shower punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except lemon slices in large punch bowl; stir until concentrate is dissolved.
Add ice cubes and lemon slices.
Makes about 2 1/4 quarts or enough for 18 (4 ounce) punch cup servings.

title: my meatless pasta sauce
directions: In a large saucepan or kettle, put the kitchen ready tomatoes. Add onion, green pepper, celery, carrot, mushrooms, fennel, dried parsley, basil and sugar.
Add 1 of the tomato cans of water. Bring to a boil.
Turn down to simmer and cook down to desired thickness.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix together 1/4 cup soup with remaining ingredients.
Shape into oblong patties, place into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Mix remainder of soup with 1/3 cup water and pour over meat.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: ann's coq au vin
directions: Remove fat and skin from halved chicken breasts.
Place chicken in a large shallow baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients well and pour over the chicken.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil. Marinate in refrigerator at least 3 hours or overnight (overnight is best).
Remove from refrigerator and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 4 to 8 servings.

title: blue cheese and walnut toasts(hors d'oeuvre)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brush 1 side of slices with melted butter and bake on cookie sheet until just golden (7 minutes). Cool slightly.
(Can be prepared 2 days ahead and stored in cookie tin or other airtight container.)

title: butternut cake
directions: Mix ingredients. Bake at 350°.

title: ziti bake
directions: Combine ziti and hamburg.
Fold in Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese and 1/2 spaghetti sauce.
Fold in ziti and hamburg.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour rest of the sauce over top.
Sprinkle with 8 ounces Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes. Cuts like lasagna.

title: pretzel delight dessert
directions: Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions.
Mix pretzels, margarine and 1 tablespoon sugar together.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 7 to 8 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine buttermilk and pudding; fold in whipped topping. Place 1/2 of fruit in mixture.
Place remaining fruit on top.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Into a large bowl, sift together the flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in the carrots, raisins, pecans, coconut and apples.
In smaller bowl, beat the eggs, oil, water and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture and stir until just combined; don't beat!
Spoon into well oiled or lined muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 30.

title: chicken appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients; spread over rolls.
Drizzle melted butter over top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: cowboy roast
directions: Brown all sides of roast.
Cover with water and add pinto beans (enough to fill in around roast).
Add green chilies.
Season to taste with dried mustard, seasoned salt, pepper and chili peppers. Cover and simmer 6 to 8 hours or all day.

title: mound cake
directions: Combine sour cream and sugar in bowl; mix well.
Stir in coconut.
Chill overnight.
Prepare and bake cake mix according to package directions, using two 8-inch cake pans.
Split each layer into 2 layers.
Spread coconut mixture between layers and over top of cake.

title: busy day peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine flour, sugar and milk in bowl, mixing well and pour over melted oleo.
Do not stir.
Spoon peaches evenly into dish and pour peach syrup over entire mixture.
Additional sugar may be sprinkled on if desired. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until dough has risen and browned.

title: maine blueberry cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Cream margarine, sugar and egg. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add lemon flavoring and blueberries.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon love note bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Pat into 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Mix sugar, flour, lemon juice and baking powder together.
Pour batter over baked shortbread and bake 25 more minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar icing; cut in bars.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, heat hot margarine.
Cook onion with thyme and garlic powder until tender, stirring often.
Add broth, corn, green beans and tomatoes.
Heat to boiling.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add chicken.
Heat thoroughly.
Stir occasionally.
Serves 5.

title: chocolate dipped brownies
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, bring sugar, butter and water to a boil; remove from the heat.
Stir in 1 cup of chocolate chips and vanilla; stir until smooth.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until well mixed.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda; stir into chocolate mixture.
Stir in another cup of chips. Pour into a greased 9 inch square baking pan.
Bake at 325 degrees for 35 minutes.
Cool completely.
Place in the freezer for 30-40 minutes (do not freeze completely).
Cut into bars.
In a microwave or double boiler, melt remaining chips with shortening; stir until smooth.
Using a small fork, dip brownies to completely coat; shake off excess.
Place on waxed paper-lined baking sheets, immediately sprinkle with nuts.
Allow to harden.
Store in an airtight container in a cool place.

title: kahlua
directions: Combine coffee, sugar and water.
Stir well until dissolved. Cool.
Add brandy.
Pour into 2 bottles.
Cut vanilla bean in half and put one in each bottle.
Close tightly and let stand at least one month.

title: beef manicotti
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add all other ingredients except shells and
cheese.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Cook shells as directed
on
package.
Stuff
shells
with
meat mixture. Place in
x
11-inch
baking
dish.
Sprinkle
with cheese; cover and
heat
thoroughly.
Cover
with foil while heating. Add about 1/4
cup of water before covering with foil to make steam while heating to prevent shells from sticking to bottom and sides and to prevent drying out while heating.
Makes 5 to 7 servings.

title: bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight; do not drain.
Add beans, ham bone, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Cover; simmer 3 to 3 1/2 hours, adding onion, thinly sliced the last half-hour.
Remove ham bone and peel meat from bone.
Mash beans slightly with back of spoon.
Return meat to soup.

title: pumpkin pecan layer cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl combine wafer crumbs, chopped pecans and 3/4 cup butter.
Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often, until crumbly (1 to 2 minutes).
Press mixture evenly on bottom of 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
In same bowl combine cake mix, pumpkin, 1/4 cup butter and eggs.
Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often, until well mixed (2 to 3 minutes).
Spread 1 3/4 cups batter over crumbs in each pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes and remove from pans.
Cool completely.

title: corn chex tamale pie
directions: In a 10-inch baking dish, put 1 cup Corn Chex with 1/2 cup onions and 1 can tamales.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup grated cheese. Repeat this step.
Pour 1/2 cup water and juice from the 2 cans of tamales over casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot bean dish
directions: Brown meat and chopped onion.
Drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together.
Bake, uncovered, in large casserole dish for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate revel bars
directions: Combine ingredients; set aside.

title: baked pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet; season.
Combine soup, onion rings, ketchup and Worcestershire in bowl.
Place chops in bottom of casserole.
Pour soup mix over pork chops.
Cover; cook at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
May be topped with bread crumbs and dotted with butter.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump cherry pie filling and pineapple into 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over the top of the fruit.
Cut butter into 12 patties and arrange on top of the dry cake mix. Sprinkle nuts over the top of the cake.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Take 3 eggs, vinegar, sugar, dry mustard and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Cook until thick. (Watch close, it will scorch.) Cool and add the salad dressing or mayo. Pour over other ingredients. Stir and chill.

title: snack oysterettes
directions: Put oysterettes, garlic powder, dill and dressing in large paper bag.
Shake well.
Add oil and continue shaking well.
Open bag and let sit on counter to "dry."
Store in airtight container.
tags: dry Hidden Valley original salad dressing

title: cheese pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: low-fat pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Coat an 8-inch square baking pan with vegetable cooking spray; set aside.
In mixer bowl, beat milk and Prune Puree to blend thoroughly.
Add flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons of cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Beat just to blend thoroughly. Spread evenly in pan.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken with bouillon cubes in 3 quarts boiling water. Remove chicken when done; drain well.
Reserve the liquid that the chicken was cooked in to cook the spaghetti.
Skin and debone chicken when cool enough to handle.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces and place in a very large mixing bowl.
Cook broken spaghetti in the liquid that chicken was cooked in.
Drain spaghetti and add it to the chicken.
Place slices cheese over chicken and spaghetti.
Let the heat from the spaghetti soften and melt the cheese.
Stir very well.

title: crunchy cheese and ham ball
directions: Mix all but nuts, then roll in nuts.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: chocolate coconut balls
directions: Mix melted butter and nuts; add coconut, sugar, condensed milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Shape into balls the size of quarters. Chill for 15 minutes. Melt paraffin and chocolate pieces (or peanut butter pieces) in top of double boiler.
Dip balls into melted mixture using toothpicks or tongs.
Place on waxed paper to dry.
Keeps well in covered container.
Yields 60 pieces.

title: cheesy broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli until barely tender; drain well.
Stir soup and sour cream together.
Add remaining ingredients to soup and sour cream mixture.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Dip chicken breasts in bread crumbs. Fry in vegetable oil until light brown. Place on foil-lined cookie sheet. Top with spaghetti sauce. Bake 30 minutes. Turn off oven and sprinkle with cheese. Let stand in oven 5 to 10 minutes until cheese melts. Serve with angel hair pasta tossed with butter and garlic powder.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Add rest of ingredients. Simmer until seasoned.
Stir often.
Crock-pot works well.

Place breasts in large shallow baking dish;

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli slightly.
Melt butter and cheese; pour over broccoli.
Crush crackers; mix with 1/2 stick butter (melted). Sprinkle on top of broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a glass dish.

title: skillet biscuit loaf
directions: In a nonstick skillet over low heat, melt margarine with garlic.
Coat biscuits with cheese overlapping slightly.
Cover. Cook over low heat for 8 minutes.
Invert biscuits.
Cover; cook 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli; mix together with other ingredients. Place in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. After 15 minutes, stir.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: pineapple-cherry whip
directions: Best made and chilled several hours before serving.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Place all of the ingredients in a large mixing bowl; mix well. (I use my hands.)
Pinch off dough and roll in your hands to make small balls.

title: strawberry big top
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate or freeze for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Cream together white sugar, brown sugar, oleo, cinnamon, eggs and salt.
Add to oatmeal mixture.
Then add flour with soda.
Mix well.
Bake in long pan greased and floured for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
While still warm, add icing.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni according to the package. Drain well.
In a saucepan, melt butter.
Whisk in the flour to make a paste.
Stir in milk.
Bring to a simmer over medium heat, whisking until thickened (about 1 minute).
Add the cheese, salt and pepper and whisk until smooth.
Add macaroni to the cheese sauce.
Scrape into a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes (uncovered).
Add a little shredded Cheddar cheese on top the last 5 minutes of baking.

title: old fashioned macaroni cheese with ham
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
In a large bowl, mix cooked macaroni, ham and cheese until well blended.
Spoon into baking dish.
Evenly pour the evaporated milk over ingredients in the baking dish.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for 55 to 65 minutes or until top is crisply brown and bubbling.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: margie's plum cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs one at a time, beating each time.
Mix dry ingredients and add to mixture; add plums and then pecans.
Bake in tube pan 75 minutes at 300°.

title: hummus
directions: Put chickpeas into food processor along with the olive oil, yogurt, garlic and lemon juice.
Blend until smooth.
If you want it a little thinner, blend in chicken stock at this time.
Add pepper to taste.
Serve with pita bread, cut into triangles and toasted.
Akmak crackers are special with this also.

title: garlic shrimp and vegetables
directions: Heat butter and oil in medium skillet or wok over medium heat. Add onions and bell pepper.
Stir-fry 2 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Add shrimp and garlic; stir-fry 3 to 5 minutes or until shrimp turn opaque.
Stir in lime juice. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Mix cheese with margarine.
Sift flour, salt, red pepper and paprika.
Add to cheese mixture; blend well.
Add Rice Krispies; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Saute onions and peppers in butter.
Add cheese and sour cream.
Stir over low heat to melt.
Add tomatoes, spaghetti and chicken.
Mix well.
Add peas.

title: baked corn
directions: Melt butter in a casserole dish.
Mix together other ingredients and pour into casserole dish.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix together and put into oblong pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli at room temperature or in a pan over low heat or a microwave, but do not cook.
Drain well.
Beat eggs.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a greased casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes, then cool.
Refrigerate overnight.
Grate potatoes and onions; mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: window cleaner
directions: Mix water and cornstarch into a spray bottle; use as you would any window cleaner.
Discard after several weeks and mix new batch.

title: squash casserole
directions: Chop onion.
Seed and dice pepper.
Fry and crumble bacon. Dice tomato and cook in small pan until soft and most of the juice has thickened.
Cut squash into small pieces.
Saute squash, pepper and onion in small amount of bacon grease, in small batches.
After all is sauteed, mix in a large bowl or pan, other ingredients, except cheese and bacon.

title: wash day cake
directions: Grease long cake pan.
Pour in can of pineapple.
Spread evenly, cherry pie filling over this.
Sprinkle cake mix.
Add nuts.
Cut up butter on top of this.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream on top.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix the first 10 ingredients well and make into small balls. Arrange in baking dish.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Fold in noodles and almonds just before baking.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: popsicles
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Stir until jello, sugar and Kool-Aid are dissolved.
Pour into popsicle molds or ice cube trays and freeze until solid.

title: teether bread stix
directions: Take 1 piece of bread and trim to a triangle shape.
Spread with peanut butter.
Use a red hot or red M&M for a nose.
Raisins or chocolate chips can be used for eyes and pretzels for the antlers.
Cupcakes can be frosted with chocolate frosting and decorated the same as the Rudolph sandwiches.

title: key lime pie
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until meringue is light brown.

title: devil dump cupcakes
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
"Dump" in everything else and mix.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 18.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats. Let stand for 20 minutes. Beat margarine until creamy. Gradually add sugar and beat until fluffy. Blend in vanilla and eggs. Add oats and mix well. Sift flour, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg together. Add to oat mixture and mix well. Pour into greased and floured 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Do not remove from pan. Add frosting.

title: dill pickles
directions: Mix together.
Pour over pickles in jar.
Seal tight.
Put in canner 3/4 full of water.
Bring to boil.
Boil about 4 to 5 minutes.
Turn off heat. Take out.
Reseal.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Put broth in saucepan and heat.
When broth is hot, slowly drizzle beaten eggs into broth while whisking rapidly.
Remove from heat and serve with crisp Chinese noodles.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix olives, English peas, string beans and pimentos; drain well.
Add celery, onion and almonds.
Mix together sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper; heat slightly to melt sugar.
Pour over mixed vegetables and refrigerate overnight.
Mix often.
Drain before serving.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together and pour into pie shells and freeze until ready to serve.

title: marshmallow meringue
directions: Cut marshmallows in quarters if large and place with milk in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, folding over and over until marshmallow are melted down to about half their original size. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and continue folding until mixture is smooth, yet light and spongy.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add salt and sugar slowly, beating constantly.
Carefully fold in slightly warm marshmallow mixture.
Pile on pie, pudding or cake. Place under broiler 3 inches from heat for 30 seconds or until meringue is a delicate brown.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch baking dish; stir in rice, onion, soup, water and salt.
Place chicken over the top of mixture. Sprinkle with black pepper.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy pork and rice
directions: Pour oil in bottom of skillet and arrange meat on it.
Add onion and green pepper.
Sprinkle on the rice.
Add catsup, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Pour boiling water or broth over all.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Allow to stand 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 4.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in salted water.
Set aside to cool.
Mix in casserole dish sugar, flour and cooking oil.
Beat eggs and mix with other ingredients.
Add cooked rice and milk.
Mix well.
Add flavoring.
Set casserole in pan of water and bake in 400° oven until brown and then at 300° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots and drain. Pour 1/2 of the carrots into a 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Dice 1/2 of the Velveeta over the top.
Repeat with carrots and cheese. Melt butter and saute onions until tender. Pour over carrots. Spread bread crumbs over the top. Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients
in large heavy pot.
Cook and stir until liquid turns light beige and peanuts start to pop. Remove from heat.
Add soda; stir well.
Pour over buttered plate or as thin as possible.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand awhile before serving.

title: chili-cheese dip
directions: Saute onion and bacon until onion is clear.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat over low heat until bubbly.
Stir frequently. Serve in chafing dish.

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar in a large bowl.
Add egg and beat well. Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Drop dough by teaspoons onto a greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: stroganoff in skillet
directions: Begin by heating vegetable oil in heavy skillet while shaking meat in flour to coat.
Then saute venison cubes until browned. Add soup mix and water.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or more until venison is tender.
Finally, add cream of mushroom soup and ketchup.
Heat thoroughly and serve over noodles or rice.
(Serves 4 to 6.)

title: filled cookies
directions: Cream together Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients.
Best to chill first.
On floured board, roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and put filling in center of each cookie.
Make another cookie and place on top, pressing sides together.
Prick tops 2 or 3 times.
Bake at 365° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: meatza
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; pat on bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate.
Cover with sliced cheese.
Spread cheese with catsup. Add mushrooms, oregano and grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Nice change from regular meat loaf.

title: haystacks
directions: Line baking sheet with waxed paper.
Melt chocolate in top of double boiler, stirring until smooth.
Add nuts and pretzels, stirring until coated.
Remove pan from heat and spoon by rounded teaspoonful onto baking sheet.
Cool to room temperature and refrigerate.
Makes 35 to 40.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon evenly into a six-cup muffin tin that has been sprayed with a cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 muffins.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook zucchini and onions in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrots and onion and zucchini mixture.
In bowl, combine stuffing mix and butter.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in bottom of 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture over stuffing mix. Sprinkle rest of stuffing over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
May add sausage to stuffing, if desired.
Also may top with shredded cheese before serving.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers well.
Snip ends off.
Place in sterilized jars.
Cover with boiling water.
Heat water, vinegar and salt to boiling.
Pour water off.
Add garlic.
Pour boiling brine over cucumbers.
Seal.
Heat in boiling water 5 minutes.
Leave at least 6 weeks before opening.

title: chicken chili rellenos
directions: Pound chicken breasts until 1/4 inch thick and divide in half. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In shallow bowl, mix together flour and cornmeal.
In each chili, wrap one piece of cheese and place on chicken breast half; roll, tucking in sides.
Fasten with wooden toothpicks.
Place each chicken roll in flour and cornmeal mixture, dredging to coat.

title: cherry, apple or peach cobbler
directions: Melt stick of butter in baking pan.
Mix, using wire whip, the sugar, flour and milk until blended smooth without lumps.
Pour flour mixture on top of melted butter in pan.
Pour peaches on top of flour mixture in pan.
Do not stir.
Put pan in oven; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable studded meat loaf
directions: Thoroughly mix together the beef, oats, egg yolk, carrots, onion, green pepper, celery and 1 tablespoon of the chili sauce. Shape mixture into a miniature loaf.
Place loaf in lightly greased pan.
Spread remaining 1 tablespoon chili sauce on top of loaf.
Bake, uncovered, in oven preheated to 375° for 45 to 55 minutes, or until done.

title: party crescent rolls
directions: Mix well the cheese, onion, mushrooms and Tabasco sauce. Spread on rolls.
Shape.
Cut in half.
Dip in melted butter, then in finely chopped pecans.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: breakfast before
directions: Saute sausage; drain.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and mustard. Layer sausage, bread cubes and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour egg mixture over top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: dirt, mud, worms
directions: Have children crunch Oreos with rolling pin, palm of hands, back of spoon, etc.
Put pieces to the side.
Mix chocolate pudding with milk according to directions in shaker container with secure lid.
Give each child a chance to shake pudding (you could shake and count).
Have children scoop pudding in see-through containers.
Add crunched Oreos.
Add gummy worms on top.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Combine egg, water and vinegar.
Add the water to the egg before vinegar; pour liquid into flour mixture all at once.
Blend with fork just until flour is all moistened.
This is an easy crust to handle and can be re-rolled without toughening.
Makes 2 or more double crust pies, depending on the size of pans.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Blend eggs and vanilla. Add other ingredients with sour cream.
Chill several hours or overnight.
On floured board roll out dough to 1/4 inch.
Cut with 3-inch cookie cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet; sprinkle with sugar or powdered sugar.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes. Yields 12 dozen.

title: mexican pasta
directions: Cook and drain pasta.
In saucepan, heat picante sauce, Parmesan cheese, margarine, sour cream and salt.
Add to pasta. Mix and serve.

title: gooey chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on package.

title: treasurer aspic
directions: In saucepan, simmer juice and pickling spice for 5 minutes, then strain. Combine gelatin and sugar. Soften gelatin in cold vegetable juice. Stir into hot juice to dissolve. Add remaining vegetable juice and lemon juice.
Chill until partly set, then fold in cheese and celery.
Pour into 6-cup mold. Chill until firm.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
